/jackson-mapper-asl/1.8.3/build/jacoco/effective/jackson_mapper_asl_1_8_3_jar/org/codehaus/jackson/map/ser/JdkSerializers$AtomicBooleanSerializer.class\n/tmp/pi-bash-c6c2a85107c1cad4.log:335:tests/src/org.codehaus.jackson/jackson-mapper-asl/1.8.3/build/jacoco/effective/jackson_mapper_asl_1_8_3_jar/org/codehaus/jackson/map/ser/JdkSerializers$AtomicLongSerializer.class\n/tmp/pi-bash-c6c2a85107c1cad4.log:354:tests/src/org.codehaus.jackson/jackson-mapper-asl/1.8.3/build/jacoco/effective/jackson_mapper_asl_1_8_3_jar/org/codehaus/jackson/map/ser/StdSerializers$BooleanSerializer.class\n/tmp/pi-bash-c6c2a85107c1cad4.log:360:tests/src/org.codehaus.jackson/jackson-mapper-asl/1.8.3/build/jacoco/effective/jackson_mapper_asl_1_8_3_jar/org/codehaus/jackson/map/ser/StdSerializers$LongSerializer.class\n/tmp/pi-bash-c6c2a85107c1cad4.log:367:tests/src/org.codehaus.jackson/jackson-mapper-asl/1.8.3/build/jacoco/effective/jackson_mapper_asl_1_8_3_jar/org/codehaus/jackson/map/ser/StdSerializers$StringSerializer.class\n/tmp/pi-bash-c6c2a85107c1cad4.log:371:tests/src/org.codehaus.jackson/jackson-mapper-asl/1.8.3/build/jacoco/effective/jackson_mapper_asl_1_8_3_jar/org/codehaus/jackson/map/ser/ToStringSerializer.class\n/tmp/human_new_issues_graphql.jsonl:1:{\"data\":{\"search\":{\"pageInfo\":{\"hasNextPage\":true,\"endCursor\":\"Y3Vyc29yOjEwMA==\"},\"issueCount\":120,\"nodes\":[{\"number\":4020,\"title\":\"Support for ch.qos.logback:logback-core:1.5.26\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/4020\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T11:41:13Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T13:49:51Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nch.qos.logback:logback-core:1.5.26\\n\\n### Reason for requesting the library\\n\\n_No response_\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"github-actions\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T11:42:43Z\",\"body\":\"Automation: No dependency issues were created by the triage workflow.\\n\\nThis typically means every dependency in the deps.dev expansion is already supported by the repository.\\n\\nPlan nodes:\\n```\\nch.qos.logback:logback-core:1.5.26\\n```\\n\\nSupported GA detected during checks:\\n```\\nch.qos.logback:logback-core\\n```\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/4020#issuecomment-4359117211\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T13:49:43Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `ch.qos.logback:logback-core:1.5.26`. Preserved work is available here:\\nhttps://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-4020-library-new-request-ch.qos.logback-logback-core-1.5.26-d420822e\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is native-image test validation, not dynamic-access coverage generation. The run reached `41/41` dynamic-access coverage (100%), and the preserved branch includes the final coverage commit (`9726e2a2`, `Dynamic-access coverage for ch.qos.logback.core.util.FileUtil (41/41)`), but the Gradle output shows `> Task :nativeTest FAILED`. The clearest blocker is a native runtime `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` for `java.lang.String.serialVersionUID`, raised during serialization in `AutoFlushingObjectWriterTest` and again from the `RemoteReceiverStreamClient` path. The native test report also shows additional failing/generated tests in `AggregationAssessorTest`, `ConsoleAppenderTest`, `EnvUtilTest`, `PropertyEvalScriptBuilderTest`, and `StringToObjectConverterTest`, so the test suite is still not valid under native image.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-core:1.5.26/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T13-44-12-153305Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/ch.qos.logback:logback-core:1.5.26/86c8cc3152d43c49c818b5eaeeebef91.out`\\n- `tests/src/ch.qos.logback/logback-core/1.5.26/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\\n- `tests/src/ch.qos.logback/logback-core/1.5.26/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Fix the native-test blocker on the preserved branch, starting with the missing serialization/reflection metadata for `java.lang.String.serialVersionUID` or by rewriting the affected serialization tests to avoid that unsupported path.\\n2. Rework the brittle generated tests that still fail under native image (`AggregationAssessorTest`, `ConsoleAppenderTest`, `EnvUtilTest`, `PropertyEvalScriptBuilderTest`, `StringToObjectConverterTest`, `RemoteReceiverStreamClientTest`).\\n3. Rerun validation for `ch.qos.logback:logback-core:1.5.26` and update the issue once `:nativeTest` passes.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/4020#issuecomment-4359590021\"}]}},{\"number\":3899,\"title\":\"Update existing library: ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.26\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3899\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T15:04:08Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T14:13:03Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.26\\nch.qos.logback:logback-core:1.5.26\\n\\n### Additional context and logs\\n\\nStarting with [release 1.5.26](https://github.com/qos-ch/logback/releases/tag/v_1.5.26), Logback has introduced new version properties files that are read at initialization time. When using a native image these files aren't available as resources, causing warnings during startup:\\n```\\n|-WARN in ch.qos.logback.classic.LoggerContext[default] - Versions of logback-classic and ? are different or unknown.\\n```\\nThis is especially annoying because a single warning during Logback initialization will cause *all* of its internal startup logging to become visible, so this produces a lot of noise.\\n\\nFor logback-classic, the file that needs to be available as a resource is `ch/qos/logback/classic/logback-classic-version.properties`. For logback-core, it's `ch/qos/logback/core/logback-core-version.properties`. \\n\\n### GraalVM version\\n\\nNot relevant, but was a 25 version\\n\\n### Operating system\\n\\nLinux\\n\\n### CPU architecture\\n\\nAMD64 (x86-64)\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T00:07:04Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.26` (`library-update-request`, workflow status `failure`). Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3899-library-update-request-ch.qos.logback-logback-classic-1.5.26-51f182a1\\n\\nThe most likely failure point was the update/finalization path around artifact URL population for an already-covered version, not the underlying Gradle test execution. `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.26/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` shows `populateArtifactURLs` completed but reported `No matching coordinates found for filter 'ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.26'`. In the repo, `metadata/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/index.json` already lists `1.5.26` under the `1.5.7` metadata entry with `test-version` `1.4.1`, and there is no `stats/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.5.26/execution-metrics.json`. In the preserved local Gradle outputs, the existing `tests/src/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.4.1` project ran `test` and `nativeTestCompile` successfully against the `1.5.26` JAR and produced a dynamic-access report with `4/18` covered calls, but that result was not recorded into stats. Please inspect `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.26/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` first, and if you check out the preserved worktree locally also inspect `build/tests/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.26/*.out`.\\n\\n1. Verify whether issue #3899 is stale or duplicate, since `1.5.26` is already present in `metadata/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/index.json`.\\n2. If coverage for `1.5.26` still needs to be refreshed, continue manually from the existing `1.4.1` test suite and write the missing stats/metadata update.\\n3. If the version is already sufficiently covered, close the issue or adjust the workflow so already-tested versions do not fail at `populateArtifactURLs`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3899#issuecomment-4356988855\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"jkuipers\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T10:37:48Z\",\"body\":\"I see that you've changed the title of the issue to only reference logback-classic: please note that this issue requires both logback-classic AND logback-core to be updated with their respective version properties file to address the issue. \",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3899#issuecomment-4358922933\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T11:40:45Z\",\"body\":\"> I see that you've changed the title of the issue to only reference logback-classic: please note that this issue requires both logback-classic AND logback-core to be updated with their respective version properties file to address the issue.\\n\\n@jkuipers I will open separate issue for logback-core. Thanks!\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3899#issuecomment-4359111517\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T14:12:54Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.26`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3899-library-new-request-ch.qos.logback-logback-classic-1.5.26-72c30579\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was test-generation validation for the new direct-module test suite, not artifact discovery. `stats/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.5.26/execution-metrics.json` shows the generation strategy itself completed successfully (`status: success`, 3 iterations, 289 generated LOC), and the final generation logs say targeted tests passed but the full suite still failed in `sequenceNumberAndCallerDataAreAvailableOnLoggingEvents` and `siftingAppenderRoutesEventsByMdcValue` (`human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.26/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T14-03-35-021907Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.26/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T14-05-18-592200Z.log`). The generated reports confirm this: `tests/src/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.5.26/build/test-results/test/TEST-ch_qos_logback.logback_classic.Logback_classicTest.xml` fails because caller data is empty, and `tests/src/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.5.26/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` also shows `java.nio.file.NoSuchFileException` for `alpha.log` in the sifting-appender test.\\n\\nThere is also a validation-path mismatch: the coordinate-level Gradle outputs under `build/tests/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.26/*.out` are mostly running the existing `tests/src/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.4.1` project against the `1.5.26` jar, while the generated `1.5.26` project has its own failing JVM/native reports. Dynamic-access coverage for the generated `1.5.26` project is still unavailable because `tests/src/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.5.26/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` was not produced. For context, artifact discovery and URL population appear to have completed; inspect `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.26/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` and `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.26/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` alongside the generation logs above.\\n\\n1. Re-run or inspect the generated `tests/src/ch.qos.logback/logback-classic/1.5.26` suite manually and fix or replace the failing `sequenceNumberAndCallerDataAreAvailableOnLoggingEvents` and `siftingAppenderRoutesEventsByMdcValue` tests.\\n2. Decide whether this library should keep the new direct-module `1.5.26` test project or continue using the existing `1.4.1` reuse path that already exercises the `1.5.26` jar.\\n3. After the test path is settled, regenerate dynamic-access coverage/stats for `1.5.26` and re-run validation.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3899#issuecomment-4359693571\"}]}},{\"number\":3887,\"title\":\"Support for com.typesafe.netty:netty-reactive-streams:2.0.4\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3887\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:15:38Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-30T16:06:20Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\ncom.typesafe.netty:netty-reactive-streams:2.0.4\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"jormundur00\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T16:06:12Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed and preserved its work here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fjormundur00%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3887-library-new-request-com.typesafe.netty-netty-reactive-streams-2.0.4-63e82ceb\\n\\nThe most likely failure point was the add-new-library-support validation/native-image repair stage, not initial test generation. The generated test itself is present and looks library-specific, and the preserved outputs show passing validation only after extra manual-style fixes: the final generator log says it had to add `metadata/com.typesafe.netty/netty-reactive-streams/2.0.4/reachability-metadata.json` to fix `No matching coordinates found for 'com.typesafe.netty:netty-reactive-streams:2.0.4'`, then modify unrelated transitive metadata in `metadata/io.netty/netty-common/4.1.80.Final/reachability-metadata.json` to fix an `EmbeddedChannel` native-image runtime issue. That cross-library metadata change is outside the normal scope of a `library-new-request` run and likely triggered the human-intervention path.\\n\\nConcrete evidence:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.typesafe.netty:netty-reactive-streams:2.0.4/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T15-49-13-779149Z.log` ends by reporting the extra `io.netty:netty-common:4.1.80.Final` metadata fix and then says `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=com.typesafe.netty:netty-reactive-streams:2.0.4` passed with `14 tests successful`.\\n- `build/tests/com.typesafe.netty:netty-reactive-streams:2.0.4/3bd3ce4135ee82e6f43fabf8e0ffda02.out` shows `nativeTestCompile` and the new test `handlerPublisherBuffersInboundMessagesUntilSubscriberArrivesAndRequestsThem()` succeeding, with `[14 tests successful]`.\\n- `tests/src/com.typesafe.netty/netty-reactive-streams/2.0.4/build/test-results/test/TEST-com_typesafe_netty.netty_reactive_streams.Netty_reactive_streamsTest.xml` shows 14 tests, 0 failures, 0 errors.\\n- `stats/com.typesafe.netty/netty-reactive-streams/2.0.4/execution-metrics.json` reports success for the generated run with 80.13% line coverage, while `stats/com.typesafe.netty/netty-reactive-streams/2.0.4/stats.json` shows `dynamicAccess` as `0/0`, so there is no meaningful dynamic-access signal to review.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.typesafe.netty:netty-reactive-streams:2.0.4/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T15-49-13-779149Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.typesafe.netty:netty-reactive-streams:2.0.4/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T15-44-39-227878Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/com.typesafe.netty:netty-reactive-streams:2.0.4/3bd3ce4135ee82e6f43fabf8e0ffda02.out`\\n- `stats/com.typesafe.netty/netty-reactive-streams/2.0.4/execution-metrics.json`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Review the preserved branch diff and decide whether the `metadata/io.netty/netty-common/4.1.80.Final/reachability-metadata.json` change is acceptable or must be split into a separate follow-up.\\n2. If that transitive Netty metadata fix is valid, keep the generated `netty-reactive-streams` test and metadata, then rerun `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=com.typesafe.netty:netty-reactive-streams:2.0.4` and `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=com.typesafe.netty:netty-reactive-streams:2.0.4`.\\n3. If cross-library metadata changes are not acceptable in this issue, back out the transitive fix, reproduce the native-image failure from the preserved logs, and handle the Netty metadata gap separately before reopening library support for `com.typesafe.netty:netty-reactive-streams:2.0.4`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3887#issuecomment-4354088619\"}]}},{\"number\":3847,\"title\":\"Support for org.apache.pekko:pekko-protobuf-v3_3:1.0.1\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3847\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:15:20Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T00:36:38Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.apache.pekko:pekko-protobuf-v3_3:1.0.1\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T00:36:30Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.apache.pekko:pekko-protobuf-v3_3:1.0.1`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3847-library-new-request-org.apache.pekko-pekko-protobuf-v3_3-1.0.1-225ccb49\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is `nativeTestCompile` during metadata-fix/post-gen, not JVM test generation. The generated JVM tests appear to run successfully (`tests/src/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_3/1.0.1/build/test-results/test/TEST-*.xml` all report `failures=\\\"0\\\"` and `errors=\\\"0\\\"`), but the native-image build aborts with `Bulk queries can only be set with 'name' which does not allow run-time conditions.` in `build/tests/org.apache.pekko:pekko-protobuf-v3_3:1.0.1/ea14e2aa784bed679a3791e8e2de46d1.out`, where the build ends with `> Task :nativeTestCompile FAILED` and `BUILD FAILED`.\\n\\nThe strongest evidence is in `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.pekko:pekko-protobuf-v3_3:1.0.1/metadata-fix/codex.log`: it identifies conditional bulk-field registrations in `metadata/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_3/1.0.1/reachability-metadata.json` for `org_apache_pekko.pekko_protobuf_v3_3.MessageSchemaMissingFieldMessage`, `SchemaUtilCoverageMessage$AttributesDefaultEntryHolder`, `UnsafeUtilAndroid32MemoryAccessorCoverageMessage$AttributesDefaultEntryHolder`, `UnsafeUtilAndroid64MemoryAccessorCoverageMessage$AttributesDefaultEntryHolder`, and `sun.misc.Unsafe`. The post-gen summary in `post-gen-interventions/org.apache.pekko_pekko-protobuf-v3_3_1.0.1.md` says the same remaining failure is metadata-related. That same report also notes a separate classpath issue from `scala3-compiler_3` pulling JLine metadata on `testRuntimeClasspath`; that was partially mitigated, but it was not the root cause.\\n\\nMetrics also ended in failure after 28 iterations and 1504 generated LOC, and there is still no `stats/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_3/1.0.1/stats.json`, so final dynamic-access coverage remains unavailable.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.pekko:pekko-protobuf-v3_3:1.0.1/metadata-fix/codex.log`\\n- `build/tests/org.apache.pekko:pekko-protobuf-v3_3:1.0.1/ea14e2aa784bed679a3791e8e2de46d1.out`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.pekko:pekko-protobuf-v3_3:1.0.1/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-05-01T00-30-36-448961Z.log`\\n- `post-gen-interventions/org.apache.pekko_pekko-protobuf-v3_3_1.0.1.md`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Rework the Pekko reachability metadata so the conditional bulk-field registrations are represented in a GraalVM-compatible way, then rerun `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.pekko:pekko-protobuf-v3_3:1.0.1 --stacktrace`.\\n2. Review the preserved branch changes around `tests/src/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_3/1.0.1/build.gradle` and `metadata/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_3/1.0.1/reachability-metadata.json`, keeping the `scala3-compiler_3` classpath cleanup only if it still helps after the metadata fix.\\n3. Once `nativeTestCompile` passes, regenerate/check `stats/org.apache.pekko/pekko-protobuf-v3_3/1.0.1/stats.json` and confirm dynamic-access coverage before resuming PR generation.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3847#issuecomment-4357111459\"}]}},{\"number\":3841,\"title\":\"Support for io.ous:jtoml:2.0.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3841\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:15:19Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T18:59:36Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nio.ous:jtoml:2.0.0\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T18:59:30Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `io.ous:jtoml:2.0.0`. Preserved work is available on https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3841-library-new-request-io.ous-jtoml-2.0.0-1ef79b60\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was the `add-new-library-support` generation bookkeeping/finalization step, not the library validation itself. In `logs/io.ous:jtoml:2.0.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T18-56-39-267522Z.log`, the generator ends by reporting coverage for `io.ous.jtoml.impl.ObjectDeserializer`, and the preserved commit `12b94b25ac9c5c8dd8c992840d8d2bef3f9fe1c2` adds three test files (`ObjectDeserializerTest.java`, test `reflect-config.json`, and a small `JtomlTest.java` update). However, `stats/io.ous/jtoml/2.0.0/execution-metrics.json` still records `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, `artifacts.test_file: None`, and `artifacts.metadata_file: None`, which matches the `test_generation_failed` reason.\\n\\nThe generated test outputs look salvageable: `build/tests/io.ous:jtoml:2.0.0/27afe0c97eed74327bfc4c3bdec62cbe.out` and `build/tests/io.ous:jtoml:2.0.0/85b6f57bc9dfcfb96f9d4cadb3d83cd7.out` both end with `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`, and `ObjectDeserializerTest` passes in JVM and native runs. For context, `logs/io.ous:jtoml:2.0.0/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` and `logs/io.ous:jtoml:2.0.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` appear to complete normally and do not look like the failing stage.\\n\\n1. Check out the preserved branch and review the generated tests under `tests/src/io.ous/jtoml/2.0.0/`, especially the new `ObjectDeserializerTest` and the still-placeholder `JtomlTest`.\\n2. Re-run the targeted validation for `io.ous:jtoml:2.0.0` from that branch to confirm `checkMetadataFiles` and `test` stay green.\\n3. If the branch looks good, continue from the preserved branch or cherry-pick commit `12b94b25ac9c5c8dd8c992840d8d2bef3f9fe1c2` instead of regenerating from scratch.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3841#issuecomment-4361077154\"}]}},{\"number\":3829,\"title\":\"Support for io.smallrye.common:smallrye-common-io:2.16.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3829\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:15:17Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-30T18:13:02Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nio.smallrye.common:smallrye-common-io:2.16.0\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"jormundur00\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T18:12:54Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `io.smallrye.common:smallrye-common-io:2.16.0`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fjormundur00%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3829-library-new-request-io.smallrye.common-smallrye-common-io-2.16.0-c34d9e63\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was test generation/validation. In `human-intervention-logs/io.smallrye.common:smallrye-common-io:2.16.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T17-50-23-662512Z.log`, `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.smallrye.common:smallrye-common-io:2.16.0` failed because `SmallryeCommonIoTest.cleanRecursivelyKeepsDirectoryButRemovesChildren()` expected the cleaned root to be empty, but the actual contents still included `left` and `right`. A later retry fixed that assertion and reached `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`, but the run still ended in human intervention: `stats/io.smallrye.common/smallrye-common-io/2.16.0/execution-metrics.json` reports `tested_library_loc: 0` and `code_coverage_percent: 0.0`, dynamic-access coverage is unavailable, and `human-intervention-logs/io.smallrye.common:smallrye-common-io:2.16.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T18-07-38-904462Z.log` shows the run still seeing a scaffold-style `Smallrye_common_ioTest` with native output containing `This is just a placeholder, implement your test`.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.smallrye.common:smallrye-common-io:2.16.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T17-50-23-662512Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.smallrye.common:smallrye-common-io:2.16.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T18-07-38-904462Z.log`\\n- `stats/io.smallrye.common/smallrye-common-io/2.16.0/execution-metrics.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Review the preserved branch and verify the generated test is library-specific and that no scaffold placeholder test or stale test artifact is still being picked up during native execution.\\n2. Re-run the library test flow from a clean state for `io.smallrye.common:smallrye-common-io:2.16.0` and confirm the placeholder output disappears.\\n3. If the tests are valid, investigate why coverage/metrics stayed at zero and why no dynamic-access stats were produced before deciding whether to keep or regenerate the test/metadata.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3829#issuecomment-4355020411\"}]}},{\"number\":3825,\"title\":\"Support for com.diffplug.spotless:spotless-lib:2.45.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3825\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:15:16Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-30T21:17:00Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\ncom.diffplug.spotless:spotless-lib:2.45.0\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"jormundur00\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T21:16:52Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed with `test_generation_failed` for `com.diffplug.spotless:spotless-lib:2.45.0`, even though the preserved work branch contains generated output: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fjormundur00%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3825-library-new-request-com.diffplug.spotless-spotless-lib-2.45.0-da8aca16\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was `add-new-library-support` finalization/artifact capture, not dynamic-access discovery itself. The latest generation log shows the agent writing `tests/src/com.diffplug.spotless/spotless-lib/2.45.0/src/test/java/com_diffplug_spotless/spotless_lib/NpmResourceHelperTest.java` and `metadata/com.diffplug.spotless/spotless-lib/2.45.0/reachability-metadata.json`, then committing `f92861c1a69e3d4110a1e042031c75300674d73b` on the preserved branch. However, `stats/com.diffplug.spotless/spotless-lib/2.45.0/execution-metrics.json` still records `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, and `artifacts.test_file` / `artifacts.metadata_file` as `None`. The run also reports dynamic-access coverage as `123/123 (100.00%)`, which further suggests the failure happened after iterative generation rather than because coverage was missing.\\n\\nPlease inspect these logs first:\\n- `logs/com.diffplug.spotless:spotless-lib:2.45.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T21-09-50-943187Z.log`\\n- `logs/com.diffplug.spotless:spotless-lib:2.45.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T21-01-29-688432Z.log`\\n- `logs/com.diffplug.spotless:spotless-lib:2.45.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T20-52-36-893986Z.log`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Check the preserved branch at commit `f92861c1a69e3d4110a1e042031c75300674d73b` and review the generated `NpmResourceHelperTest.java` plus `reachability-metadata.json`.\\n2. Run targeted validation for `com.diffplug.spotless:spotless-lib:2.45.0` (`checkMetadataFiles`, `compileTestJava`, and `test`) to confirm whether the generated artifacts are actually valid.\\n3. If the generated files pass validation, recover them from the preserved branch and continue manually; otherwise, use the same branch/logs as the starting point for a manual fix to the final test/metadata pair.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3825#issuecomment-4356216021\"}]}},{\"number\":3824,\"title\":\"Support for net.sourceforge.htmlunit:htmlunit-core-js:2.70.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3824\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:15:16Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T19:48:33Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nnet.sourceforge.htmlunit:htmlunit-core-js:2.70.0\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T19:48:27Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `net.sourceforge.htmlunit:htmlunit-core-js:2.70.0`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch:\\nhttps://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3824-library-new-request-net.sourceforge.htmlunit-htmlunit-core-js-2.70.0-98950ade\\n\\nAlthough this was labeled `test_generation_failed`, the preserved branch shows that generation mostly succeeded: it contains a large generated test suite, and the final dynamic-access report reached `133/135` covered call sites (`98.52%`). The two remaining uncovered call sites are `java.lang.Class#getMethods()` from `net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.FunctionObject.getMethodList(FunctionObject.java:252)` and `net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.JavaMembers.discoverAccessibleMethods(JavaMembers.java:338)` in `tests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`.\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is native test validation after generation, not initial test creation. `build/tests/net.sourceforge.htmlunit:htmlunit-core-js:2.70.0/b83c1c045f029666877aaf7a25449496.out` ends with `:nativeTest FAILED` and exit value `99`, and `tests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` reports `57` tests with `3` failures and `46` errors, including `SecurityException: Cannot overwrite already installed global SecurityController`, `NoClassDefFoundError: java/awt/GraphicsEnvironment`, `ClassNotFoundException: net.sourceforge.htmlunit.corejs.javascript.NativeCollectionIterator`, and `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` for `java.lang.Object.<init>()`. Earlier in the run, `human-intervention-logs/net.sourceforge.htmlunit:htmlunit-core-js:2.70.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T19-20-54-291011Z.log` also shows a concrete `compileTestJava` failure in `JavaToJSONConvertersTest`, so the generated tests still needed manual cleanup. The metrics file is also inconsistent with the preserved branch contents: `stats/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/execution-metrics.json` records `status: failure`, `iterations: 54`, `generated_loc: 0`, and no generated artifacts.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/net.sourceforge.htmlunit:htmlunit-core-js:2.70.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T19-20-54-291011Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/net.sourceforge.htmlunit:htmlunit-core-js:2.70.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T19-44-00-826834Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/net.sourceforge.htmlunit:htmlunit-core-js:2.70.0/b83c1c045f029666877aaf7a25449496.out`\\n- `tests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\\n- `tests/src/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Check out the preserved branch and fix the native-image test failures first, especially the `SecurityController`, AWT/`GraphicsEnvironment`, serialization/class-loading, and missing-reflection issues.\\n2. Add or refine coverage for the two remaining uncovered `Class#getMethods()` call sites in `FunctionObject` and `JavaMembers`, then rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=net.sourceforge.htmlunit:htmlunit-core-js:2.70.0`.\\n3. Verify why `stats/net.sourceforge.htmlunit/htmlunit-core-js/2.70.0/execution-metrics.json` recorded `generated_loc: 0` and no artifacts even though the preserved branch contains generated commits.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3824#issuecomment-4361291645\"}]}},{\"number\":3822,\"title\":\"Support for com.diffplug.durian:durian-core:1.2.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3822\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:15:15Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T16:39:05Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\ncom.diffplug.durian:durian-core:1.2.0\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T16:38:57Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job for `com.diffplug.durian:durian-core:1.2.0` failed. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3822-library-new-request-com.diffplug.durian-durian-core-1.2.0-27f9f154\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was test generation/finalization rather than dynamic-access discovery. `stats/com.diffplug.durian/durian-core/1.2.0/execution-metrics.json` records `status: failure` with `generated_loc: 0`, `test_file: None`, and `metadata_file: None`, even though the preserved diff from `11846575f4c1d1337d4f981ac70f9e97a14d10fc` to `1d17789536525c4c5cc6a8ff43c11db9ac5a0be8` adds generated tests/metadata locally. The generation logs also show the agent leaving the scaffold placeholder in `tests/src/com.diffplug.durian/durian-core/1.2.0/src/test/java/com_diffplug_durian/durian_core/Durian_coreTest.java` (`This is just a placeholder, implement your test`) and getting stuck around untracked files instead of cleanly finalizing artifacts. Please inspect `human-intervention-logs/com.diffplug.durian:durian-core:1.2.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T15-54-41-135258Z.log`, `human-intervention-logs/com.diffplug.durian:durian-core:1.2.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T16-17-18-122537Z.log`, and `human-intervention-logs/com.diffplug.durian:durian-core:1.2.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T16-30-28-091585Z.log`.\\n\\nThere is also a concrete preserved runtime issue to review manually: `tests/src/com.diffplug.durian/durian-core/1.2.0/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` shows `FinalizerTest.finalizableWeakReferenceIsCleanedByFinalizerThread()` failing under native image with `NoSuchMethodException: com.diffplug.common.base.internal.Finalizer.startFinalizer(...)`. At the same time, the preserved dynamic-access report reached `17/17` coverage in `tests/src/com.diffplug.durian/durian-core/1.2.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`, so the failure is not lack of dynamic-access coverage.\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Review the preserved branch and replace/remove the scaffold `Durian_coreTest`, then make sure the intended generated test and metadata files are actually tracked.\\n2. Fix or drop `FinalizerTest` so native-image runtime passes for this coordinate, then rerun the coordinate tests.\\n3. Once the content is valid, refresh/re-record the run so metrics stop reporting `generated_loc: 0` and missing artifact paths.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3822#issuecomment-4360412391\"}]}},{\"number\":3816,\"title\":\"Support for io.quarkus:quarkus-development-mode-spi:3.33.1\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3816\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:15:14Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-30T22:39:56Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nio.quarkus:quarkus-development-mode-spi:3.33.1\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"jormundur00\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T22:39:49Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `io.quarkus:quarkus-development-mode-spi:3.33.1`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fjormundur00%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3816-library-new-request-io.quarkus-quarkus-development-mode-spi-3.33.1-f143db28\\n\\nMost likely failing stage: test generation / promotion of generated output. The preserved run contains a generated `TerminalUtilsTest` and local test artifacts showing it passed, with dynamic-access coverage reported as `1/1` for `io.quarkus.dev.console.TerminalUtils` (`tests/src/io.quarkus/quarkus-development-mode-spi/3.33.1/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` and `.../build/test-results/test/TEST-io_quarkus.quarkus_development_mode_spi.TerminalUtilsTest.xml`). However, the scaffold test `tests/src/io.quarkus/quarkus-development-mode-spi/3.33.1/src/test/java/io_quarkus/quarkus_development_mode_spi/Quarkus_development_mode_spiTest.java` is still just the placeholder test, and its report still prints `This is just a placeholder, implement your test` (`.../build/test-results/test/TEST-io_quarkus.quarkus_development_mode_spi.Quarkus_development_mode_spiTest.xml`). The metrics file also still records overall failure with `generated_loc: 0`, `metadata_entries: 0`, `test_file: None`, and `metadata_file: None` despite the preserved commit containing test changes (`stats/io.quarkus/quarkus-development-mode-spi/3.33.1/execution-metrics.json`).\\n\\nLogs to inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.quarkus:quarkus-development-mode-spi:3.33.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T22-34-48-056609Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.quarkus:quarkus-development-mode-spi:3.33.1/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.quarkus:quarkus-development-mode-spi:3.33.1/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n- `tests/src/io.quarkus/quarkus-development-mode-spi/3.33.1/build/reports/tests/test/index.html`\\n- `tests/src/io.quarkus/quarkus-development-mode-spi/3.33.1/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n- Replace the scaffold-only `Quarkus_development_mode_spiTest` with a real library-specific test, or fold the `TerminalUtilsTest` coverage into the expected new-library test layout.\\n- Verify why the generated test/metadata artifacts were not recognized by the metrics pipeline even though commit `a18ffada88e60f32919f3624141d9f6e2fc20e83` contains test changes.\\n- Re-run the library validation for `io.quarkus:quarkus-development-mode-spi:3.33.1` after fixing the test generation output.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3816#issuecomment-4356640004\"}]}},{\"number\":3771,\"title\":\"Support for org.apache.camel:apt:2.16.2\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3771\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:14:59Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-30T19:02:21Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.apache.camel:apt:2.16.2\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T19:02:14Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed to complete automatically for `org.apache.camel:apt:2.16.2` and was routed for human follow-up (`test_generation_failed`).\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3771-library-new-request-org.apache.camel-apt-2.16.2-6205c0a2\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was the automated test-generation qualification step, not Gradle validation. The run made 3 generation attempts, ended with an empty metadata file (`metadata/org.apache.camel/apt/2.16.2/reachability-metadata.json` is `{}`), and produced no dynamic-access signal (`stats/org.apache.camel/apt/2.16.2/stats.json` and `tests/src/org.apache.camel/apt/2.16.2/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` both show `coveredCalls: 0` and `totalCalls: 0`). The generated test file is substantial but focuses on helper/model methods and JSON-schema generation in `tests/src/org.apache.camel/apt/2.16.2/src/test/java/org_apache_camel/apt/AptTest.java`, rather than an end-to-end javac/APT-style annotation-processing scenario.\\n\\nValidation artifacts are green: `tests/src/org.apache.camel/apt/2.16.2/build/test-results/test/TEST-org_apache_camel.apt.AptTest.xml` shows 10 tests, 0 failures, 0 errors; `tests/src/org.apache.camel/apt/2.16.2/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` also shows 10 tests, 0 failures, 0 errors; and native-image/test execution completed successfully in `build/tests/org.apache.camel:apt:2.16.2/3773df10bdc0d6268bbb84e1c0c4e64a.out` and `build/tests/org.apache.camel:apt:2.16.2/32b30f71bf4753963b090947737c617d.out`.\\n\\nPlease inspect these logs and artifacts:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.camel:apt:2.16.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T18-47-31-116531Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.camel:apt:2.16.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T18-51-30-442688Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.camel:apt:2.16.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T18-54-32-033616Z.log`\\n- `tests/src/org.apache.camel/apt/2.16.2/src/test/java/org_apache_camel/apt/AptTest.java`\\n- `stats/org.apache.camel/apt/2.16.2/stats.json`\\n- `tests/src/org.apache.camel/apt/2.16.2/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Decide whether `camel-apt` should be accepted as a no-metadata case with `{}` or whether this new-library request needs stronger, end-to-end annotation-processor coverage.\\n2. If stronger coverage is required, replace the helper-focused test with a javac/APT-style test that compiles annotated sample sources and asserts the generated schema/metadata output.\\n3. If the current no-metadata result is acceptable, review the preserved branch and open a PR manually from it.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3771#issuecomment-4355407153\"}]}},{\"number\":3761,\"title\":\"Support for org.jboss.shrinkwrap.descriptors:shrinkwrap-descriptors-api-base:2.0.0-alpha-8\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3761\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:14:57Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-30T16:04:03Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.jboss.shrinkwrap.descriptors:shrinkwrap-descriptors-api-base:2.0.0-alpha-8\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T16:03:56Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.jboss.shrinkwrap.descriptors:shrinkwrap-descriptors-api-base:2.0.0-alpha-8`. Preserved work is available on branch `https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3761-library-new-request-org.jboss.shrinkwrap.descriptors-shrinkwrap-descriptors-api-base-2.0.0-alpha-8-ccfa04a5`.\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was the post-generation artifact/metrics handoff in `add-new-library-support`, not the generated test logic itself. In `human-intervention-logs/org.jboss.shrinkwrap.descriptors:shrinkwrap-descriptors-api-base:2.0.0-alpha-8/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T16-01-45-238976Z.log`, the agent detours into unrelated metadata/URL-discovery work, then commits only test-side files in `be488b75a4366d16dd709ce97ba1f6df37c84719`; the same log still shows `git status --short` with `?? metadata/org.jboss.shrinkwrap.descriptors/shrinkwrap-descriptors-api-base/2.0.0-alpha-8/`, so the library metadata directory was left untracked. That matches `stats/org.jboss.shrinkwrap.descriptors/shrinkwrap-descriptors-api-base/2.0.0-alpha-8/execution-metrics.json`, which reports `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, `metadata_entries: 0`, `artifacts.test_file: None`, and `artifacts.metadata_file: None`.\\n\\nThe generated test artifacts themselves look viable: `tests/src/org.jboss.shrinkwrap.descriptors/shrinkwrap-descriptors-api-base/2.0.0-alpha-8/build/test-results/test/TEST-org_jboss_shrinkwrap_descriptors.shrinkwrap_descriptors_api_base.DescriptorInstantiatorTest.xml` has 3 tests with 0 failures/errors, `tests/src/org.jboss.shrinkwrap.descriptors/shrinkwrap-descriptors-api-base/2.0.0-alpha-8/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` has 4 tests with 0 failures/errors, and `tests/src/org.jboss.shrinkwrap.descriptors/shrinkwrap-descriptors-api-base/2.0.0-alpha-8/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` shows `7/7` covered call sites.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.jboss.shrinkwrap.descriptors:shrinkwrap-descriptors-api-base:2.0.0-alpha-8/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T16-01-45-238976Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.jboss.shrinkwrap.descriptors:shrinkwrap-descriptors-api-base:2.0.0-alpha-8/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.jboss.shrinkwrap.descriptors:shrinkwrap-descriptors-api-base:2.0.0-alpha-8/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Review the preserved branch and add/commit the missing `metadata/org.jboss.shrinkwrap.descriptors/shrinkwrap-descriptors-api-base/2.0.0-alpha-8/reachability-metadata.json` alongside the generated tests.\\n2. Re-run the library validation/metrics flow so the committed test and metadata artifacts are rediscovered.\\n3. If metrics still report `test_file: None` / `metadata_file: None`, investigate the artifact-detection logic in the `add-new-library-support` pipeline for this library.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3761#issuecomment-4354072837\"}]}},{\"number\":3759,\"title\":\"Support for org.jboss.shrinkwrap:shrinkwrap-api:1.2.2\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3759\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:14:56Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T11:58:54Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.jboss.shrinkwrap:shrinkwrap-api:1.2.2\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T11:58:47Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job for `org.jboss.shrinkwrap:shrinkwrap-api:1.2.2` failed. Preserved work is available on branch `https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3759-library-new-request-org.jboss.shrinkwrap-shrinkwrap-api-1.2.2-3f4fc7a6`.\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is post-generation `nativeTest` validation. The generated JVM-side tests and dynamic-access report exist, and `tests/src/org.jboss.shrinkwrap/shrinkwrap-api/1.2.2/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` reports `6/6` covered calls, but `build/tests/org.jboss.shrinkwrap:shrinkwrap-api:1.2.2/63a3cec689f8a414009eab22ca734ad8.out` shows `> Task :nativeTest FAILED` with 3 native-image test failures: `ClassLoaderAssetTest` cannot find `org_jboss_shrinkwrap/shrinkwrap_api/class-loader-asset.txt`, `ClassLoaderSearchUtilTest` cannot load `org.jboss.shrinkwrap.impl.base.path.BasicPath`, and `SecurityActionsTest` cannot find `org.jboss.shrinkwrap.api.ConfigurationBuilder` in the native-image class loader. The same failures are recorded in `tests/src/org.jboss.shrinkwrap/shrinkwrap-api/1.2.2/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`. There is also a leftover scaffold test in `tests/src/org.jboss.shrinkwrap/shrinkwrap-api/1.2.2/src/test/java/org_jboss_shrinkwrap/shrinkwrap_api/Shrinkwrap_apiTest.java`, and its placeholder output still appears in the native test log. Metrics were written as failure with `generated_loc: 0`, `test_file: None`, and `metadata_file: None` in `stats/org.jboss.shrinkwrap/shrinkwrap-api/1.2.2/execution-metrics.json`.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n`human-intervention-logs/org.jboss.shrinkwrap:shrinkwrap-api:1.2.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T11-46-52-246155Z.log`\\n`human-intervention-logs/org.jboss.shrinkwrap:shrinkwrap-api:1.2.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T11-49-35-876567Z.log`\\n`human-intervention-logs/org.jboss.shrinkwrap:shrinkwrap-api:1.2.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T11-53-45-553311Z.log`\\n`build/tests/org.jboss.shrinkwrap:shrinkwrap-api:1.2.2/63a3cec689f8a414009eab22ca734ad8.out`\\n`tests/src/org.jboss.shrinkwrap/shrinkwrap-api/1.2.2/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Fix or replace the generated tests so they pass under Native Image, especially the missing resource/classloader assumptions in `ClassLoaderAssetTest`, `ClassLoaderSearchUtilTest`, and `SecurityActionsTest`.\\n2. Remove or replace the leftover scaffold placeholder `Shrinkwrap_apiTest`.\\n3. Rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.jboss.shrinkwrap:shrinkwrap-api:1.2.2` and confirm `nativeTest` passes, not just dynamic-access coverage.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3759#issuecomment-4359165732\"}]}},{\"number\":3751,\"title\":\"Support for org.aesh:readline:2.6\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3751\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:14:52Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T19:25:57Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.aesh:readline:2.6\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T19:25:51Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.aesh:readline:2.6`. Preserved work is available on branch `https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3751-library-new-request-org.aesh-readline-2.6-3a1f5a32`.\\n\\n`discover-artifact-metadata` and `populate-artifact-urls` completed successfully (`logs/org.aesh:readline:2.6/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` and `logs/org.aesh:readline:2.6/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` both end with `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`), so the likely failure is in `add-new-library-support` test generation/validation. The preserved reports show dynamic-access coverage is already 9/9 (100%) in `tests/src/org.aesh/readline/2.6/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`, but native validation fails in `tests/src/org.aesh/readline/2.6/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`: `org_aesh.readline.TerminalBuilderTest.windowsSystemTerminalChecksWhetherConsoleIsATerminal()` throws `java.lang.NoSuchFieldException: cons`. The preserved test set also still contains a scaffold placeholder in `tests/src/org.aesh/readline/2.6/src/test/java/org_aesh/readline/ReadlineTest.java`, and the run metrics stayed failed after 2 iterations with `generated_loc: 0` and no recorded test/metadata artifact paths in `stats/org.aesh/readline/2.6/execution-metrics.json`, which matches the stalled generation logs.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `logs/org.aesh:readline:2.6/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T19-18-42-369519Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.aesh:readline:2.6/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T19-22-36-105024Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.aesh:readline:2.6/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n- `logs/org.aesh:readline:2.6/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n- `tests/src/org.aesh/readline/2.6/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Replace or remove the placeholder `ReadlineTest` with a library-specific test.\\n2. Rework `TerminalBuilderTest` so it does not depend on `sun.misc.Unsafe` or private JDK fields like `System.cons`, which are failing under native image.\\n3. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.aesh:readline:2.6` and confirm native tests pass while keeping the existing 9/9 dynamic-access coverage.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3751#issuecomment-4361193743\"}]}},{\"number\":3748,\"title\":\"Support for org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu-iossimulatorarm64:0.26.1\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3748\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:14:51Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T00:56:32Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu-iossimulatorarm64:0.26.1\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T00:56:27Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu-iossimulatorarm64:0.26.1`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3748-library-new-request-org.jetbrains.kotlinx-atomicfu-iossimulatorarm64-0.26.1-ea99f34b\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was scaffold/test generation after artifact metadata discovery completed. `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu-iossimulatorarm64:0.26.1/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` shows `:discoverArtifactMetadata` completed successfully and the discovered metadata file was populated, but the Gradle problems report at `build/reports/problems/problems-report.html` reports an `:scaffold` error for `scaffold --coordinates=org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu-iossimulatorarm64:0.26.1`: Gradle could not choose between multiple matching variants because the consumer did not set `org.gradle.usage`. The report names two competing variants, `iosSimulatorArm64ApiElements-published` (`kotlin-api`) and `iosSimulatorArm64MetadataElements-published` (`kotlin-metadata`).\\n\\nI did not find generated test, metadata, or stats output for this coordinate under `tests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlinx`, `metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx`, or `stats/org.jetbrains.kotlinx`, which is consistent with `test_generation_failed`. Dynamic-access coverage and run metrics are unavailable because generation appears to have stopped before any test project or stats were produced.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu-iossimulatorarm64:0.26.1/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n- `build/reports/problems/problems-report.html`\\n- `build/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.jetbrains.kotlinx-atomicfu-iossimulatorarm64-0.26.1.log`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Update the scaffold/test-generation path to handle Kotlin Multiplatform native target artifacts like `atomicfu-iossimulatorarm64` by selecting the intended variant explicitly or setting the required consumer attributes.\\n2. Re-run scaffold/test generation for `org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu-iossimulatorarm64:0.26.1` and verify that a test project and `stats/.../stats.json` are created.\\n3. If this iOS simulator target artifact is not a suitable TCK candidate, retarget the request to the appropriate JVM/common artifact instead of the platform-specific native module.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3748#issuecomment-4357178418\"}]}},{\"number\":3744,\"title\":\"Support for org.osgi:org.osgi.framework:1.9.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3744\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:14:49Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T16:44:03Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.osgi:org.osgi.framework:1.9.0\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T16:43:57Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job failed for `org.osgi:org.osgi.framework:1.9.0`. Preserved work is available at https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3744-library-new-request-org.osgi-org.osgi.framework-1.9.0-d862c79a.\\n\\nThis does not look like a compile or runtime test failure. The preserved branch contains generated test changes, `tests/src/org.osgi/org.osgi.framework/1.9.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` reports `4/4` covered calls, and `build/tests/org.osgi:org.osgi.framework:1.9.0/dc28e1a164560f1469fb92d62c69b16b.out` shows `nativeTestCompile`, `nativeTest`, and `generateDynamicAccessReport` completed successfully. The most likely failing stage is `add-new-library-support` finalization or result recording: `stats/org.osgi/org.osgi.framework/1.9.0/execution-metrics.json` still records `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, and `artifacts.test_file` / `metadata_file` as `None`, even though the preserved commit added `FrameworkUtilInnerFilterImplTest.java` and a test-side `reflect-config.json`.\\n\\nThe preserved output is also not PR-ready as-is: `tests/src/org.osgi/org.osgi.framework/1.9.0/src/test/java/org_osgi/org_osgi_framework/Org_osgi_frameworkTest.java` is still the placeholder scaffold test, and the generated test metadata was added as a legacy `tests/src/org.osgi/org.osgi.framework/1.9.0/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/org.osgi.framework-filter-test/reflect-config.json`.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.osgi:org.osgi.framework:1.9.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T16-40-41-076289Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.osgi:org.osgi.framework:1.9.0/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.osgi:org.osgi.framework:1.9.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n- Review the preserved branch and salvage the generated coverage test, but remove or replace the scaffold placeholder test.\\n- Decide whether the test-side `reflect-config.json` should be converted to repository-accepted test metadata before opening a PR.\\n- Re-run `checkMetadataFiles` and `test -Pcoordinates=org.osgi:org.osgi.framework:1.9.0`; if they stay green, investigate why metrics/finalization still marked the run as failed.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3744#issuecomment-4360442614\"}]}},{\"number\":3739,\"title\":\"Support for org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu-iosarm64:0.26.1\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3739\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:14:46Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T06:43:31Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu-iosarm64:0.26.1\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T06:43:25Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job failed for `org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu-iosarm64:0.26.1`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3739-library-new-request-org.jetbrains.kotlinx-atomicfu-iosarm64-0.26.1-b2db7893\\n\\nArtifact discovery appears to have succeeded, but the workflow most likely failed during test generation after that step. `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu-iosarm64:0.26.1/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` and `build/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.jetbrains.kotlinx-atomicfu-iosarm64-0.26.1.log` show `discoverArtifactMetadata` completed and wrote `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx-atomicfu-iosarm64-0.26.1.json`; those logs also identify the artifact as a Kotlin/Native `iosArm64` artifact with `packaging=klib`. No generated `tests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/atomicfu-iosarm64/0.26.1`, `metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/atomicfu-iosarm64`, or `stats/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/atomicfu-iosarm64/0.26.1` outputs are present, and no run metrics were preserved, so the pipeline appears to have stopped before any PR-ready test project or coverage data was created.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu-iosarm64:0.26.1/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n- `build/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.jetbrains.kotlinx-atomicfu-iosarm64-0.26.1.log`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n- Confirm whether `org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu-iosarm64:0.26.1` should be excluded from the current JVM/native-image new-library workflow because it is a Kotlin/Native `klib`.\\n- If support is expected, add or use a manual generation path for Kotlin/Native artifacts and rerun the workflow.\\n- Review the preserved branch and salvage the discovered artifact metadata JSON before preparing any manual follow-up PR.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3739#issuecomment-4358194943\"}]}},{\"number\":3736,\"title\":\"Support for io.smallrye.common:smallrye-common-classloader:2.15.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3736\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:14:45Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T06:47:57Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nio.smallrye.common:smallrye-common-classloader:2.15.0\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T06:47:52Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job for `io.smallrye.common:smallrye-common-classloader:2.15.0` failed. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3736-library-new-request-io.smallrye.common-smallrye-common-classloader-2.15.0-36657bbb\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is the post-generation artifact/metrics capture in `add-new-library-support`, not the generated test logic itself. In `human-intervention-logs/io.smallrye.common:smallrye-common-classloader:2.15.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T06-45-54-551848Z.log`, the agent finishes by reporting that it added `ClassPathUtilsTest.java`, and the preserved ending commit `09c29d3e654f47bb8b7a749c9e936b55db169127` contains that file. However, `forge/.pending_metrics.json` and `stats/io.smallrye.common/smallrye-common-classloader/2.15.0/execution-metrics.json` still record `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, and `artifacts.test_file: None`.\\n\\nThe generated tests appear to be valid. `tests/src/io.smallrye.common/smallrye-common-classloader/2.15.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` reports `4/4` covered calls for `io.smallrye.common.classloader.ClassPathUtils`, `tests/src/io.smallrye.common/smallrye-common-classloader/2.15.0/build/test-results/test/TEST-io_smallrye_common.smallrye_common_classloader.ClassPathUtilsTest.xml` shows 4 JVM tests passing, and `tests/src/io.smallrye.common/smallrye-common-classloader/2.15.0/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` shows 5 native tests passing. Additional setup logs to inspect are `human-intervention-logs/io.smallrye.common:smallrye-common-classloader:2.15.0/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` and `human-intervention-logs/io.smallrye.common:smallrye-common-classloader:2.15.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`.\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Review the preserved branch and confirm the generated `ClassPathUtilsTest.java` should be kept.\\n2. Re-run or repair the metrics/artifact recording step so the generated test file and non-zero LOC are captured instead of `test_generation_failed`.\\n3. If the workflow still marks failure, investigate why `forge/.pending_metrics.json` and `stats/.../execution-metrics.json` are not picking up the committed test artifact from commit `09c29d3e654f47bb8b7a749c9e936b55db169127`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3736#issuecomment-4358207811\"}]}},{\"number\":3683,\"title\":\"Support for org.ow2.asm:asm-debug-all:5.0.1\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3683\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:14:12Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T08:20:11Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.ow2.asm:asm-debug-all:5.0.1\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T08:20:05Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.ow2.asm:asm-debug-all:5.0.1`. Preserved work is available on branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3683-library-new-request-org.ow2.asm-asm-debug-all-5.0.1-5dc1f993\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was test generation/finalization rather than artifact discovery. `stats/org.ow2.asm/asm-debug-all/5.0.1/execution-metrics.json` records `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, `metadata_entries: 0`, and `artifacts.test_file: None` / `artifacts.metadata_file: None`, even though the preserved worktree contains generated files. The generation logs also show the scaffold test was left in place as a placeholder (`tests/src/org.ow2.asm/asm-debug-all/5.0.1/src/test/java/org_ow2_asm/asm_debug_all/Asm_debug_allTest.java` still prints “This is just a placeholder, implement your test”), and one attempt only changed that class to `public` instead of replacing it (`human-intervention-logs/org.ow2.asm:asm-debug-all:5.0.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T08-11-48-474037Z.log`). A later attempt created untracked files and then stopped without validating them (`human-intervention-logs/org.ow2.asm:asm-debug-all:5.0.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T08-17-56-209122Z.log`).\\n\\nThere is also a concrete native test failure in the preserved Gradle output: `build/tests/org.ow2.asm:asm-debug-all:5.0.1/03d10902e95547e6ef43082ef5d5cb96.out` shows `:nativeTest FAILED` because `ClassWriterTest.returnsSharedSuperclassForConcreteCollectionTypes()` throws `java.lang.RuntimeException: java.lang.ClassNotFoundException: java.util.LinkedList`. The native JUnit report shows the same failure in `tests/src/org.ow2.asm/asm-debug-all/5.0.1/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`. Coverage itself looks complete in `tests/src/org.ow2.asm/asm-debug-all/5.0.1/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` with `7/7` covered dynamic-access calls, so the remaining work is to turn the preserved output into a valid non-scaffold test set and fix the native-only `ClassWriterTest` behavior.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.ow2.asm:asm-debug-all:5.0.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T08-11-48-474037Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.ow2.asm:asm-debug-all:5.0.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T08-17-56-209122Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/org.ow2.asm:asm-debug-all:5.0.1/03d10902e95547e6ef43082ef5d5cb96.out`\\n- `stats/org.ow2.asm/asm-debug-all/5.0.1/execution-metrics.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Clean up the preserved branch by replacing/removing the scaffold `Asm_debug_allTest` and keeping only library-specific tests plus the generated metadata file.\\n2. Fix or rewrite `ClassWriterTest` so it passes under Native Image without relying on loading `java.util.LinkedList` in a way that triggers `ClassNotFoundException`.\\n3. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.ow2.asm:asm-debug-all:5.0.1` and confirm the generated files are tracked/recognized by the pipeline.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3683#issuecomment-4358478785\"}]}},{\"number\":3678,\"title\":\"Support for com.squareup:javawriter:2.5.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3678\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:14:07Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T08:45:33Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\ncom.squareup:javawriter:2.5.0\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T08:45:27Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job for `com.squareup:javawriter:2.5.0` failed. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3678-library-new-request-com.squareup-javawriter-2.5.0-bbaf5bea\\n\\nThe most likely failure point was the handoff after artifact discovery, before any test generation actually started. In `human-intervention-logs/com.squareup:javawriter:2.5.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`, the discovery step successfully resolved upstream URLs and wrote `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/com.squareup-javawriter-2.5.0.json`, but `human-intervention-logs/com.squareup:javawriter:2.5.0/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` then reports `No matching coordinates found for filter 'com.squareup:javawriter:2.5.0'.` and exits without producing any `metadata/`, `tests/src/`, or `stats/` output for this coordinate. Metrics and dynamic-access coverage are unavailable because the pipeline did not reach that stage.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.squareup:javawriter:2.5.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.squareup:javawriter:2.5.0/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Verify why `populateArtifactURLs` cannot resolve `com.squareup:javawriter:2.5.0` even though discovery produced `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/com.squareup-javawriter-2.5.0.json`.\\n2. Fix the coordinate/index handoff for this new library and rerun the new-library generation flow.\\n3. Once generation proceeds, add library-specific tests and regenerate stats/coverage for maintainer review.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3678#issuecomment-4358557291\"}]}},{\"number\":3675,\"title\":\"Support for com.googlecode.juniversalchardet:juniversalchardet:1.0.3\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3675\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:14:06Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T08:47:21Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\ncom.googlecode.juniversalchardet:juniversalchardet:1.0.3\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T08:47:16Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `com.googlecode.juniversalchardet:juniversalchardet:1.0.3`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3675-library-new-request-com.googlecode.juniversalchardet-juniversalchardet-1.0.3-c9e6d073\\n\\nThe most likely failure point was the initial scaffold/test-generation path, after artifact metadata discovery succeeded but before any usable generated test or stats output was retained. `human-intervention-logs/com.googlecode.juniversalchardet:juniversalchardet:1.0.3/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` shows `discoverArtifactMetadata` completed successfully, and `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/com.googlecode.juniversalchardet-juniversalchardet-1.0.3.json` was populated with source/test/doc URLs. However, `human-intervention-logs/com.googlecode.juniversalchardet:juniversalchardet:1.0.3/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` reports `No matching coordinates found for filter 'com.googlecode.juniversalchardet:juniversalchardet:1.0.3'.` On the preserved branch there are no retained `tests/src/com.googlecode.juniversalchardet/...`, `metadata/com.googlecode.juniversalchardet/...`, or `stats/com.googlecode.juniversalchardet/...` artifacts, and both `forge/script_run_metrics` and `forge/benchmark_run_metrics` are empty, so no valid generated test or coverage output was produced.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.googlecode.juniversalchardet:juniversalchardet:1.0.3/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.googlecode.juniversalchardet:juniversalchardet:1.0.3/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n- `build/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/com.googlecode.juniversalchardet-juniversalchardet-1.0.3.log`\\n- `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/com.googlecode.juniversalchardet-juniversalchardet-1.0.3.json`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Re-run scaffold/add-library generation locally and verify it creates `metadata/com.googlecode.juniversalchardet/juniversalchardet/index.json` and `tests/src/com.googlecode.juniversalchardet/juniversalchardet/1.0.3/` before `populateArtifactURLs` runs.\\n2. Investigate why `populateArtifactURLs` cannot match the new coordinate and manually repair or seed the scaffolded index entry if needed.\\n3. Once scaffold/index creation is working, add a library-specific `juniversalchardet` test and rerun the library workflow to produce stats and coverage.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3675#issuecomment-4358563285\"}]}},{\"number\":3645,\"title\":\"Support for net.sf.saxon:Saxon-HE:9.9.1-6\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3645\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:13:43Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T16:53:21Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nnet.sf.saxon:Saxon-HE:9.9.1-6\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T16:53:15Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `net.sf.saxon:Saxon-HE:9.9.1-6`. Preserved work is available on https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3645-library-new-request-net.sf.saxon-Saxon-HE-9.9.1-6-d98823e5.\\n\\nAlthough the run was classified as `test_generation_failed`, the preserved work suggests generation mostly succeeded and the likely blocker is the native test validation stage. The generation branch reached commit `4291afc9735787fcc5ced03dd697337235c99efe` with dynamic-access coverage `34/34`, but `build/tests/net.sf.saxon:Saxon-HE:9.9.1-6/c35116e37832c3899b684b6cc8082941.out` shows `:nativeTest FAILED` with 11 failing tests, including `BuiltInFunctionSetTest`, `ConfigurationTest`, `DynamicLoaderTest`, `PJConverter*`, and `StyleNodeFactoryTest`. The repeated root cause is reflective instantiation of classes that do not have a public zero-arg constructor, especially `net.sf.saxon.Configuration` and `net.sf.saxon.functions.UpperCase` (`InstantiationException` / `NoSuchMethodException`). The metrics file `stats/net.sf.saxon/Saxon-HE/9.9.1-6/execution-metrics.json` also ends in `failure` after 12 iterations and records no accepted artifact (`generated_loc: 0`, `test_file: None`, `metadata_file: None`), so the automation never reconciled the generated work with a passing validation run.\\n\\nPlease inspect `human-intervention-logs/net.sf.saxon:Saxon-HE:9.9.1-6/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T16-40-46-728013Z.log`, `human-intervention-logs/net.sf.saxon:Saxon-HE:9.9.1-6/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T16-48-21-648164Z.log`, `build/tests/net.sf.saxon:Saxon-HE:9.9.1-6/c35116e37832c3899b684b6cc8082941.out`, and `stats/net.sf.saxon/Saxon-HE/9.9.1-6/execution-metrics.json`.\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Check out the preserved branch and review the generated tests under `tests/src/net.sf.saxon/Saxon-HE/9.9.1-6`.\\n2. Rework or drop tests that assume reflective `Class#newInstance()` succeeds for `Configuration` or built-in function classes without public zero-arg constructors, then rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=net.sf.saxon:Saxon-HE:9.9.1-6`.\\n3. If validation passes, use the preserved branch as the starting point for the manual PR.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3645#issuecomment-4360490930\"}]}},{\"number\":3624,\"title\":\"Support for org.jetbrains.compose.ui:ui:1.8.2\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3624\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:12:50Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T03:37:42Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.jetbrains.compose.ui:ui:1.8.2\\n\\n### Reason for requesting the library\\n\\nPopular Maven library rank 263 from `/home/jovan/mvnrepository-popular-scraper/popular-maven-libraries.json`.\\nMirrored from fork issue https://github.com/jormundur00/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3505 after strict `groupId:artifactId` metadata and open-issue filtering.\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"github-actions\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:14:27Z\",\"body\":\"Automation: No dependency issues were created by the triage workflow.\\n\\nThis typically means every dependency in the deps.dev expansion is already supported by the repository.\\n\\nPlan nodes:\\n```\\norg.jetbrains.compose.ui:ui:1.8.2\\n```\\n\\nSupported GA detected during checks:\\n```\\n(none)\\n```\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3624#issuecomment-4353191592\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T03:37:36Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.jetbrains.compose.ui:ui:1.8.2`. Preserved work is available at https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3624-library-new-request-org.jetbrains.compose.ui-ui-1.8.2-f333197f.\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is post-test stats/coverage finalization, not basic test execution. In `logs/org.jetbrains.compose.ui:ui:1.8.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T03-34-03-434414Z.log`, the final retry shows `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.jetbrains.compose.ui:ui:1.8.2 --stacktrace` succeeding and the native test run reporting 10/10 tests successful. The generated result files under `tests/src/org.jetbrains.compose.ui/ui/1.8.2/build/test-results/test/TEST-org_jetbrains_compose_ui.ui.UiTest.xml` and `tests/src/org.jetbrains.compose.ui/ui/1.8.2/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` also show zero failures. However, the run still ends in failure and no usable coverage/stats were produced: `stats/org.jetbrains.compose.ui/ui/1.8.2/execution-metrics.json` records `status: failure`, `tested_library_loc: 0`, `metadata_entries: 0`, and `code_coverage_percent: 0.0`, and there is no `stats/org.jetbrains.compose.ui/ui/1.8.2/stats.json` or dynamic-access coverage report for this coordinate. Earlier retries in `logs/org.jetbrains.compose.ui:ui:1.8.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T03-31-06-118904Z.log` also show transient TCK/artifact-resolution failures (`No matching coordinates found for 'org.jetbrains.compose.ui:ui:1.8.2'` and `No eligible artifacts found on the classpath for org.jetbrains.compose.ui:ui:1.8.2`) before the test module was adjusted.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `logs/org.jetbrains.compose.ui:ui:1.8.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T03-34-03-434414Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.jetbrains.compose.ui:ui:1.8.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T03-31-06-118904Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.jetbrains.compose.ui:ui:1.8.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T03-27-40-762637Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.jetbrains.compose.ui:ui:1.8.2/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n- `logs/org.jetbrains.compose.ui:ui:1.8.2/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n- Verify why stats/dynamic-access artifacts were not emitted after the successful final `test` run, and whether this library is expected to remain a `{}` metadata case.\\n- Re-check top-level coordinate discovery for `org.jetbrains.compose.ui:ui:1.8.2`, since earlier retries failed before the final run stabilized.\\n- If stats generation can be completed, refresh the coverage artifacts and then decide whether the preserved test plus empty metadata are sufficient for a PR.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3624#issuecomment-4357669837\"}]}},{\"number\":3614,\"title\":\"Support for org.ow2.asm:asm-commons:9.8\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3614\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:12:31Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T09:39:13Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.ow2.asm:asm-commons:9.8\\n\\n### Reason for requesting the library\\n\\nPopular Maven library rank 247 from `/home/jovan/mvnrepository-popular-scraper/popular-maven-libraries.json`.\\nMirrored from fork issue https://github.com/jormundur00/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3494 after strict `groupId:artifactId` metadata and open-issue filtering.\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"github-actions\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:14:03Z\",\"body\":\"Automation: No dependency issues were created by the triage workflow.\\n\\nThis typically means every dependency in the deps.dev expansion is already supported by the repository.\\n\\nPlan nodes:\\n```\\norg.ow2.asm:asm-commons:9.8\\norg.ow2.asm:asm:9.8\\norg.ow2.asm:asm-tree:9.8\\n```\\n\\nSupported GA detected during checks:\\n```\\norg.ow2.asm:asm\\norg.ow2.asm:asm-tree\\n```\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3614#issuecomment-4353188448\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T09:39:04Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.ow2.asm:asm-commons:9.8`. Preserved work is available at https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3614-library-new-request-org.ow2.asm-asm-commons-9.8-6d7a99b2.\\n\\nMost likely failing stage: post-test-generation finalization/scope handling, not the generated library tests themselves. The `add-new-library-support` run looks green: `human-intervention-logs/org.ow2.asm:asm-commons:9.8/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T09-23-25-780860Z.log` ends with `BUILD SUCCESSFUL` and reports all 8 tests passing including native image, and the preserved test results in `tests/src/org.ow2.asm/asm-commons/9.8/build/test-results/test/TEST-org_ow2_asm.asm_commons.Asm_commonsTest.xml` plus `tests/src/org.ow2.asm/asm-commons/9.8/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` show the later 9-test variant also passing on JVM and native image. Metrics do not show a dynamic-access blocker either: `stats/org.ow2.asm/asm-commons/9.8/execution-metrics.json` shows 4 iterations / 552 generated LOC, and `stats/org.ow2.asm/asm-commons/9.8/stats.json` reports `0/0` dynamic-access calls.\\n\\nThe preserved follow-up suggests the workflow drifted into an out-of-scope metadata fix. `human-intervention-logs/org.ow2.asm:asm-commons:9.8/metadata-fix/codex.log` reruns under `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all` and reports changing `metadata/org.ow2.asm/asm/9.4/reachability-metadata.json` and `metadata/org.junit.platform/junit-platform-commons/1.8.2/reachability-metadata.json` to make `asm-commons:9.8` pass. Those edits are outside a normal `library-new-request` scope and are the most likely reason the automation stopped for human review.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.ow2.asm:asm-commons:9.8/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T09-23-25-780860Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.ow2.asm:asm-commons:9.8/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T09-25-27-344884Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.ow2.asm:asm-commons:9.8/metadata-fix/codex.log`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Review the preserved branch and keep only the scoped `asm-commons` additions under `tests/src/org.ow2.asm/asm-commons/9.8`, `metadata/org.ow2.asm/asm-commons/9.8`, and `stats/org.ow2.asm/asm-commons/9.8`.\\n2. Drop or split out the unrelated metadata edits to `metadata/org.ow2.asm/asm/9.4` and `metadata/org.junit.platform/junit-platform-commons/1.8.2`.\\n3. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.ow2.asm:asm-commons:9.8` and only treat `future-defaults-all` cleanup as a separate follow-up if you want to keep that broader change.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3614#issuecomment-4358734341\"}]}},{\"number\":3609,\"title\":\"Support for org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-core:1.9.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3609\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:12:20Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-30T17:10:16Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-core:1.9.0\\n\\n### Reason for requesting the library\\n\\nPopular Maven library rank 237 from `/home/jovan/mvnrepository-popular-scraper/popular-maven-libraries.json`.\\nMirrored from fork issue https://github.com/jormundur00/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3489 after strict `groupId:artifactId` metadata and open-issue filtering.\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"github-actions\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:14:10Z\",\"body\":\"Automation: No dependency issues were created by the triage workflow.\\n\\nThis typically means every dependency in the deps.dev expansion is already supported by the repository.\\n\\nPlan nodes:\\n```\\norg.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-core:1.9.0\\norg.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-core-jvm:1.9.0\\norg.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib:2.2.0\\norg.jetbrains:annotations:13.0\\n```\\n\\nSupported GA detected during checks:\\n```\\norg.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-core-jvm\\norg.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib\\norg.jetbrains:annotations\\n```\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3609#issuecomment-4353189381\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T17:10:09Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job for `org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-core:1.9.0` failed. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3609-library-new-request-org.jetbrains.kotlinx-kotlinx-serialization-core-1.9.0-36de2cf6\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is coverage/metrics setup for the requested coordinate, not the generated Kotlin test itself. The preserved Gradle outputs in `build/tests/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-core:1.9.0/f8b404645b2389f22cd2eba00592e8e8.out` and `build/tests/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-core:1.9.0/9bab911ff000252918610e0124455237.out` fail in `:listLibraryJars` and `:jacocoTestReport` with `No eligible artifacts found on the classpath for org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-core:1.9.0`. That lines up with the published metadata for this coordinate being a multiplatform wrapper (`packaging` is `pom`) that points to `org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-core-jvm:1.9.0` as the JVM artifact. The preserved worktree also contains both `tests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-core/1.9.0/...` and `tests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-core-jvm/1.9.0/...`, and `stats/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-core/1.9.0/execution-metrics.json` ended with `status: failure`, `code_coverage_percent: 0.0`, and no dynamic-access coverage.\\n\\nPlease inspect these logs first:\\n- `logs/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-core:1.9.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T17-02-32-344501Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-core:1.9.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T17-04-47-012168Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-core:1.9.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T17-07-38-328530Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-core:1.9.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n- `logs/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-core:1.9.0/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n- Confirm whether this issue should target `org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-core-jvm:1.9.0` instead of the root `kotlinx-serialization-core` multiplatform coordinate.\\n- If yes, keep only the `-jvm` metadata/tests and rerun the library-new-request flow for the JVM artifact; there is already a successful `stats/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-core-jvm/1.9.0/execution-metrics.json` indicating that coordinate is testable.\\n- If the root coordinate must remain the issue target, update the automation to treat this POM-only wrapper specially and skip JAR/JaCoCo resolution against `org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-core:1.9.0`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3609#issuecomment-4354545796\"}]}},{\"number\":3600,\"title\":\"Support for org.scoverage:scalac-scoverage-plugin:1.1.1\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3600\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:12:02Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-30T17:06:38Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.scoverage:scalac-scoverage-plugin:1.1.1\\n\\n### Reason for requesting the library\\n\\nPopular Maven library rank 221 from `/home/jovan/mvnrepository-popular-scraper/popular-maven-libraries.json`.\\nMirrored from fork issue https://github.com/jormundur00/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3480 after strict `groupId:artifactId` metadata and open-issue filtering.\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"github-actions\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:13:50Z\",\"body\":\"Automation: No dependency issues were created by the triage workflow.\\n\\nThis typically means every dependency in the deps.dev expansion is already supported by the repository.\\n\\nPlan nodes:\\n```\\norg.scoverage:scalac-scoverage-plugin:1.1.1\\n```\\n\\nSupported GA detected during checks:\\n```\\n(none)\\n```\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3600#issuecomment-4353186688\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T17:06:32Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.scoverage:scalac-scoverage-plugin:1.1.1`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3600-library-new-request-org.scoverage-scalac-scoverage-plugin-1.1.1-f0d4fd0c\\n\\nThe most likely failure point was the handoff from artifact discovery into test generation, not artifact discovery itself. In `human-intervention-logs/org.scoverage:scalac-scoverage-plugin:1.1.1/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`, the workflow updates `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/org.scoverage-scalac-scoverage-plugin-1.1.1.json`, validates it with `jq`, reports `Ran agent for org.scoverage:scalac-scoverage-plugin:1.1.1 (exit 0)`, and ends with `BUILD SUCCESSFUL in 2m 40s`; immediately before that, it logs `ERROR codex_core::session: failed to record rollout items: thread 019ddf57-11a1-77a1-9ce9-d24d965cb650 not found`. No library files were generated under `metadata/` or `tests/`, and run metrics / dynamic-access coverage are unavailable, which is consistent with the workflow stopping before scaffolded tests were produced.\\n\\nPlease inspect `human-intervention-logs/org.scoverage:scalac-scoverage-plugin:1.1.1/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`. If you still have the preserved worktree locally, also inspect `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/org.scoverage-scalac-scoverage-plugin-1.1.1.json` and `build/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.scoverage-scalac-scoverage-plugin-1.1.1.log`.\\n\\n1. Use the discovered metadata JSON as the starting point and manually create the `metadata/` and `tests/` scaffolding for `org.scoverage:scalac-scoverage-plugin:1.1.1`.\\n2. Run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.scoverage:scalac-scoverage-plugin:1.1.1` after scaffolding is in place to surface the first real compile/runtime failure.\\n3. Investigate or rerun the automation around the post-discovery session persistence error (`failed to record rollout items: thread ... not found`) if the generator path needs to be restored.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3600#issuecomment-4354521302\"}]}},{\"number\":3283,\"title\":\"Support for org.jboss.modules:jboss-modules:2.1.6.Final\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3283\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-29T06:43:54Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-29T17:35:55Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.jboss.modules:jboss-modules:2.1.6.Final\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[{\"login\":\"kimeta\"}]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-29T17:35:52Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe workflow completed, but it did not produce meaningful dynamic-access coverage for `org.jboss.modules:jboss-modules:2.1.6.Final`. Stats show `0/57` dynamic accesses covered (`46` reflection, `11` resources), and the dynamic-access report has `hasDynamicAccess=false` with an empty `classes` list. The generated tests only cover `Version`, `PathUtils`, `PathFilters`, and basic `PathResourceLoader` behavior, with low library coverage around 4% lines, and they do not exercise core JBoss Modules flows such as module loading, module class loading, `module.xml` parsing, service loading, or module resource discovery. The generated metadata only contains a `java.base` ICU resource conditioned on `PathUtils`, and the test build relies on native-image build arguments for `ModuleLoggerFinder` rather than validating library metadata for the main dynamic paths.\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Add scenario tests based on upstream JBoss Modules tests that create a real module repository with `module.xml` and load modules/classes/resources through `ModuleLoader` and `ModuleClassLoader`.\\n2. Exercise service/provider loading and module resource lookup paths in JVM and native tests, then regenerate or adjust reachability metadata from those scenarios.\\n3. Re-run the dynamic-access report and confirm coverage improves beyond `0/57`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3283#issuecomment-4346063289\"}]}},{\"number\":3276,\"title\":\"Support for com.sun.xml.dtd-parser:dtd-parser:1.5.1\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3276\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-29T06:43:51Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T17:11:28Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\ncom.sun.xml.dtd-parser:dtd-parser:1.5.1\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T17:11:21Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job for `com.sun.xml.dtd-parser:dtd-parser:1.5.1` failed. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3276-library-new-request-com.sun.xml.dtd-parser-dtd-parser-1.5.1-c5f569bb\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was the post-generation `nativeTest` run. The generated work did improve dynamic-access coverage to `8/9`, but `build/tests/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser:dtd-parser:1.5.1/3707db0411d0e6d6eff1f2a466a012f0.out` ends with `Execution failed for task ':nativeTest'` and 9 native test failures. `tests/src/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser/dtd-parser/1.5.1/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` shows repeated `MissingResourceException` for `com_sun_xml_dtd_parser.dtd_parser.resources.Messages` and `ResolverTest` errors for `/unreachable-widget.dtd (No such file or directory)`, so the generated resource-loading tests are not working under Native Image. The generated suite is also incomplete: `tests/src/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser/dtd-parser/1.5.1/src/test/java/com_sun_xml_dtd_parser/dtd_parser/Dtd_parserTest.java` is still the scaffold placeholder, and `tests/src/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser/dtd-parser/1.5.1/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` still leaves `MessageCatalog.isLocaleSupported(MessageCatalog.java:506)` via `ClassLoader#getSystemResourceAsStream(...)` uncovered.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser:dtd-parser:1.5.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T16-56-45-615754Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser:dtd-parser:1.5.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T17-08-27-828177Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser:dtd-parser:1.5.1/3707db0411d0e6d6eff1f2a466a012f0.out`\\n- `tests/src/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser/dtd-parser/1.5.1/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n- Replace the remaining scaffold placeholder test with a library-specific test or remove it if it is unnecessary.\\n- Fix the generated `MessageCatalog`/`Resolver` tests so their bundles and DTD resources are available under Native Image, then rerun the native tests.\\n- Add one focused test for the remaining uncovered `MessageCatalog.isLocaleSupported()` system-resource path and refresh the dynamic-access coverage report.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3276#issuecomment-4360574913\"}]}},{\"number\":3152,\"title\":\"Support for org.apache.parquet:parquet-common:1.12.2\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3152\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:52:54Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-02T02:41:29Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.apache.parquet:parquet-common:1.12.2\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T02:41:24Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.apache.parquet:parquet-common:1.12.2`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3152-library-new-request-org.apache.parquet-parquet-common-1.12.2-3001818e\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is the final native test validation of the generated test. Dynamic-access coverage reached 12/12 (100%), but `stats/org.apache.parquet/parquet-common/1.12.2/execution-metrics.json` still recorded `status: failure` after 5 iterations, and `tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-common/1.12.2/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` shows `CompressionCodecNameTest.resolvesCompressionCodecMetadataAndProbesOptionalHadoopCodecClass()` failing with `expected: org.apache.hadoop.io.compress.GzipCodec but was: null` at `CompressionCodecNameTest.java:24`. The native image itself compiled successfully in `build/tests/org.apache.parquet:parquet-common:1.12.2/1db94b27abd2d887303d81e0ebe6a4d1.out`, but the actual native test run failed in `build/tests/org.apache.parquet:parquet-common:1.12.2/25efb9f6d9841b5199f67e0779814701.out` with `:nativeTest FAILED`.\\n\\nPlease inspect these paths first:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.parquet:parquet-common:1.12.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T02-35-01-227698Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/org.apache.parquet:parquet-common:1.12.2/25efb9f6d9841b5199f67e0779814701.out`\\n- `tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-common/1.12.2/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\\n- `tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-common/1.12.2/src/test/java/org_apache_parquet/parquet_common/CompressionCodecNameTest.java`\\n- `tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-common/1.12.2/src/test/java/org/apache/hadoop/io/compress/GzipCodec.java`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Replace or rework `CompressionCodecNameTest` so it covers a native-image-safe, library-specific path; the current test-scope `GzipCodec` stub is not enough because the codec lookup still resolves to `null` at native runtime.\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.parquet:parquet-common:1.12.2` and confirm both JVM and native tests pass.\\n3. Review the preserved branch for overall `library-new-request` quality before opening a PR, since `tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-common/1.12.2/src/test/java/org_apache_parquet/parquet_common/Parquet_commonTest.java` is still just a placeholder scaffold.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3152#issuecomment-4362703289\"}]}},{\"number\":3102,\"title\":\"Support for org.apache.arrow:arrow-memory-core:7.0.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3102\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:44:08Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-02T03:38:51Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.apache.arrow:arrow-memory-core:7.0.0\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T03:38:46Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job for `org.apache.arrow:arrow-memory-core:7.0.0` failed. Preserved work is available on branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3102-library-new-request-org.apache.arrow-arrow-memory-core-7.0.0-16f0ec47\\n\\nThe most likely failure point is test generation followed by native-test verification. The run metrics ended in failure after 8 iterations with `generated_loc: 0`, `metadata_entries: 0`, and no produced `test_file` or `metadata_file`, and the preserved test tree still contains the scaffold `Arrow_memory_coreTest` placeholder. Native verification logs also show the partial preserved tests failing at runtime: `logs/org.apache.arrow:arrow-memory-core:7.0.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-02T03-35-07-293941Z.log` reports `CheckAllocatorTest` and `DefaultAllocationManagerOptionTest` failing with `ExceptionInInitializerError` caused by `ClassNotFoundException: org.apache.arrow.memory.DefaultAllocationManagerFactory`; earlier runs in `logs/org.apache.arrow:arrow-memory-core:7.0.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-02T03-13-31-516283Z.log` and `logs/org.apache.arrow:arrow-memory-core:7.0.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-02T03-22-54-687051Z.log` failed on missing `org.apache.arrow.memory.NettyAllocationManager`. Dynamic-access coverage reached 6/8 (75%), but the remaining uncovered calls are the two `MemoryUtil` `Constructor#newInstance(...)` sites.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `logs/org.apache.arrow:arrow-memory-core:7.0.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T03-33-37-816836Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.apache.arrow:arrow-memory-core:7.0.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T03-15-40-055389Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.apache.arrow:arrow-memory-core:7.0.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-02T03-35-07-293941Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.apache.arrow:arrow-memory-core:7.0.0/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-02T03-22-54-687051Z.log`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Replace the scaffold `Arrow_memory_coreTest` with a real Arrow-specific test and review whether the preserved `CheckAllocatorTest`, `DefaultAllocationManagerOptionTest`, and `MemoryUtilTest` should be kept or rewritten.\\n2. Fix the native-image allocator discovery path so `DefaultAllocationManagerFactory` / `NettyAllocationManager` are available in native runs, then rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.arrow:arrow-memory-core:7.0.0`.\\n3. If the preserved test-only native config is kept, convert the legacy `reflect-config.json` / `resource-config.json` files to test-only `reachability-metadata.json` and recheck coverage for the two remaining `MemoryUtil` calls.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3102#issuecomment-4362827012\"}]}},{\"number\":3046,\"title\":\"Support for org.apache.kerby:kerby-pkix:1.0.1\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3046\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:43:51Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T20:25:01Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.apache.kerby:kerby-pkix:1.0.1\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T20:24:54Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.apache.kerby:kerby-pkix:1.0.1`, but preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3046-library-new-request-org.apache.kerby-kerby-pkix-1.0.1-a3968aee\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was add-new-library-support test generation/validation, not artifact discovery. In `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.kerby:kerby-pkix:1.0.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T19-49-39-738729Z.log`, the first generated test failed in `:compileTestJava` with `SubjectKeyIdentifier cannot be converted to KeyIdentifier` at `Kerby_pkixTest.java:185`, which caused `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.kerby:kerby-pkix:1.0.1` and `:tckTest` to fail. Discovery and URL population appear to have succeeded in `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.kerby:kerby-pkix:1.0.1/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` and `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.kerby:kerby-pkix:1.0.1/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`.\\n\\nThere is also evidence that the generated work is recoverable. `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.kerby:kerby-pkix:1.0.1/metadata-fix/codex.log` shows the exact `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.kerby:kerby-pkix:1.0.1 --stacktrace` command eventually passing, and the final generated reports under `tests/src/org.apache.kerby/kerby-pkix/1.0.1/build/test-results/test/TEST-org_apache_kerby.kerby_pkix.Kerby_pkixTest.xml` and `tests/src/org.apache.kerby/kerby-pkix/1.0.1/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` both show 8/8 tests passing. Metrics in `stats/org.apache.kerby/kerby-pkix/1.0.1/execution-metrics.json` show a successful 7-iteration recovery run; `stats/org.apache.kerby/kerby-pkix/1.0.1/stats.json` reports `0/0` dynamic-access calls and about 24% line coverage, so there is no useful dynamic-access coverage signal to review.\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Check out the preserved branch and review the generated test plus `metadata/org.apache.kerby/kerby-pkix/1.0.1/reachability-metadata.json`.\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.kerby:kerby-pkix:1.0.1 --stacktrace` on that branch to confirm the compile fix and native-image pass.\\n3. If the result looks acceptable for a `library-new-request`, prepare the final PR from the preserved branch; otherwise regenerate or trim the test based on the original compile failure log.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3046#issuecomment-4361462993\"}]}},{\"number\":3039,\"title\":\"Support for com.sun.jmx:jmxri:1.2.1\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3039\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:43:49Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T17:57:18Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\ncom.sun.jmx:jmxri:1.2.1\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"jormundur00\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T17:51:50Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `com.sun.jmx:jmxri:1.2.1`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fjormundur00%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3039-library-new-request-com.sun.jmx-jmxri-1.2.1-72c87ad6\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was artifact/source discovery leading into test generation, before any generated tests, metadata, stats, or coverage artifacts were produced. In `logs/com.sun.jmx:jmxri:1.2.1/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`, Maven Central resolves this coordinate with only `.pom` metadata, the archived JMX 1.2.1 RI site exposes documentation/examples but the attempted exact-version `src/` path returns HTTP 404, and the resulting `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/com.sun.jmx-jmxri-1.2.1.json` ends up with `source-code-url`, `repository-url`, and `test-code-url` all set to `N/A` while only `documentation-url` is populated. There is also no `tests/src/com.sun.jmx/jmxri/1.2.1`, `metadata/com.sun.jmx/jmxri`, or `stats/com.sun.jmx/jmxri/1.2.1` output in the worktree, and run metrics are unavailable, which is consistent with the workflow failing before test generation and coverage collection.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `logs/com.sun.jmx:jmxri:1.2.1/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n- `build/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/com.sun.jmx-jmxri-1.2.1.log`\\n- `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/com.sun.jmx-jmxri-1.2.1.json`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n- Find a trustworthy exact-version source or source bundle for JMX RI 1.2.1 and update the missing repository/source/test URLs if one exists.\\n- If no exact-version source/test repository is publicly available, decide whether this coordinate should be handled manually from archived materials or skipped as unsupported for automated generation.\\n- After resolving the source context, rerun the new-library workflow so scaffold/test generation and coverage collection can proceed.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3039#issuecomment-4337821544\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T17:57:13Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `com.sun.jmx:jmxri:1.2.1`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3039-library-new-request-com.sun.jmx-jmxri-1.2.1-ae440f71\\n\\nThe most likely failure point was immediately after artifact discovery, before scaffold/test generation started. `human-intervention-logs/com.sun.jmx:jmxri:1.2.1/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` ends with `BUILD SUCCESSFUL` for `:discoverArtifactMetadata`, and `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/com.sun.jmx-jmxri-1.2.1.json` was produced, but it only found a documentation URL and left `source-code-url`, `repository-url`, and `test-code-url` as `N/A`. There is no generated `tests/src/com.sun.jmx/jmxri/1.2.1` tree, no `metadata/com.sun.jmx/jmxri` tree, no `populate_artifact_urls.log`, and no run metrics/dynamic-access report for this library, which points to the workflow stopping before any test scaffold or coverage analysis was created.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.sun.jmx:jmxri:1.2.1/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n- `build/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/com.sun.jmx-jmxri-1.2.1.log`\\n- `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/com.sun.jmx-jmxri-1.2.1.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n- Verify whether this archived Oracle RI artifact has stable source, repository, and test URLs that can replace the current `N/A` values.\\n- If valid upstream materials can be identified, rerun the new-library workflow or scaffold manually for `com.sun.jmx:jmxri:1.2.1`.\\n- If not, decide whether this issue should be handled as a manual metadata/test addition or closed as unsupported due to missing upstream sources.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3039#issuecomment-4360786769\"}]}},{\"number\":3038,\"title\":\"Support for com.sun.jdmk:jmxtools:1.2.1\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3038\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:43:48Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T18:02:33Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\ncom.sun.jdmk:jmxtools:1.2.1\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"jormundur00\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T18:29:14Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job for `com.sun.jdmk:jmxtools:1.2.1` failed. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fjormundur00%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3038-library-new-request-com.sun.jdmk-jmxtools-1.2.1-22650437\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was downstream test generation, not artifact-metadata discovery itself. The preserved `discoverArtifactMetadata` log shows that discovery completed successfully, but Maven Central exposed only `jmxtools-1.2.1.pom`, while direct requests for `jmxtools-1.2.1.jar`, `-sources.jar`, `-javadoc.jar`, and `-tests.jar` returned `404`; the generated discovery JSON therefore ended up with `\\\"source-code-url\\\" : \\\"N/A\\\"`, `\\\"repository-url\\\" : \\\"N/A\\\"`, and `\\\"test-code-url\\\" : \\\"N/A\\\"`, with only a documentation mirror available. There are also no generated outputs for this coordinate under `tests/src/com.sun.jdmk/jmxtools/1.2.1`, `metadata/com.sun.jdmk/jmxtools`, or `stats/com.sun.jdmk/jmxtools`, and metrics are unavailable, which is consistent with test generation never producing usable artifacts.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.sun.jdmk:jmxtools:1.2.1/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n- `build/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/com.sun.jdmk-jmxtools-1.2.1.log`\\n- `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/com.sun.jdmk-jmxtools-1.2.1.json`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Confirm whether an exact-version upstream source or test archive exists for `1.2.1`, or whether this coordinate only ships a POM/docs mirror.\\n2. If the exact-version sources are unavailable, manually decide whether to author the test scaffold from the JMX 1.2.1 RI docs/binaries or to treat this coordinate as unsupported for automated onboarding.\\n3. If a valid upstream source location can be identified, update the preserved branch with that source/test context and rerun scaffold/test generation for `com.sun.jdmk:jmxtools:1.2.1`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3038#issuecomment-4338050546\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T18:02:27Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job failed for `com.sun.jdmk:jmxtools:1.2.1`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3038-library-new-request-com.sun.jdmk-jmxtools-1.2.1-8d40aa50\\n\\nThe most likely failure was after `discoverArtifactMetadata`, during scaffold/test generation. The preserved `logs/com.sun.jdmk:jmxtools:1.2.1/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` shows `:discoverArtifactMetadata` completed successfully, but it only produced `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/com.sun.jdmk-jmxtools-1.2.1.json` with `source-code-url`, `repository-url`, and `test-code-url` all set to `N/A`; the same log notes that Maven only exposes the POM for this coordinate and that the versioned source material found was for `jmxri.jar`, not `jmxtools.jar`. There is also no generated `tests/src/com.sun.jdmk/jmxtools/1.2.1` tree, no `stats/com.sun.jdmk/jmxtools/1.2.1`, and no run metrics or dynamic-access coverage snapshot, which is consistent with generation stopping before tests were created and exercised.\\n\\nPlease inspect `logs/com.sun.jdmk:jmxtools:1.2.1/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` first; if needed, compare it with `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/com.sun.jdmk-jmxtools-1.2.1.json` on the preserved branch.\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n- Verify whether there is a canonical upstream source repository or exact-version source/test artifact for `jmxtools:1.2.1`; if not, decide whether this library is a good candidate for automated onboarding.\\n- If usable sources can be identified, update the preserved branch with correct artifact URLs and add a library-specific test under `tests/src/com.sun.jdmk/jmxtools/1.2.1`.\\n- Re-run the workflow or continue manually from the preserved branch and confirm that test outputs and stats files are generated.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3038#issuecomment-4360811187\"}]}},{\"number\":3036,\"title\":\"Support for org.rxtx:rxtx:2.1.7\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3036\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:43:47Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-29T21:17:21Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.rxtx:rxtx:2.1.7\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"jormundur00\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-29T21:17:13Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job for `org.rxtx:rxtx:2.1.7` failed. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fjormundur00%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3036-library-new-request-org.rxtx-rxtx-2.1.7-65ab19f9\\n\\nThe most likely failure point was the `add-new-library-support` stage after generation started producing RXTX-specific work. `stats/org.rxtx/rxtx/2.1.7/execution-metrics.json` still reports `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, `metadata_entries: 0`, and the same start/end commit (`3ae07b75010d14914d4041ab2f9d7fea539b7ea4`), but `logs/org.rxtx:rxtx:2.1.7/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T20-58-58-009381Z.log` shows the agent actually created and committed RXTX-specific changes as `41ef9d230 Keep Graal SDK off RXTX native image classpath`. Those changes do not appear to have been preserved onto the human-intervention branch.\\n\\nThere is also still a real RXTX runtime problem blocking useful coverage. The generated test artifacts show `CommPortIdentifierTest` running, but `build/tests/org.rxtx:rxtx:2.1.7/40132cecd17098f522bc9d1ac443c573.out` and `build/tests/org.rxtx:rxtx:2.1.7/603e0e8a6510e1bb034e539d47d4403e.out` report `UnsatisfiedLinkError` / `NoClassDefFoundError` while loading `gnu.io.RXTXCommDriver`, including `Can't load library: rxtxSerial`. Coverage stayed at `0/1`: `tests/src/org.rxtx/rxtx/2.1.7/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` still shows the remaining uncovered call `java.lang.Class#newInstance()` from `gnu.io.CommPortIdentifier.getPortIdentifiers(CommPortIdentifier.java:260)`.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `logs/org.rxtx:rxtx:2.1.7/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T20-58-58-009381Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.rxtx:rxtx:2.1.7/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n- `logs/org.rxtx:rxtx:2.1.7/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Recover or reapply the generated RXTX-specific patch from commit `41ef9d230` onto the preserved branch.\\n2. Rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.rxtx:rxtx:2.1.7` and fix the RXTX native library setup so `gnu.io.RXTXCommDriver` can load `rxtxSerial` under native-image tests.\\n3. Recheck `tests/src/org.rxtx/rxtx/2.1.7/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` and iterate until `CommPortIdentifier` coverage is no longer `0/1`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3036#issuecomment-4347573505\"}]}},{\"number\":3033,\"title\":\"Support for com.esotericsoftware:kryo-shaded:3.0.3\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3033\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:43:47Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-30T01:30:01Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\ncom.esotericsoftware:kryo-shaded:3.0.3\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"jormundur00\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T01:29:53Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `com.esotericsoftware:kryo-shaded:3.0.3`. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fjormundur00%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3033-library-new-request-com.esotericsoftware-kryo-shaded-3.0.3-e88a5e58\\n\\nMost likely failing stage: post-generation native-test validation/test curation. The generator produced several tests that exercise ReflectASM runtime class generation (`*FieldAccess`, `*MethodAccess`, `*ConstructorAccess`), which Native Image rejects by default. That is called out in `post-gen-interventions/com.esotericsoftware_kryo-shaded_3.0.3.md` and `human-intervention-logs/com.esotericsoftware:kryo-shaded:3.0.3/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-04-30T01-24-25-869652Z.log`. The earlier generation log also shows those tests being generated (`MethodAccessTest`, `ConstructorAccessTest`, `FieldSerializerTest`, `BeanSerializerInnerCachedPropertyTest`, `ClosureSerializerTest`, etc.) in `human-intervention-logs/com.esotericsoftware:kryo-shaded:3.0.3/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T01-02-27-375281Z.log`.\\n\\nAfter removing the non-metadata failures, the preserved targeted run still has one metadata-related native failure: `ExternalizableSerializerTest#usesJavaSerializationWhenAnInheritedWriteReplaceMethodIsPresent()` fails with `MissingReflectionRegistrationError: Cannot reflectively invoke constructor 'public java.lang.Object()'`. See `human-intervention-logs/com.esotericsoftware:kryo-shaded:3.0.3/metadata-fix/codex.log` and `build/tests/com.esotericsoftware:kryo-shaded:3.0.3/2393a4384e54a909640d231902e5f89e.out`. That run reached 48 native tests with 47 passing, so the remaining work is focused rather than a full regeneration problem. The execution metrics also recorded an overall failure after 42 iterations in `stats/com.esotericsoftware/kryo-shaded/3.0.3/execution-metrics.json`.\\n\\n1. Inspect the preserved `ExternalizableSerializerTest` failure and decide whether the fix should be a refined metadata entry for the `ObjectInputStream` deserialization path or a test adjustment if that path is not supportable.\\n2. Review the generated tests called out in the post-gen intervention report and keep only coverage that does not rely on ReflectASM runtime class definition under native image.\\n3. Re-run `./gradlew clean test -Pcoordinates=com.esotericsoftware:kryo-shaded:3.0.3 --stacktrace` on the preserved branch after the metadata/test cleanup.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3033#issuecomment-4348911093\"}]}},{\"number\":3024,\"title\":\"Support for org.apache.commons:commons-crypto:1.1.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3024\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:43:45Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-29T23:00:19Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.apache.commons:commons-crypto:1.1.0\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-29T23:00:14Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.apache.commons:commons-crypto:1.1.0`. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3024-library-new-request-org.apache.commons-commons-crypto-1.1.0-18efe052\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was `add-new-library-support`, specifically native-test validation / artifact promotion. `stats/org.apache.commons/commons-crypto/1.1.0/execution-metrics.json` records `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, `test_file: None`, and `metadata_file: None`, even though the preserved work reaches 9/9 dynamic-access coverage. The preserved output is not shippable as-is: `tests/src/org.apache.commons/commons-crypto/1.1.0/src/test/java/org_apache_commons/commons_crypto/Commons_cryptoTest.java` is still the scaffold placeholder, `metadata/org.apache.commons/commons-crypto/1.1.0/reachability-metadata.json` is `{}`, and the preserved native test results fail with 4 errors, including `ClassNotFoundException` for `org.apache.commons.crypto.Crypto`, `org.apache.commons.crypto.random.JavaCryptoRandom`, and `org.apache.commons.crypto.cipher.JceCipher`, plus `NoSuchMethodException` for `CryptoRandomFactory.<init>()`. The preserved Gradle output also ends with `Execution failed for task ':nativeTest'`.\\n\\nLogs worth checking:\\n- `logs/org.apache.commons:commons-crypto:1.1.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T22-49-42-730363Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.apache.commons:commons-crypto:1.1.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T22-52-15-839156Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.apache.commons:commons-crypto:1.1.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T22-54-52-467127Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.apache.commons:commons-crypto:1.1.0/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n- `logs/org.apache.commons:commons-crypto:1.1.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Replace/remove the scaffold `Commons_cryptoTest` and review `ReflectionUtilsTest` / `CryptoInputStreamTest` so they only assert valid native-image behavior.\\n2. Add the missing reachability metadata for the reflectively loaded Commons Crypto classes/providers, then re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.commons:commons-crypto:1.1.0`.\\n3. Re-check the preserved branch against the `add-new-library-support` logs before re-running automation.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3024#issuecomment-4348128934\"}]}},{\"number\":3017,\"title\":\"Support for io.trino.hadoop:hadoop-apache:3.2.0-12\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3017\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:43:43Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T18:34:43Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nio.trino.hadoop:hadoop-apache:3.2.0-12\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T20:22:32Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `io.trino.hadoop:hadoop-apache:3.2.0-12`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3017-library-new-request-io.trino.hadoop-hadoop-apache-3.2.0-12-d77abfc2\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is downstream metrics / dynamic-access reporting, not the final test-generation pass itself. Earlier generation iterations did fail in the expected places: `logs/io.trino.hadoop:hadoop-apache:3.2.0-12/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T19-57-19-626662Z.log` shows native test failures (`UnsupportedOperationException: getSubject is not supported` and `SequenceFile doesn't work with GzipCodec without native-hadoop code!`), and `logs/io.trino.hadoop:hadoop-apache:3.2.0-12/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T20-03-50-745746Z.log` shows `checkstyleTest` failures for an illegal space and non-ASCII characters in `Hadoop_apacheTest.java`. However, the final iteration in `logs/io.trino.hadoop:hadoop-apache:3.2.0-12/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T20-09-12-574447Z.log` ends with the agent reporting `./gradlew checkstyle javaTest nativeTestCompile -Pcoordinates=io.trino.hadoop:hadoop-apache:3.2.0-12 --stacktrace`, `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.trino.hadoop:hadoop-apache:3.2.0-12 --stacktrace`, and `./gradlew spotlessCheck -Pcoordinates=io.trino.hadoop:hadoop-apache:3.2.0-12 --stacktrace` as passing. The run summary still records `Metrics status: failure` and `Dynamic-access coverage: unavailable`, which suggests the failure happened after generation while collecting or publishing metrics.\\n\\nPlease inspect these logs first:\\n- `logs/io.trino.hadoop:hadoop-apache:3.2.0-12/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T20-09-12-574447Z.log`\\n- `logs/io.trino.hadoop:hadoop-apache:3.2.0-12/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T20-03-50-745746Z.log`\\n- `logs/io.trino.hadoop:hadoop-apache:3.2.0-12/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T19-57-19-626662Z.log`\\n- `logs/io.trino.hadoop:hadoop-apache:3.2.0-12/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n- `logs/io.trino.hadoop:hadoop-apache:3.2.0-12/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Check out the preserved branch and rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.trino.hadoop:hadoop-apache:3.2.0-12` (and the `future-defaults-all` lane if needed) to confirm the final generated state is still green.\\n2. Inspect the metrics / dynamic-access output location for this run and determine why coverage was not produced even though the last generation log reports passing validation.\\n3. If validation is green locally, continue from the preserved branch and regenerate or manually record the missing metrics so the library can move forward.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3017#issuecomment-4338782551\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T18:34:37Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `io.trino.hadoop:hadoop-apache:3.2.0-12`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: `https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3017-library-new-request-io.trino.hadoop-hadoop-apache-3.2.0-12-1f1975e5`\\n\\nMost likely failing stage: post-validation coverage/metrics aggregation, not the final generated test source itself. The preserved logs show earlier failures during the generation loop: `sequenceFilePersistsMetadataAndWritableRecords()` hit `java.io.EOFException` in `human-intervention-logs/io.trino.hadoop:hadoop-apache:3.2.0-12/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T18-11-50-076459Z.log`, and one native-image build failed to link SCTP JNI symbols in `build/tests/io.trino.hadoop:hadoop-apache:3.2.0-12/355de4c5eb8549d02846c73046862c80.out`. However, the last preserved generation attempt passed `test`/`nativeTest`, metadata validation, and checkstyle (`human-intervention-logs/io.trino.hadoop:hadoop-apache:3.2.0-12/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T18-23-47-255026Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/io.trino.hadoop:hadoop-apache:3.2.0-12/checkstyle/pi-checkstyle-2026-05-01T18-27-25-088792Z.log`).\\n\\nThe remaining evidence is that `stats/io.trino.hadoop/hadoop-apache/3.2.0-12/execution-metrics.json` still records `\\\"status\\\": \\\"failure\\\"` and `\\\"code_coverage_percent\\\": 0.0`, dynamic-access coverage is unavailable, and there is no `stats/io.trino.hadoop/hadoop-apache/3.2.0-12/stats.json` even though dynamic-access artifacts were emitted under `tests/src/io.trino.hadoop/hadoop-apache/3.2.0-12/build/native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access/hadoop-apache-3.2.0-12/`.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.trino.hadoop:hadoop-apache:3.2.0-12/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T18-11-50-076459Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.trino.hadoop:hadoop-apache:3.2.0-12/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T18-17-30-004718Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.trino.hadoop:hadoop-apache:3.2.0-12/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T18-23-47-255026Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.trino.hadoop:hadoop-apache:3.2.0-12/checkstyle/pi-checkstyle-2026-05-01T18-27-25-088792Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/io.trino.hadoop:hadoop-apache:3.2.0-12/355de4c5eb8549d02846c73046862c80.out`\\n- `stats/io.trino.hadoop/hadoop-apache/3.2.0-12/execution-metrics.json`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Reproduce from the preserved branch and confirm whether the generated tests are already green on a clean run.\\n2. Trace why the dynamic-access artifacts were not promoted into `stats/io.trino.hadoop/hadoop-apache/3.2.0-12/stats.json` and why metrics stayed at failure/`0.0%`.\\n3. If native-image still flakes on your environment, investigate the SCTP JNI linker failure from `355de4c5eb8549d02846c73046862c80.out` before re-running the `library-new-request` pipeline.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3017#issuecomment-4360960223\"}]}},{\"number\":3011,\"title\":\"Support for org.codehaus.janino:commons-compiler:3.0.16\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3011\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:43:41Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-30T02:15:05Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.codehaus.janino:commons-compiler:3.0.16\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"jormundur00\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T02:14:59Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.codehaus.janino:commons-compiler:3.0.16`. Preserved work is available on branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fjormundur00%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3011-library-new-request-org.codehaus.janino-commons-compiler-3.0.16-cbc2014e\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was the agent-side test generation/finalization step, not the library validation itself. The run metrics in `stats/org.codehaus.janino/commons-compiler/3.0.16/execution-metrics.json` ended with `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, and `artifacts.test_file` / `artifacts.metadata_file` both set to `None`, even though generated tests and metadata are present in the preserved worktree and the dynamic-access report shows `19/19` covered calls. In the final generation log, `human-intervention-logs/org.codehaus.janino:commons-compiler:3.0.16/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T02-10-30-205883Z.log`, the agent explicitly says it committed focused test updates but “did not compile or run tests” and left `metadata/org.codehaus.janino/commons-compiler/3.0.16/reachability-metadata.json` untracked. Earlier generation logs such as `human-intervention-logs/org.codehaus.janino:commons-compiler:3.0.16/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T01-36-15-007472Z.log` also show source-context lookup problems (`local_repositories/source_context/.../main/extracted` not found), which likely contributed to the failed rollout bookkeeping.\\n\\nThe preserved build outputs suggest the generated tests themselves are probably viable: `build/tests/org.codehaus.janino:commons-compiler:3.0.16/31ab6ccdff09a79731dd1433aef209eb.out` shows `test` and `nativeTestCompile` succeeding, `build/tests/org.codehaus.janino:commons-compiler:3.0.16/a663f305b40a35010600747d8525518e.out` shows `jacocoTestReport` succeeding, and `tests/src/org.codehaus.janino/commons-compiler/3.0.16/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` reports full `19/19` dynamic-access coverage.\\n\\nRecommended next steps:\\n1. Review the preserved branch and decide whether to keep and polish the generated tests plus `metadata/org.codehaus.janino/commons-compiler/3.0.16/reachability-metadata.json`, since the artifacts appear to exist but were not finalized cleanly by automation.\\n2. Re-run the normal library validation for `org.codehaus.janino:commons-compiler:3.0.16` from the preserved branch to confirm the generated test set is stable end-to-end.\\n3. Inspect the generation logs and metrics mismatch (`human-intervention-logs/.../add-new-library-support/*.log` and `stats/.../execution-metrics.json`) to determine why successful generated artifacts were recorded as `generated_loc: 0` and `None`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3011#issuecomment-4349229504\"}]}},{\"number\":3007,\"title\":\"Support for org.apache.parquet:parquet-jackson:1.12.2\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3007\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:43:40Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-30T05:08:09Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.apache.parquet:parquet-jackson:1.12.2\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"jormundur00\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T05:08:03Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.apache.parquet:parquet-jackson:1.12.2`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fjormundur00%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-3007-library-new-request-org.apache.parquet-parquet-jackson-1.12.2-7a1f9026\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was generated test validation in native runtime. The native image build and dynamic-access reporting completed successfully, and coverage reached `70/70 (100.00%)`, but `:nativeTest` still failed with 6 errors (`46/52` tests passed). The failing cases were `AnnotatedConstructorTest`, `AnnotatedFieldTest`, and `AnnotatedMethodTest` (`InvalidClassException: ... no valid constructor` during serialization round-trip), `ClassUtilInnerEnumTypeLocatorTest` for empty `EnumSet` and `EnumMap` (`IllegalStateException: Cannot figure out type for EnumSet/EnumMap`), and `ClassUtilTest.reloadsClassMethodsFromContextClassLoaderWhenMethodTypesAreMissing()` (`ClassNotFoundException` synthesized from constant `Class.forName`). The final generation attempt also shows the agent committed only `ObjectBufferTest.java` while `metadata/org.apache.parquet/parquet-jackson/1.12.2/` remained untracked, and `stats/org.apache.parquet/parquet-jackson/1.12.2/execution-metrics.json` still recorded `generated_loc: 0`, `metadata_entries: 0`, and `artifacts.test_file` / `metadata_file` as `None`.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.parquet:parquet-jackson:1.12.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T05-01-50-981832Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/org.apache.parquet:parquet-jackson:1.12.2/737f9a532d1fa11c365f52c86bcdf830.out`\\n- `tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-jackson/1.12.2/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\\n- `stats/org.apache.parquet/parquet-jackson/1.12.2/execution-metrics.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Review and fix or remove the 6 generated native-failing tests on the preserved branch, especially the serialization round-trip and `EnumSet`/`EnumMap`/`Class.forName` cases.\\n2. Confirm the generated metadata under `metadata/org.apache.parquet/parquet-jackson/1.12.2/` is actually added on the preserved branch together with the test changes.\\n3. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.parquet:parquet-jackson:1.12.2` after adjusting the test set.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/3007#issuecomment-4349848702\"}]}},{\"number\":2989,\"title\":\"Support for dnsjava:dnsjava:2.1.7\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2989\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:43:32Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T17:08:19Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\ndnsjava:dnsjava:2.1.7\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T17:08:12Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `dnsjava:dnsjava:2.1.7`. Preserved work is available on branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2989-library-new-request-dnsjava-dnsjava-2.1.7-667cfe6f\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is post-generation native test validation, not artifact discovery or coverage collection. `populate-artifact-urls` and `discover-artifact-metadata` both completed successfully, JVM tests passed, native-image compilation succeeded, and the dynamic-access report reached `10/10 (100.00%)`; however `build/tests/dnsjava:dnsjava:2.1.7/17dd67b396d54b3ec3c0b3e55809e6c7.out` shows `> Task :nativeTest FAILED`, with `ResolverConfigTest.windowsParserLoadsLocaleSpecificResourceBundleAndParsesDnsServers()` and `windowsParserLoadsDefaultResourceBundleAndParsesDnsServers()` both failing with `java.lang.NoSuchFieldException: servers`. The native JUnit XML at `tests/src/dnsjava/dnsjava/2.1.7/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` confirms the failure comes from `ResolverConfigTest.newEmptyResolverConfig()` reflecting on `ResolverConfig` private fields that are not available at native runtime. There is also still a scaffold placeholder test printing `This is just a placeholder, implement your test`, so the generated suite likely needs cleanup beyond the native fix.\\n\\nLogs and artifacts to inspect:\\n- `logs/dnsjava:dnsjava:2.1.7/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T16-58-50-673024Z.log`\\n- `logs/dnsjava:dnsjava:2.1.7/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T17-00-56-123538Z.log`\\n- `logs/dnsjava:dnsjava:2.1.7/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T17-04-50-958634Z.log`\\n- `logs/dnsjava:dnsjava:2.1.7/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n- `logs/dnsjava:dnsjava:2.1.7/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n- `build/tests/dnsjava:dnsjava:2.1.7/17dd67b396d54b3ec3c0b3e55809e6c7.out`\\n- `tests/src/dnsjava/dnsjava/2.1.7/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n\\n1. Fix `tests/src/dnsjava/dnsjava/2.1.7/src/test/java/dnsjava/dnsjava/ResolverConfigTest.java` so it does not depend on reflective access to `ResolverConfig` private fields under native image.\\n2. Replace or remove the scaffold placeholder in `tests/src/dnsjava/dnsjava/2.1.7/src/test/java/dnsjava/dnsjava/DnsjavaTest.java`.\\n3. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=dnsjava:dnsjava:2.1.7` and confirm native tests pass while dynamic-access coverage stays at `10/10`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2989#issuecomment-4360560815\"}]}},{\"number\":2976,\"title\":\"Support for it.unimi.dsi:fastutil:8.1.1\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2976\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:43:23Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T18:30:53Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nit.unimi.dsi:fastutil:8.1.1\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T23:34:05Z\",\"body\":\"### Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `it.unimi.dsi:fastutil:8.1.1`. Preserved work is available on: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2976-library-new-request-it.unimi.dsi-fastutil-8.1.1-0f7b1b4c\\n\\nThe earliest concrete failure is in test generation: `human-intervention-logs/it.unimi.dsi:fastutil:8.1.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T23-26-15-197089Z.log` shows `FastutilTest > sortedSetAndPriorityQueueProvidePrimitiveOrderedContainers()` failing with `expected: 5` / `but was: 7`, followed by `8 tests completed, 1 failed`, `BUILD FAILED`, and `Test for it.unimi.dsi:fastutil:8.1.1 failed with exit code 1`. Later preserved runs appear to recover: `human-intervention-logs/it.unimi.dsi:fastutil:8.1.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T23-28-10-633106Z.log` shows `0 tests failed` and `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`, and `human-intervention-logs/it.unimi.dsi:fastutil:8.1.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T23-29-52-458711Z.log` shows final `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=it.unimi.dsi:fastutil:8.1.1 --stacktrace` and `./gradlew checkstyle -Pcoordinates=it.unimi.dsi:fastutil:8.1.1 --stacktrace` both passing, including native-image execution. Metrics still ended in failure with dynamic-access coverage unavailable, and both `human-intervention-logs/it.unimi.dsi:fastutil:8.1.1/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` and `human-intervention-logs/it.unimi.dsi:fastutil:8.1.1/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` contain `failed to record rollout items: thread ... not found`, so the workflow may also have failed to record/finalize the successful preserved state.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/it.unimi.dsi:fastutil:8.1.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T23-26-15-197089Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/it.unimi.dsi:fastutil:8.1.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T23-28-10-633106Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/it.unimi.dsi:fastutil:8.1.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T23-29-52-458711Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/it.unimi.dsi:fastutil:8.1.1/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/it.unimi.dsi:fastutil:8.1.1/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Check out the preserved branch and rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=it.unimi.dsi:fastutil:8.1.1` and `./gradlew checkstyle -Pcoordinates=it.unimi.dsi:fastutil:8.1.1` to confirm the preserved state is still green.\\n2. Review the generated test/metadata on that branch and open a manual PR if the preserved changes look acceptable.\\n3. Investigate the `failed to record rollout items: thread ... not found` session error, since it may be why the run stayed in `test_generation_failed` despite later passing logs.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2976#issuecomment-4339840853\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T18:30:44Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `it.unimi.dsi:fastutil:8.1.1`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2976-library-new-request-it.unimi.dsi-fastutil-8.1.1-37e70306\\n\\nMost likely failing stage: `add-new-library-support` orchestration / metrics finalization, not the preserved test artifacts themselves. The first generation attempt hit repeated response-stream disconnects in `human-intervention-logs/it.unimi.dsi:fastutil:8.1.1/failure-analysis/codex_failure_analysis_issue_2976.log` and `human-intervention-logs/it.unimi.dsi:fastutil:8.1.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T17-49-14-598276Z.log`. Later preserved artifacts show successful validation: `build/tests/it.unimi.dsi:fastutil:8.1.1/01eea6a4655fea6ded39773fa3d15b26.out` reports native-image execution with 11 tests successful and 0 failed, and `tests/src/it.unimi.dsi/fastutil/8.1.1/build/test-results/test/TEST-it_unimi_dsi.fastutil.FastutilTest.xml` records 11 tests, 0 failures, 0 errors. Coverage bookkeeping appears incomplete: `stats/it.unimi.dsi/fastutil/8.1.1/execution-metrics.json` still ends with `\\\"status\\\": \\\"failure\\\"`, `\\\"tested_library_loc\\\": 0`, and `\\\"code_coverage_percent\\\": 0.0`, while `stats/it.unimi.dsi/fastutil/8.1.1/stats.json` was not written even though `tests/src/it.unimi.dsi/fastutil/8.1.1/build/native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access/fastutil-8.1.1/reflection-calls.json` and `tests/src/it.unimi.dsi/fastutil/8.1.1/build/reports/jacoco/test/jacocoTestReport.xml` exist.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/it.unimi.dsi:fastutil:8.1.1/failure-analysis/codex_failure_analysis_issue_2976.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/it.unimi.dsi:fastutil:8.1.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T17-49-14-598276Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/it.unimi.dsi:fastutil:8.1.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T18-18-17-477666Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/it.unimi.dsi:fastutil:8.1.1/01eea6a4655fea6ded39773fa3d15b26.out`\\n- `stats/it.unimi.dsi/fastutil/8.1.1/execution-metrics.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n- Review the preserved branch and decide whether to keep the generated `FastutilTest` / metadata, since the preserved test artifacts pass.\\n- Re-run or manually finish the coverage/stats export for this coordinate so `stats/it.unimi.dsi/fastutil/8.1.1/stats.json` is generated and the metrics are reconciled.\\n- If the rerun still fails, investigate the transient stream-disconnect/orchestration failure from the first generation attempt.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2976#issuecomment-4360942057\"}]}},{\"number\":2904,\"title\":\"Support for net.sf.ehcache:ehcache-core:2.4.4\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2904\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:42:54Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-02T03:00:32Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nnet.sf.ehcache:ehcache-core:2.4.4\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T03:00:26Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job failed for `net.sf.ehcache:ehcache-core:2.4.4`. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2904-library-new-request-net.sf.ehcache-ehcache-core-2.4.4-18378238\\n\\nThe most likely failure happened after the last successful generation/native-trace cycle, in result accounting or metrics capture rather than in the generated test itself. In `human-intervention-logs/net.sf.ehcache:ehcache-core:2.4.4/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T02-54-11-880498Z.log`, the agent reports adding `tests/src/net.sf.ehcache/ehcache-core/2.4.4/src/test/java/net_sf_ehcache/ehcache_core/ProductInfoTest.java` and `metadata/net.sf.ehcache/ehcache-core/2.4.4/reachability-metadata.json`; `human-intervention-logs/net.sf.ehcache:ehcache-core:2.4.4/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-02T02-55-22-111250Z.log` ends with `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`; and `tests/src/net.sf.ehcache/ehcache-core/2.4.4/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` shows 96/96 covered calls (100.00%), including the final `net.sf.ehcache.util.ProductInfo.parseProductInfo(ProductInfo.java:67)` resource access. However, `stats/net.sf.ehcache/ehcache-core/2.4.4/execution-metrics.json` still records `\\\"status\\\": \\\"failure\\\"`, `\\\"generated_loc\\\": 0`, `\\\"metadata_entries\\\": 0`, and `\\\"artifacts\\\": { \\\"test_file\\\": \\\"None\\\", \\\"metadata_file\\\": \\\"None\\\" }`, which does not match the preserved branch contents.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/net.sf.ehcache:ehcache-core:2.4.4/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T02-54-11-880498Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/net.sf.ehcache:ehcache-core:2.4.4/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-02T02-55-22-111250Z.log`\\n- `stats/net.sf.ehcache/ehcache-core/2.4.4/execution-metrics.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Review the preserved branch and recover `ProductInfoTest.java` plus `metadata/net.sf.ehcache/ehcache-core/2.4.4/reachability-metadata.json` into a PR if they look correct.\\n2. Re-run the library validation from that preserved state to confirm the generated files pass end-to-end.\\n3. Investigate why the metrics/artifact recording step reported zero generated output even though the preserved branch contains the generated test and metadata.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2904#issuecomment-4362739369\"}]}},{\"number\":2894,\"title\":\"Support for commons-beanutils:commons-beanutils-core:1.8.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2894\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:42:50Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T18:06:45Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\ncommons-beanutils:commons-beanutils-core:1.8.0\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T18:06:39Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `commons-beanutils:commons-beanutils-core:1.8.0`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: `https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2894-library-new-request-commons-beanutils-commons-beanutils-core-1.8.0-1c4ec19a`\\n\\nMost likely failing stage: the dynamic-access test-generation loop did not actually cover the remaining `LocaleConvertUtilsBean` sites. In `human-intervention-logs/commons-beanutils:commons-beanutils-core:1.8.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T18-02-59-740412Z.log`, the final attempt targets `org.apache.commons.beanutils.locale.LocaleConvertUtilsBean` and claims it added `LocaleConvertUtilsBeanTest.java` to hit `Class#forName` and `Array#newInstance`, but `tests/src/commons-beanutils/commons-beanutils-core/1.8.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` still shows `LocaleConvertUtilsBean` at `0/2` covered and overall dynamic-access coverage remains `69/94 (73.40%)`. The run metrics in `stats/commons-beanutils/commons-beanutils-core/1.8.0/execution-metrics.json` also stayed on the starting commit (`da97572125ad0572ccf9e5904a3e516bf740dea5` -> same commit) and recorded `generated_loc: 0`, `test_file: None`, and `metadata_file: None`, which matches the `test_generation_failed` reason.\\n\\nThere is also preserved but incomplete follow-up work: the branch adds `tests/src/commons-beanutils/commons-beanutils-core/1.8.0/src/test/java/commons_beanutils/commons_beanutils_core/LocaleConvertUtilsBeanTest.java`, and its JVM report passes in `tests/src/commons-beanutils/commons-beanutils-core/1.8.0/build/test-results/test/TEST-commons_beanutils.commons_beanutils_core.LocaleConvertUtilsBeanTest.xml`, but the metadata file is still `{}` and native execution still has 16 errors in `tests/src/commons-beanutils/commons-beanutils-core/1.8.0/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`. An earlier attempt worth checking is `human-intervention-logs/commons-beanutils:commons-beanutils-core:1.8.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T17-55-15-161610Z.log`, which worked on `WrapDynaClassTest` but that source file was not preserved in the final commit.\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Review the preserved `LocaleConvertUtilsBeanTest.java` and the earlier `WrapDynaClassTest` attempt from the logs, then replace/refine the generated test so it actually hits the two uncovered `LocaleConvertUtilsBean` dynamic-access call sites.\\n2. Add the missing reachability metadata needed for the native failures instead of leaving `metadata/commons-beanutils/commons-beanutils-core/1.8.0/reachability-metadata.json` empty.\\n3. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=commons-beanutils:commons-beanutils-core:1.8.0` and confirm both the dynamic-access report improves past `69/94` and the native errors are gone.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2894#issuecomment-4360831169\"}]}},{\"number\":2889,\"title\":\"Support for org.apache.htrace:htrace-core:3.1.0-incubating\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2889\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:42:49Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T19:51:29Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.apache.htrace:htrace-core:3.1.0-incubating\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T19:51:23Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.apache.htrace:htrace-core:3.1.0-incubating`. Preserved work is available on the branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2889-library-new-request-org.apache.htrace-htrace-core-3.1.0-incubating-ff652950\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is test generation/content review, not a current Gradle or native-image build break. The generation log shows the workflow explicitly chasing dynamic-access coverage for internal shaded classes such as `org.apache.htrace.fasterxml.jackson.databind.util.ArrayBuilders` (`human-intervention-logs/org.apache.htrace:htrace-core:3.1.0-incubating/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T18-04-36-225948Z.log`). The generated tests are correspondingly dominated by shaded Jackson and commons-logging internals: for example, `BeanDeserializerBaseTest.java` imports `org.apache.htrace.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper`, and `LogFactoryImplTest.java` targets `org.apache.htrace.commons.logging.impl.LogFactoryImpl`. The final dynamic-access report is 100/103 covered, but the covered calls break down to 62 shaded Jackson, 32 commons-logging, and only 9 other HTrace calls (`tests/src/org.apache.htrace/htrace-core/3.1.0-incubating/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`). A later replay in `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.htrace:htrace-core:3.1.0-incubating/metadata-fix/codex.log` shows `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.htrace:htrace-core:3.1.0-incubating` succeeding with 52 native tests, 0 failures, and 1 aborted native test, which points to a quality/scope problem in the generated tests rather than an active infra failure. The run metrics also ended in failure after 43 iterations and 1753 generated LOC (`stats/org.apache.htrace/htrace-core/3.1.0-incubating/execution-metrics.json`).\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.htrace:htrace-core:3.1.0-incubating/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T18-04-36-225948Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.htrace:htrace-core:3.1.0-incubating/metadata-fix/codex.log`\\n- `tests/src/org.apache.htrace/htrace-core/3.1.0-incubating/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n- `tests/src/org.apache.htrace/htrace-core/3.1.0-incubating/src/test/java/org_apache_htrace/htrace_core/`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Replace the shaded-Jackson/commons-logging-heavy generated tests with HTrace-specific tests that exercise public tracing behavior for this coordinate.\\n2. Review the preserved native tests for policy issues; `LogFactoryImplTest` currently aborts one native case instead of proving the behavior under native image.\\n3. Re-run `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=org.apache.htrace:htrace-core:3.1.0-incubating` and `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.htrace:htrace-core:3.1.0-incubating` after narrowing the test set.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2889#issuecomment-4361304532\"}]}},{\"number\":2877,\"title\":\"Support for org.slf4j:slf4j-ext:1.5.10\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2877\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:42:42Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-29T21:52:22Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.slf4j:slf4j-ext:1.5.10\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-29T21:52:15Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.slf4j:slf4j-ext:1.5.10`. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2877-library-new-request-org.slf4j-slf4j-ext-1.5.10-41174777\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was `add-new-library-support` / test generation finalization, not artifact URL discovery. Both `populate-artifact-urls` and `discover-artifact-metadata` completed without obvious failures, but `human-intervention-logs/org.slf4j:slf4j-ext:1.5.10/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T21-49-35-239660Z.log` shows early `ENOENT` errors for `DEVELOPING.md` and the `source_context` path to `LogTransformer.java`, then a later commit (`fe501fcaf2`) adding test changes. The preserved outputs are also inconsistent with the recorded metrics: `stats/org.slf4j/slf4j-ext/1.5.10/execution-metrics.json` reports `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, `metadata_entries: 0`, and `artifacts.test_file` / `artifacts.metadata_file` as `None`, even though the preserved branch contains generated tests and `metadata/org.slf4j/slf4j-ext/1.5.10/reachability-metadata.json`. The generated test set is also incomplete as preserved: `tests/src/org.slf4j/slf4j-ext/1.5.10/src/test/java/org_slf4j/slf4j_ext/Slf4j_extTest.java` is still the scaffold placeholder, while `LogTransformerTest.java` is the only library-specific test. Since dynamic-access coverage was reported as `1/1 (100.00%)`, this looks more like a generation/finalization problem than an uncovered-callsite problem.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.slf4j:slf4j-ext:1.5.10/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T21-49-35-239660Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.slf4j:slf4j-ext:1.5.10/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.slf4j:slf4j-ext:1.5.10/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n- `tests/src/org.slf4j/slf4j-ext/1.5.10/src/test/java/org_slf4j/slf4j_ext/Slf4j_extTest.java`\\n- `tests/src/org.slf4j/slf4j-ext/1.5.10/src/test/java/org_slf4j/slf4j_ext/LogTransformerTest.java`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Clean up the preserved test set by removing or replacing the scaffold `Slf4j_extTest.java` and validating whether `LogTransformerTest.java` plus the `build.gradle` change are the intended final submission.\\n2. Run `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=org.slf4j:slf4j-ext:1.5.10` and `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.slf4j:slf4j-ext:1.5.10` from the preserved branch.\\n3. If those pass, continue from the preserved branch and refresh the library-new-request submission.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2877#issuecomment-4347808449\"}]}},{\"number\":2862,\"title\":\"Support for org.codehaus.jackson:jackson-mapper-asl:1.8.3\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2862\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:42:32Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-02T00:45:53Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.codehaus.jackson:jackson-mapper-asl:1.8.3\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T00:45:45Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.codehaus.jackson:jackson-mapper-asl:1.8.3`. Preserved work is available on the branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2862-library-new-request-org.codehaus.jackson-jackson-mapper-asl-1.8.3-3f926576\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was post-generation validation/native test execution, not coverage collection. The generated suite reached full dynamic-access coverage (`55/55` in `tests/src/org.codehaus.jackson/jackson-mapper-asl/1.8.3/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`), but native results still show `44` JUnit Jupiter tests with `1` failure and `13` errors in `tests/src/org.codehaus.jackson/jackson-mapper-asl/1.8.3/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`. Concrete native failures include `CollectionDeserializerTest` (`No default constructor found for container class java.util.LinkedList`), `OptionalHandlerFactoryTest` (`actual not to be null`), plus additional errors involving `LinkedHashMap`, `GregorianCalendar`, `QName`, `AtomicBooleanSerializer`, `AtomicReferenceSerializer`, `EnumMap`, and `EnumSet`. The run metrics also ended in failure after 31 iterations and did not finalize cleanly (`stats/org.codehaus.jackson/jackson-mapper-asl/1.8.3/execution-metrics.json` reports `generated_loc: 0` and `artifacts: None`).\\n\\nThe generated tests also appear incomplete: `tests/src/org.codehaus.jackson/jackson-mapper-asl/1.8.3/src/test/java/org_codehaus_jackson/jackson_mapper_asl/Jackson_mapper_aslTest.java` is still the placeholder scaffold (`This is just a placeholder, implement your test`). Maintainers should inspect `logs/org.codehaus.jackson:jackson-mapper-asl:1.8.3/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T00-38-22-322333Z.log`, `logs/org.codehaus.jackson:jackson-mapper-asl:1.8.3/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T00-41-34-305806Z.log`, `tests/src/org.codehaus.jackson/jackson-mapper-asl/1.8.3/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`, and `tests/src/org.codehaus.jackson/jackson-mapper-asl/1.8.3/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`.\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Replace or remove the remaining scaffold `Jackson_mapper_aslTest` and review the generated suite for library-specific native-safe tests only.\\n2. Triage the native failures in `TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` and either add the missing metadata for the failing JDK/Jackson paths or narrow tests that are not valid under native image.\\n3. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.codehaus.jackson:jackson-mapper-asl:1.8.3` from the preserved branch once the native test suite is corrected.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2862#issuecomment-4362426885\"}]}},{\"number\":2860,\"title\":\"Support for org.jboss:jboss-common-core:2.0.5.GA\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2860\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:42:31Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T19:59:04Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.jboss:jboss-common-core:2.0.5.GA\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[{\"login\":\"kimeta\"}]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T19:59:02Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe workflow succeeded, but dynamic-access coverage is still missing: stats report 0/79 covered calls (0/69 reflection, 0/10 resources). The generated tests only exercise straightforward utility paths such as JBossStringBuilder, Heap, Graph, Base64 byte encode/decode, and file copy/delete helpers. They do not reach the dynamic-access sites captured for this library, including XML catalog/resource loading, property editors, class-loading helpers, marshalled stream resolution, URL protocol handlers, and RMI multi-socket proxy/method reflection paths. The committed metadata only contains conditional reflection entries for JBoss logging plugins, so it does not appear to address the org.jboss:jboss-common-core dynamic-access surface.\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Add targeted tests for the dynamic paths listed in the native dynamic-access call data, especially XML catalog/resource resolution, PropertyMap/PropertyEditors, Classes/MethodHashing, MarshalledValueInputStream, and URL/RMI helper flows.\\n2. Re-run metadata generation after those tests exercise the dynamic paths, then verify the dynamic-access coverage report improves from 0/79.\\n3. Review whether the logger-only metadata is actually needed for this artifact or whether additional jboss-common-core-specific metadata should be added.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2860#issuecomment-4361337909\"}]}},{\"number\":2861,\"title\":\"Support for javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2861\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:42:31Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-02T01:00:41Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\njavax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T01:00:35Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job for `javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0` failed. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2861-library-new-request-javax.servlet-jsp-api-2.0-8b9306c8\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was test generation / dynamic-access coverage improvement, not basic test execution. The preserved run added `SimpleTagSupportTest` and `TagSupportTest`, and the JVM/native test result XML under `tests/src/javax.servlet/jsp-api/2.0/build/test-results/` shows those tests passed, but `tests/src/javax.servlet/jsp-api/2.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` still reports `0/2` covered calls for `javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.SimpleTagSupport.class$(SimpleTagSupport.java:183)` and `javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.TagSupport.class$(TagSupport.java:80)`. The run metrics also ended in failure with `generated_loc: 0`, `metadata_entries: 0`, and `test_file` / `metadata_file` still `None` in `stats/javax.servlet/jsp-api/2.0/execution-metrics.json`, which matches the `test_generation_failed` workflow status.\\n\\nThere is also an upstream-context gap that likely hurt generation: both generation logs say the main sources were unavailable (`URL: N/A` / `no URL in index.json`), and artifact discovery left `source-code-url`, `repository-url`, and `test-code-url` as `N/A` for this coordinate. Please inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T00-43-25-132367Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T00-52-14-878334Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/javax.servlet:jsp-api:2.0/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Review the preserved tests on the branch, especially `tests/src/javax.servlet/jsp-api/2.0/src/test/java/javax_servlet/jsp_api/SimpleTagSupportTest.java` and `TagSupportTest.java`, and decide whether the synthetic `class$` call sites are realistically coverable for this library.\\n2. Fill in any recoverable upstream metadata for `metadata/javax.servlet/jsp-api/index.json` so future runs are not operating with `source-code-url` / `repository-url` / `test-code-url` set to `N/A`.\\n3. Either replace the current tests with a library-specific approach that actually exercises those two `Class.forName` paths, or document that these call sites are not practically coverable and handle the coordinate manually.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2861#issuecomment-4362468914\"}]}},{\"number\":2858,\"title\":\"Support for javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2858\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:42:30Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T22:06:34Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\njavassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T21:36:57Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job for `javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA` failed during test generation/review, even though the workflow completed and metrics were produced. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2858-library-new-request-javassist-javassist-3.12.0.GA-d4ec2b2d\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is `add-new-library-support`, not Gradle validation. In `human-intervention-logs/javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T20-56-58-918845Z.log`, the generator adds `tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/src/test/java/javassist_javassist/RuntimeSupportInnerDefaultMethodHandlerTest.java` specifically to cover `javassist.util.proxy.RuntimeSupport$DefaultMethodHandler.invoke()` / `Method#invoke(...)`, but the preserved test now disables itself under native image via `assumeFalse(NativeImageConditions.isNativeImageRuntime())`. The preserved branch also adds `tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/src/test/java/javassist_javassist/NativeImageConditions.java`, and there are 8 native-image skip sites across the generated tests, so the suite is not acceptable native-image coverage for a new-library request. Metrics still show `93/105` dynamic-access coverage (`88.57%`) in `stats/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/stats.json`, which suggests the blocker is test quality rather than missing metadata generation. For reference, `human-intervention-logs/javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA/checkstyle/pi-checkstyle-2026-04-28T21-22-53-179914Z.log` reports `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`, so style was not the failure.\\n\\nRelevant paths to inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T20-56-58-918845Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T21-00-10-395357Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA/checkstyle/pi-checkstyle-2026-04-28T21-22-53-179914Z.log`\\n- `tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/src/test/java/javassist_javassist/RuntimeSupportInnerDefaultMethodHandlerTest.java`\\n- `tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/src/test/java/javassist_javassist/NativeImageConditions.java`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Remove or rewrite the generated tests that call `NativeImageConditions.isNativeImageRuntime()`, especially `RuntimeSupportInnerDefaultMethodHandlerTest`, so the targeted behavior actually runs under native image.\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA` and `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA`.\\n3. If the preserved branch still looks useful after that cleanup, continue from it and open a manual PR.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2858#issuecomment-4339264462\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T22:06:27Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job for `javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA` failed. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2858-library-new-request-javassist-javassist-3.12.0.GA-4653b8b0\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was test generation / validation rather than coverage collection. Metrics still ended in `failure` after 43 iterations and 2410 generated LOC, even though dynamic-access coverage reached `102/105 (97.14%)`. The generation logs show multiple unresolved generated-test problems: `logs/javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T21-11-31-685957Z.log` has `:compileTestJava FAILED` in `FactoryHelperTest` (`String cannot be converted to CtClass`), `logs/javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T20-55-44-991233Z.log` has `SecurityActionsTest` failing with `javassist.CannotCompileException: no such class: javassist.util.proxy.SecurityActions`, and earlier generation logs include native missing-registration failures. The last preserved generation attempt, `logs/javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T21-32-34-992805Z.log`, only adds `SecurityActionsAnonymous6Test` and explicitly says tests were not run, so the job never reached a final green verification pass.\\n\\nThe preserved follow-up in `logs/javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA/metadata-fix/codex.log` is the best hint for manual recovery: it reproduces the remaining native issue under `future-defaults-all`, shows repeated `ServiceConfigurationError` lines for JDI connectors, then updates metadata for the `Viewer` resource and JDI connector reflection and adjusts `HotSwapperTest` for native `no Connectors loaded`; that reproducer finishes with `42 tests successful, 0 failed`.\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Review the preserved branch and compare it against `logs/javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA/metadata-fix/codex.log`, especially the `HotSwapperTest` and `SecurityActions*` changes.\\n2. Re-run `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=javassist:javassist:3.12.0.GA` and confirm the JDI connector path is handled correctly.\\n3. If that passes, clean up the final diff and resume the issue with the preserved branch as the starting point.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2858#issuecomment-4361862797\"}]}},{\"number\":2842,\"title\":\"Support for jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2842\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:42:20Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T22:32:19Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\njspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T23:39:21Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2842-library-new-request-jspapi-jsp-api-2.0-20040521-a2f48c56\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was `add-new-library-support` / dynamic-access test generation, not artifact discovery. `discover-artifact-metadata` and `populate-artifact-urls` both completed successfully and produced `N/A` URLs plus a description, but the generated test iterations never covered the two tracked reflection call sites. The final dynamic-access report still shows `0/2` covered calls for `javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.SimpleTagSupport.class$(SimpleTagSupport.java:183)` and `javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.TagSupport.class$(TagSupport.java:80)`, both mapping to `java.lang.Class#forName(java.lang.String)`. The generated tests did compile and pass on JVM/native-image, but they did not satisfy the coverage gate; the automation made multiple commits during generation and then reset back to the scaffold, so the preserved branch contains logs and `{}` metadata but no generated tests.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T23-25-16-214779Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T23-31-53-250786Z.log`\\n- `tests/src/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n- `tests/src/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/build/native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access/jsp-api-2.0-20040521/reflection-calls.json`\\n- `tests/src/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Recreate or recover the generated `SimpleTagSupport`/`TagSupport` tests from the add-new-library-support logs and verify whether the public API can actually trigger those legacy `class$` paths under tracking.\\n2. Rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521` and confirm whether dynamic-access coverage can be raised above `0/2`; if not, document why these call sites are not practically coverable.\\n3. Decide whether this legacy API-only artifact should keep `{}` metadata with stronger manual tests, or whether the coverage expectation for these `class$` call sites needs to be handled differently.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2842#issuecomment-4339859917\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T21:13:38Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2842-library-new-request-jspapi-jsp-api-2.0-20040521-0c244361\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is the dynamic-access coverage improvement step inside `add-new-library-support`, not artifact discovery or basic test execution. `stats/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/execution-metrics.json` shows `status: failure`, `iterations: 6`, `generated_loc: 0`, `test_file: None`, and `metadata_file: None`, and `tests/src/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` still reports `0/2` covered calls: `javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.SimpleTagSupport.class$(SimpleTagSupport.java:183)` and `javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.TagSupport.class$(TagSupport.java:80)`. The generated tests under `tests/src/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/src/test/java/jspapi/jsp_api/` do pass on JVM and native image (`tests/src/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/build/test-results/test/*.xml` and `tests/src/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` show 4 successful native tests), so the issue appears to be that the tests do not actually execute the tracked `Class.forName(String)` sites at runtime.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `logs/jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T20-57-28-146674Z.log`\\n- `logs/jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T21-04-39-458642Z.log`\\n- `logs/jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n- `logs/jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Review and replace/refine `TagSupportTest.java` and `SimpleTagSupportTest.java` so native execution really hits the legacy `findAncestorWithClass` `class$` lookups at `TagSupport.java:80` and `SimpleTagSupport.java:183`.\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521` and confirm `tests/src/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` improves from `0/2`.\\n3. If those call sites cannot be exercised at runtime because they are folded away during native-image build, document that explicitly and decide whether this library should stay with `{}` metadata or be handled with a different manual test strategy.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2842#issuecomment-4361673590\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T21:40:45Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job for `jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521` failed. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2842-library-new-request-jspapi-jsp-api-2.0-20040521-55d4b55e\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was `add-new-library-support` / test generation, not artifact discovery or URL population. Both `human-intervention-logs/jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` and `human-intervention-logs/jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` completed successfully, but `stats/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/execution-metrics.json` still reports `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, `artifacts.test_file: None`, `artifacts.metadata_file: None`, and the run never advanced past `starting_commit == ending_commit == 6e5dac38d1c4cf04b00b899893db98770ab1e9d5`.\\n\\nThe preserved branch does contain attempted follow-up work (`tests/src/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/src/test/java/jspapi/jsp_api/SimpleTagSupportTest.java`, `TagSupportTest.java`, and empty metadata `{}`), and those JVM/native test runs succeeded (`build/tests/jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521/ec662465264d6b1b8e9ecb03661956ea.out` and `build/tests/jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521/f75e216594bd3f535829bbc2f2f715e7.out`). However, the dynamic-access report stayed at `0/2`: `tests/src/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` still shows both uncovered `Class.forName` call sites in `javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.SimpleTagSupport.class$(SimpleTagSupport.java:183)` and `javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.TagSupport.class$(TagSupport.java:80)`, matching `tests/src/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/build/native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access/jsp-api-2.0-20040521/reflection-calls.json`. The scaffold placeholder `tests/src/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/src/test/java/jspapi/jsp_api/Jsp_apiTest.java` also still contains `This is just a placeholder, implement your test`.\\n\\nPlease inspect these paths first:\\n`human-intervention-logs/jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T21-23-10-339902Z.log`\\n`human-intervention-logs/jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T21-31-55-045133Z.log`\\n`tests/src/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n`build/tests/jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521/f75e216594bd3f535829bbc2f2f715e7.out`\\n\\n1. Replace or remove the scaffold `Jsp_apiTest.java` and rework `SimpleTagSupportTest.java` / `TagSupportTest.java` so they actually execute the old `class$` helper branches that invoke `Class.forName`.\\n2. Re-run targeted validation for `jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521` and confirm `dynamic-access-coverage.json` improves from `0/2` before keeping this as a new-library addition.\\n3. If those call sites cannot be exercised through supported public API behavior, decide whether to keep only `{}` metadata with stronger non-placeholder tests or close this library request as not suitable for this workflow.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2842#issuecomment-4361774537\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T22:32:14Z\",\"body\":\"### Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job for `jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521` failed. Preserved work is available on https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2842-library-new-request-jspapi-jsp-api-2.0-20040521-41038b71.\\n\\nThe most likely failure point was the handoff from generated test work to recorded metrics, not raw Gradle execution. The preserved branch contains partial generated work (`SimpleTagSupportTest`, `TagSupportTest`, and `{}` metadata), and the preserved Gradle outputs show `jacocoTestReport`, `generateDynamicAccessReport`, `nativeTest`, and JVM/native test runs finishing successfully. However, `stats/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/execution-metrics.json` still records `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, `test_file: None`, and `metadata_file: None`, and the run-level report still ended at dynamic-access coverage `0/2 (0.00%)`. The preserved native test output also shows the scaffold placeholder still running (`Jsp_apiTest` prints “This is just a placeholder, implement your test”), so the generated work was not fully normalized before the pipeline stopped.\\n\\nA contributing factor is missing upstream source metadata. Both generation sessions start with `Main sources: unavailable (no URL in index.json)`, `metadata/jspapi/jsp-api/index.json` still has `N/A` URLs, `human-intervention-logs/jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` shows `svn: command not found`, and `human-intervention-logs/jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` shows 404s for the `-tests.jar` and `-javadoc.jar` artifacts. The main files to inspect are `human-intervention-logs/jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T22-13-24-861211Z.log`, `human-intervention-logs/jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T22-22-41-763690Z.log`, `human-intervention-logs/jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`, `human-intervention-logs/jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`, and `build/tests/jspapi:jsp-api:2.0-20040521/c55be891f2eb10c3c8aacd6eed52db1f.out`.\\n\\nNext steps:\\n- Review the preserved branch, remove or replace the scaffold `tests/src/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/src/test/java/jspapi/jsp_api/Jsp_apiTest.java`, and validate whether `SimpleTagSupportTest` and `TagSupportTest` are the right long-term tests.\\n- Re-run the library’s dynamic-access/stats generation on the preserved branch and confirm whether the two `Class.forName(...)` sites in `SimpleTagSupport` and `TagSupport` are actually counted as covered and whether `stats/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/stats.json` is produced.\\n- If coverage still stays at `0/2`, adjust the tests to hit the intended public API path or decide explicitly that `{}` metadata is sufficient and close out the issue with manual justification.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2842#issuecomment-4361947083\"}]}},{\"number\":2843,\"title\":\"Support for servletapi:servletapi:2.4-20040521\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2843\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:42:20Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T20:51:23Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nservletapi:servletapi:2.4-20040521\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T22:00:19Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `servletapi:servletapi:2.4-20040521` with `test_generation_failed`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2843-library-new-request-servletapi-servletapi-2.4-20040521-1893b4f1\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was the handoff into scaffold/test generation, not artifact discovery itself. `human-intervention-logs/servletapi:servletapi:2.4-20040521/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` and `build/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/servletapi-servletapi-2.4-20040521.log` show `discoverArtifactMetadata` completed with `BUILD SUCCESSFUL` and `EXIT_CODE: 0`, and it produced `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/servletapi-servletapi-2.4-20040521.json`. That discovery output only contains a description plus `N/A` for `source-code-url`, `repository-url`, `test-code-url`, and `documentation-url`, and the same logs also contain `ERROR codex_core::session: failed to record rollout items: thread 019dd615-8cdc-79a3-952a-ad411484f9f9 not found`.\\n\\nThere is no generated test or metadata output for this coordinate after discovery: no `tests/src/servletapi/servletapi/2.4-20040521/`, no `metadata/servletapi/servletapi/2.4-20040521/`, and no `stats/servletapi/servletapi/2.4-20040521/stats.json`, so metrics and dynamic-access coverage are unavailable.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/servletapi:servletapi:2.4-20040521/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n- `build/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/servletapi-servletapi-2.4-20040521.log`\\n- `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/servletapi-servletapi-2.4-20040521.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. From the preserved branch, manually scaffold `metadata/servletapi/servletapi/2.4-20040521/` and `tests/src/servletapi/servletapi/2.4-20040521/`, likely by adapting the existing servlet API coverage in `tests/src/org.mortbay.jetty/servlet-api/2.5-20081211/`.\\n2. Verify or replace the discovered artifact URLs/description if better exact-version sources can be found, then run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=servletapi:servletapi:2.4-20040521`.\\n3. Once the tests exist, generate stats for the coordinate so coverage can be reviewed.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2843#issuecomment-4339395454\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T20:51:17Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `servletapi:servletapi:2.4-20040521` with workflow status `failure`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2843-library-new-request-servletapi-servletapi-2.4-20040521-e3bc8dd8\\n\\nThe most likely failure point was test generation after artifact discovery completed. In `human-intervention-logs/servletapi:servletapi:2.4-20040521/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`, the discovery step found that Maven Central only exposes the main JAR and POM for this coordinate and returned 404s for the version-matched `-sources.jar`, `-tests.jar`, and `-javadoc.jar`; the generated `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/servletapi-servletapi-2.4-20040521.json` therefore ended up with `\\\"source-code-url\\\": \\\"N/A\\\"` and `\\\"test-code-url\\\": \\\"N/A\\\"`. No generated library files were produced for this coordinate (`metadata/servletapi/servletapi/index.json`, `tests/src/servletapi/servletapi/2.4-20040521`, and `stats/servletapi/servletapi/2.4-20040521` are all absent), and run metrics are unavailable, which suggests the workflow stopped before it could synthesize tests or metadata from usable source context.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/servletapi:servletapi:2.4-20040521/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n- `build/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/servletapi-servletapi-2.4-20040521.log`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n- Find a trustworthy version-specific source or test reference for Servlet 2.4, or decide to hand-author tests directly from the API/spec and binary JAR.\\n- Use existing servlet API support in this repo, such as `org.mortbay.jetty:servlet-api:2.5-20081211` or `javax.servlet:javax.servlet-api:3.1.0`, as a baseline for manual test and metadata creation.\\n- Re-run the `library-new-request` flow after adding usable source/test context or manual scaffolding.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2843#issuecomment-4361583338\"}]}},{\"number\":2840,\"title\":\"Support for org.osgi:osgi_R4_core:1.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2840\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:42:18Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T21:16:09Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.osgi:osgi_R4_core:1.0\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T21:16:03Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job failed for `org.osgi:osgi_R4_core:1.0`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2840-library-new-request-org.osgi-osgi_R4_core-1.0-58ac883b\\n\\nThe most likely failure point is the dynamic-access test generation/finalization stage, not artifact discovery or basic Gradle/native-image execution. `logs/org.osgi:osgi_R4_core:1.0/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` completed successfully, and `build/tests/org.osgi:osgi_R4_core:1.0/2e00178844ead5b3c4eef8955096b57c.out` shows `nativeTest` success. However, `stats/org.osgi/osgi_R4_core/1.0/execution-metrics.json` still records `status: failure`, `iterations: 5`, `generated_loc: 0`, and no finalized `test_file`/`metadata_file`, while `tests/src/org.osgi/osgi_R4_core/1.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` stops at 11/12 covered calls. The only remaining uncovered site is `java.lang.Class#forName(String)` from `org.osgi.framework.AdminPermission.class$(AdminPermission.java:156)`. The generator logs show repeated attempts to cover that site and later successful additions for `FrameworkUtil$1` and `BundleSignerCondition$1`, but the run never finalized the last `AdminPermission` site. The generated suite also still contains the scaffold placeholder `tests/src/org.osgi/osgi_R4_core/1.0/src/test/java/org_osgi/osgi_R4_core/Osgi_R4_coreTest.java`, and the native test output still prints `This is just a placeholder, implement your test`.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `logs/org.osgi:osgi_R4_core:1.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T20-59-39-461833Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.osgi:osgi_R4_core:1.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T21-08-52-164929Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.osgi:osgi_R4_core:1.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T21-12-26-784400Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.osgi:osgi_R4_core:1.0/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n- `tests/src/org.osgi/osgi_R4_core/1.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n- `stats/org.osgi/osgi_R4_core/1.0/execution-metrics.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Reproduce from the preserved branch and focus on why `AdminPermissionTest.syntheticClassAccessorResolvesNamedClass()` succeeds but does not register coverage for `AdminPermission.class$(...)` in the dynamic-access report.\\n2. Replace or remove the scaffold-only `Osgi_R4_coreTest` so the final suite is fully library-specific.\\n3. After the remaining `AdminPermission` call is covered and the scaffold is cleaned up, regenerate the final `stats.json`/artifacts and rerun the `library-new-request` workflow.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2840#issuecomment-4361683288\"}]}},{\"number\":2839,\"title\":\"Support for javax.ws.rs:jsr311-api:1.1.1\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2839\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:42:18Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T21:07:38Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\njavax.ws.rs:jsr311-api:1.1.1\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T20:08:56Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed and ended in `test_generation_failed`, but the preserved work looks salvageable: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2839-library-new-request-javax.ws.rs-jsr311-api-1.1.1-36a4f5ba\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was the initial `add-new-library-support` test-generation pass, not metadata discovery or final library validation. In `logs/javax.ws.rs:jsr311-api:1.1.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T19-42-57-576125Z.log`, the first pass immediately drifted into reading `README.md` and a missing `DEVELOPING.md` instead of producing the required test update. A later recovery pass and metadata-fix flow did produce usable output: `logs/javax.ws.rs:jsr311-api:1.1.1/metadata-fix/codex.log` shows `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=javax.ws.rs:jsr311-api:1.1.1 --stacktrace` finishing with `BUILD SUCCESSFUL` and `Test for javax.ws.rs:jsr311-api:1.1.1 passed`, and `stats/javax.ws.rs/jsr311-api/1.1.1/stats.json` reports dynamic-access coverage `8/8 (100.00%)`. That same metadata-fix log ends with `failed to record rollout items: thread ... not found`, so the pipeline may have failed to recognize the repaired result after generation completed.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `logs/javax.ws.rs:jsr311-api:1.1.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T19-42-57-576125Z.log`\\n- `logs/javax.ws.rs:jsr311-api:1.1.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T19-47-36-396541Z.log`\\n- `logs/javax.ws.rs:jsr311-api:1.1.1/metadata-fix/codex.log`\\n- `logs/javax.ws.rs:jsr311-api:1.1.1/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n- `logs/javax.ws.rs:jsr311-api:1.1.1/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Review the preserved branch and confirm the generated `FactoryFinderTest`, `RuntimeDelegateTest`, and `reachability-metadata.json` are acceptable to keep.\\n2. If the patch looks correct, reuse the preserved branch state and rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=javax.ws.rs:jsr311-api:1.1.1 --stacktrace`.\\n3. If automation still reports failure, investigate the rollout-recording error in `logs/javax.ws.rs:jsr311-api:1.1.1/metadata-fix/codex.log` before retrying generation.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2839#issuecomment-4338685716\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T21:07:32Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `javax.ws.rs:jsr311-api:1.1.1`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2839-library-new-request-javax.ws.rs-jsr311-api-1.1.1-d04bea86\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is native test verification after the second generation pass added `RuntimeDelegateTest`. The earlier native trace run in `human-intervention-logs/javax.ws.rs:jsr311-api:1.1.1/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-01T21-00-59-611297Z.log` finished with 4/4 tests successful, but the later run in `human-intervention-logs/javax.ws.rs:jsr311-api:1.1.1/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-01T21-04-19-953086Z.log` shows `javax_ws_rs.jsr311_api.RuntimeDelegateTest > reportsProviderClassResourceLocationsWhenProviderHasWrongType() FAILED` with `java.lang.AssertionError: Expecting code to raise a throwable.` at `RuntimeDelegateTest.java:45`. The same failure is recorded in `tests/src/javax.ws.rs/jsr311-api/1.1.1/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`, and Gradle output in `build/tests/javax.ws.rs:jsr311-api:1.1.1/ae942a6bad39546aacb7643d7ee7df7c.out` shows `:nativeTest FAILED`.\\n\\nCoverage itself looks good: `tests/src/javax.ws.rs/jsr311-api/1.1.1/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` reports `8/8` covered calls, and the generated changes from `1aff1c3d52d2240313b061528dbd4eb938b3c70b` to `11205d81e51ac424a547d36b60eab690e5e0d6e0` added `FactoryFinderTest`, `RuntimeDelegateTest`, service resources, and test reachability metadata. However, the generation logs in `human-intervention-logs/javax.ws.rs:jsr311-api:1.1.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T20-59-40-946833Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/javax.ws.rs:jsr311-api:1.1.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T21-03-21-551556Z.log` show this was built in two passes, `tests/src/javax.ws.rs/jsr311-api/1.1.1/src/test/java/javax_ws_rs/jsr311_api/Jsr311_apiTest.java` is still the scaffold placeholder, and `stats/javax.ws.rs/jsr311-api/1.1.1/execution-metrics.json` still reports `generated_loc: 0` with `test_file: None` / `metadata_file: None`, so the metrics summary is inconsistent with the preserved changes.\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Fix or replace `RuntimeDelegateTest` so it asserts the actual native-image behavior of `RuntimeDelegate.getInstance()` instead of expecting an exception that is not thrown.\\n2. Replace or remove the remaining scaffold placeholder in `tests/src/javax.ws.rs/jsr311-api/1.1.1/src/test/java/javax_ws_rs/jsr311_api/Jsr311_apiTest.java`.\\n3. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=javax.ws.rs:jsr311-api:1.1.1` (or at least `javaTest`, `nativeTestCompile`, and `nativeTest`) and refresh the metrics/artifact summary once the test set is stable.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2839#issuecomment-4361649868\"}]}},{\"number\":2820,\"title\":\"Support for jakarta.json:jakarta.json-api:2.1.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2820\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:42:09Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-30T06:32:21Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\njakarta.json:jakarta.json-api:2.1.0\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T06:32:13Z\",\"body\":\"## Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `jakarta.json:jakarta.json-api:2.1.0`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2820-library-new-request-jakarta.json-jakarta.json-api-2.1.0-e1fd3644\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was post-generation artifact capture in `add-new-library-support`, not the Gradle test execution itself. In `human-intervention-logs/jakarta.json:jakarta.json-api:2.1.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T06-28-41-438891Z.log`, the agent created commit `45625303f43ec4dc90ae1fbf76eda77577f55145` adding `JsonProviderTest.java`, and the preserved test outputs show `BUILD SUCCESSFUL` for JVM tests, native compile, native test, and dynamic-access report generation in `build/tests/jakarta.json:jakarta.json-api:2.1.0/46b229172e1003724477ba72cc7be125.out`, `build/tests/jakarta.json:jakarta.json-api:2.1.0/a605fa336ef99d04442d5beeaa1b2f64.out`, and `build/tests/jakarta.json:jakarta.json-api:2.1.0/fba7518d08cc5fffeca1c07fd8ed09f2.out`. Dynamic-access coverage also reached `3/3 (100%)` in `tests/src/jakarta.json/jakarta.json-api/2.1.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`.\\n\\nHowever, `stats/jakarta.json/jakarta.json-api/2.1.0/execution-metrics.json` still records `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, and `test_file` / `metadata_file` as `None`, and the generation log notes that `metadata/jakarta.json/jakarta.json-api/2.1.0/` remained untracked and was not included in the commit. `human-intervention-logs/jakarta.json:jakarta.json-api:2.1.0/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` and `human-intervention-logs/jakarta.json:jakarta.json-api:2.1.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` both completed successfully, so artifact URL/metadata discovery does not appear to be the blocker.\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Check out the preserved branch and review/stage the untracked metadata files under `metadata/jakarta.json/jakarta.json-api/` together with the generated tests.\\n2. Review whether the leftover scaffold test `tests/src/jakarta.json/jakarta.json-api/2.1.0/src/test/java/jakarta_json/jakarta_json_api/Jakarta_json_apiTest.java` should be replaced or removed, then rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=jakarta.json:jakarta.json-api:2.1.0`.\\n3. If the content is valid, re-run or repair the metrics/artifact collection step so the run records the generated test/metadata files instead of reporting `generated_loc: 0`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2820#issuecomment-4350188986\"}]}},{\"number\":2817,\"title\":\"Support for jakarta.authentication:jakarta.authentication-api:3.0.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2817\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:42:08Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-30T06:55:53Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\njakarta.authentication:jakarta.authentication-api:3.0.0\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T06:55:46Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job for `jakarta.authentication:jakarta.authentication-api:3.0.0` failed with `test_generation_failed`. Preserved work is available on branch https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2817-library-new-request-jakarta.authentication-jakarta.authentication-api-3.0.0-468d6ef8.\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was the post-generation scaffold-placeholder quality gate, not downstream Gradle execution. The preserved branch contains commit `79a855967c8d6077c86567bdd1d61f1f29ddcd96`, which adds `tests/src/jakarta.authentication/jakarta.authentication-api/3.0.0/src/test/java/jakarta_authentication/jakarta_authentication_api/AuthConfigFactoryAnonymous1Test.java`, and the preserved Gradle output in `build/tests/jakarta.authentication:jakarta.authentication-api:3.0.0/c5fc3ace26d91c4f916f2e9fedf949b4.out` shows `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`, 2 passing tests, and 3/3 dynamic-access coverage was reported overall. However, `tests/src/jakarta.authentication/jakarta.authentication-api/3.0.0/src/test/java/jakarta_authentication/jakarta_authentication_api/Jakarta_authentication_apiTest.java` still contains the scaffold text `This is just a placeholder, implement your test`, and `stats/jakarta.authentication/jakarta.authentication-api/3.0.0/execution-metrics.json` still records `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, and `artifacts.test_file: None`.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/jakarta.authentication:jakarta.authentication-api:3.0.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T06-51-51-553484Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/jakarta.authentication:jakarta.authentication-api:3.0.0/c5fc3ace26d91c4f916f2e9fedf949b4.out`\\n- `stats/jakarta.authentication/jakarta.authentication-api/3.0.0/execution-metrics.json`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/jakarta.authentication:jakarta.authentication-api:3.0.0/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/jakarta.authentication:jakarta.authentication-api:3.0.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Remove or replace the scaffold placeholder test in `Jakarta_authentication_apiTest.java` so no placeholder text remains under the generated test sources.\\n2. Keep the dedicated `AuthConfigFactoryAnonymous1Test` from the preserved branch, then rerun the library test workflow for `jakarta.authentication:jakarta.authentication-api:3.0.0`.\\n3. If the rerun still fails, investigate why the metrics writer did not recognize the generated test artifact despite the successful preserved Gradle outputs.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2817#issuecomment-4350308029\"}]}},{\"number\":2803,\"title\":\"Support for com.querydsl:querydsl-core:5.0.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2803\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:42:04Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T22:44:07Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\ncom.querydsl:querydsl-core:5.0.0\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T19:03:46Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `com.querydsl:querydsl-core:5.0.0`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2803-library-new-request-com.querydsl-querydsl-core-5.0.0-c4869cef\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is native runtime validation after test generation, not dynamic-access generation itself. The metrics/report side completed with `46/46 (100.00%)` dynamic-access coverage, `nativeTestCompile` succeeded, and `generateDynamicAccessReport` succeeded (`build/tests/com.querydsl:querydsl-core:5.0.0/9038d4f0da0d9bbf1f5915d729aff1ad.out`, `tests/src/com.querydsl/querydsl-core/5.0.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`). However, `nativeTest` then failed with 4 runtime failures (`build/tests/com.querydsl:querydsl-core:5.0.0/1a8a42ab470ff8296c04a63bae757bd6.out`): `CollectionPathBaseTest.anyCreatesTypedPathWithMetadataOnlyConstructor`, `CollectionPathBaseTest.anyCreatesUntypedPathWithMetadataOnlyConstructor`, `MapPathTest.getWithExpressionKeyCreatesUntypedValuePath`, and `MapPathTest.getWithConstantKeyCreatesTypedValuePath`.\\n\\nAll 4 failures are `ExpressionException` wrappers around `NoSuchMethodException` for Querydsl constructors reached reflectively in native image, specifically `com.querydsl.core.types.dsl.SimplePath.<init>(java.lang.Class, com.querydsl.core.types.PathMetadata)` and `com.querydsl.core.types.dsl.StringPath.<init>(com.querydsl.core.types.PathMetadata)`. The generated coverage report shows those call sites were exercised (`CollectionPathBase` 8/8 and `MapPath` 4/4), so this looks like a real metadata gap rather than a missing-coverage gap. The current metadata file is still empty: `metadata/com.querydsl/querydsl-core/5.0.0/reachability-metadata.json` contains `{}`.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `build/tests/com.querydsl:querydsl-core:5.0.0/1a8a42ab470ff8296c04a63bae757bd6.out`\\n- `build/tests/com.querydsl:querydsl-core:5.0.0/9038d4f0da0d9bbf1f5915d729aff1ad.out`\\n- `tests/src/com.querydsl/querydsl-core/5.0.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.querydsl:querydsl-core:5.0.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T19-00-43-350873Z.log`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Add reachability metadata for the Querydsl constructors exercised by `CollectionPathBase` and `MapPath`, especially `SimplePath(Class, PathMetadata)` and `StringPath(PathMetadata)`.\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=com.querydsl:querydsl-core:5.0.0` and confirm `nativeTest` passes.\\n3. If those constructors are not intended to be supported in native image, revise the failing tests to exercise only supported public behavior.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2803#issuecomment-4338258422\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T22:44:01Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `com.querydsl:querydsl-core:5.0.0`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2803-library-new-request-com.querydsl-querydsl-core-5.0.0-2e1c39ca\\n\\nMost likely the run failed in generated test stabilization / final artifact assembly rather than in coverage collection. The coverage report reached `46/46 (100.00%)`, but `stats/com.querydsl/querydsl-core/5.0.0/execution-metrics.json` still records `status: failure`, `iterations: 14`, `generated_loc: 0`, `metadata_entries: 0`, and `artifacts.test_file: None` / `artifacts.metadata_file: None`. The recorded ending commit `7551ca27a70c159295ac127eda1bdde9b9f14e91` contains only test-side changes and does not include `metadata/com.querydsl/querydsl-core/5.0.0/reachability-metadata.json`, so the automation did not finish a complete new-library support diff.\\n\\nThere is also concrete Gradle failure evidence in `logs/com.querydsl:querydsl-core:5.0.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T22-15-34-360777Z.log`: `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=com.querydsl:querydsl-core:5.0.0` fails in `ConstructorExpressionTest.deserializedExpressionRestoresTransientConstructorState()` with a `NullPointerException` from `com.querydsl.core.types.ToStringVisitor.visit(...)` while asserting `restored.getType()` at `tests/src/com.querydsl/querydsl-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/com_querydsl/querydsl_core/ConstructorExpressionTest.java:46`. The generated suite also still contains a scaffold placeholder test at `tests/src/com.querydsl/querydsl-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/com_querydsl/querydsl_core/Querydsl_coreTest.java`.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `logs/com.querydsl:querydsl-core:5.0.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T22-15-34-360777Z.log`\\n- `logs/com.querydsl:querydsl-core:5.0.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T22-40-43-848297Z.log`\\n- `stats/com.querydsl/querydsl-core/5.0.0/execution-metrics.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Fix or replace the failing generated `ConstructorExpressionTest` assertion and remove the remaining scaffold placeholder test.\\n2. Ensure `metadata/com.querydsl/querydsl-core/5.0.0/reachability-metadata.json` is actually included in the preserved branch/commit together with the generated tests.\\n3. Re-run metadata validation and `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=com.querydsl:querydsl-core:5.0.0`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2803#issuecomment-4362009946\"}]}},{\"number\":2755,\"title\":\"Support for com.google.auto.value:auto-value:1.4.1\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2755\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:41:54Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T18:49:35Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\ncom.google.auto.value:auto-value:1.4.1\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T18:49:28Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `com.google.auto.value:auto-value:1.4.1`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: [ai/vjovanov/human-intervention/issue-2755-library-new-request-com.google.auto.value-auto-value-1.4.1-a7d0eeae](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2755-library-new-request-com.google.auto.value-auto-value-1.4.1-a7d0eeae)\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is native test validation, not dynamic-access generation. The preserved run reached full dynamic-access coverage (`71/71`, 100%) in `tests/src/com.google.auto.value/auto-value/1.4.1/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`, but `build/tests/com.google.auto.value:auto-value:1.4.1/943a41d3d566cb7889bd8c88a07dfc05.out` ends with `Execution failed for task ':nativeTest'`, and `tests/src/com.google.auto.value/auto-value/1.4.1/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` records 15 native-image test errors.\\n\\nThe concrete failures cluster in two areas: serialization-focused generated tests are hitting `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` and deserialization errors such as `ClassNotFoundException` for shaded types like `$HashMultimap` / `$Multimaps$CustomListMultimap` and `InvalidClassException` for `LinkedHashMap` / `$MapMakerInternalMap`; compiler-based tests are also not native-safe, with `TemplateVarsTest` failing on `NoClassDefFoundError: Could not initialize class com.sun.tools.javac.file.Locations` and `AutovalueShadedComGoogleInnerAutoCommonInnerMoreTypesTest` failing with `ExceptionInInitializerError` from the same `javac` path. The preserved suite also still contains the scaffold placeholder `Auto_valueTest`.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `logs/com.google.auto.value:auto-value:1.4.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T18-46-03-068313Z.log`\\n- `logs/com.google.auto.value:auto-value:1.4.1/failure-analysis/codex_failure_analysis_issue_2755.log`\\n- `build/tests/com.google.auto.value:auto-value:1.4.1/943a41d3d566cb7889bd8c88a07dfc05.out`\\n- `tests/src/com.google.auto.value/auto-value/1.4.1/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Replace or remove the scaffold `Auto_valueTest`, and trim the preserved suite to tests that exercise real AutoValue behavior and can run under native image.\\n2. Rework the serialization tests and test-only metadata so the shaded deserialization paths pass under native image instead of failing with missing reflection/class registration errors.\\n3. Revisit `TemplateVarsTest` and `AutovalueShadedComGoogleInnerAutoCommonInnerMoreTypesTest`; they currently depend on `javac` internals that are failing in the native lane, so they likely need a different testing approach or to be dropped from the native-covered set.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2755#issuecomment-4361031524\"}]}},{\"number\":2750,\"title\":\"Support for com.ethlo.time:itu:1.10.3\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2750\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:41:53Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-30T05:20:45Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\ncom.ethlo.time:itu:1.10.3\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"jormundur00\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T05:20:38Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job for `com.ethlo.time:itu:1.10.3` failed. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fjormundur00%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2750-library-new-request-com.ethlo.time-itu-1.10.3-15c6127a\\n\\nMost likely failure stage: native test execution of the generated test, not artifact discovery. The preserved commit `0ea7aee2d` added `tests/src/com.ethlo.time/itu/1.10.3/src/test/java/com_ethlo_time/itu/DefaultLeapSecondHandlerTest.java`, and the generated dynamic-access artifact confirms the intended call site was reached (`ClassLoader#getResourceAsStream(...)` in `DefaultLeapSecondHandler.<init>`). However, `build/tests/com.ethlo.time:itu:1.10.3/d1863b06ac5db0d237edaabbbb955c68.out` shows `com_ethlo_time.itu.DefaultLeapSecondHandlerTest > loadsLeapSecondMonthsFromBundledResource() FAILED` with `java.lang.NullPointerException: leap_second_dates.csv was not found on the classpath` at `DefaultLeapSecondHandlerTest.java:19`. The scaffold `ItuTest` also remains and still prints the placeholder message. Separately, `stats/com.ethlo.time/itu/1.10.3/execution-metrics.json` reports `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, and `artifacts.test_file: None` / `metadata_file: None` even though the preserved branch contains generated test changes, so there may also be a metrics/accounting mismatch after the failed run.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.ethlo.time:itu:1.10.3/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T05-15-56-092240Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/com.ethlo.time:itu:1.10.3/d1863b06ac5db0d237edaabbbb955c68.out`\\n- `stats/com.ethlo.time/itu/1.10.3/execution-metrics.json`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.ethlo.time:itu:1.10.3/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.ethlo.time:itu:1.10.3/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Replace the scaffold test with a library-specific test that exercises ITU through a path that works under native image, or explicitly include the `leap_second_dates.csv` resource if that internal-path test is kept.\\n2. Re-run the single-library lane for `com.ethlo.time:itu:1.10.3` and confirm the native test passes, not just dynamic-access coverage.\\n3. Verify the rerun records the generated test artifact correctly in `stats/com.ethlo.time/itu/1.10.3/execution-metrics.json`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2750#issuecomment-4349895153\"}]}},{\"number\":2746,\"title\":\"Support for net.sf.jopt-simple:jopt-simple:5.0.4\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2746\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:41:52Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T19:03:39Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nnet.sf.jopt-simple:jopt-simple:5.0.4\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T19:03:33Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job for `net.sf.jopt-simple:jopt-simple:5.0.4` failed. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2746-library-new-request-net.sf.jopt-simple-jopt-simple-5.0.4-40ac5a6b\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is native test execution after generation, not artifact discovery. The preserved branch contains generated follow-up commits up to `f838c276dcbc308a337bed4fd01c5b8d4dc48c46`, and `tests/src/net.sf.jopt-simple/jopt-simple/5.0.4/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` shows `6/6` covered calls, but `build/tests/net.sf.jopt-simple:jopt-simple:5.0.4/a7f6fe7f2b0b605cfd6b1b3cc531083c.out` ends with `> Task :nativeTest FAILED`. The concrete failures are in `tests/src/net.sf.jopt-simple/jopt-simple/5.0.4/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`: `JoptsimpleInternalReflectionTest` fails twice with `java.lang.IllegalArgumentException` (`class java.lang.Integer is not a value type` and `class java.io.File is not a value type`) from `joptsimple.internal.Reflection.findConverter(Reflection.java:66)` via `ArgumentAcceptingOptionSpec.ofType(...)`. The generated test tree also still contains a scaffold placeholder: `tests/src/net.sf.jopt-simple/jopt-simple/5.0.4/build/test-results/test/TEST-net_sf_jopt_simple.jopt_simple.Jopt_simpleTest.xml` prints `This is just a placeholder, implement your test`. Metrics also look inconsistent: `stats/net.sf.jopt-simple/jopt-simple/5.0.4/execution-metrics.json` reports failure with `generated_loc: 0` and no artifacts even though the preserved branch contains generated test commits.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/net.sf.jopt-simple:jopt-simple:5.0.4/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T18-54-16-000902Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/net.sf.jopt-simple:jopt-simple:5.0.4/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T18-57-21-448004Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/net.sf.jopt-simple:jopt-simple:5.0.4/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T19-00-23-613875Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/net.sf.jopt-simple:jopt-simple:5.0.4/a7f6fe7f2b0b605cfd6b1b3cc531083c.out`\\n- `tests/src/net.sf.jopt-simple/jopt-simple/5.0.4/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/net.sf.jopt-simple:jopt-simple:5.0.4/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/net.sf.jopt-simple:jopt-simple:5.0.4/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Fix or replace `JoptsimpleInternalReflectionTest` so it exercises native-compatible value conversion behavior, or add the necessary test-only metadata if that is the intended coverage path.\\n2. Remove the scaffold-only `Jopt_simpleTest` placeholder and replace it with a library-specific test or drop it.\\n3. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=net.sf.jopt-simple:jopt-simple:5.0.4` on the preserved branch and continue from there if native tests pass.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2746#issuecomment-4361095380\"}]}},{\"number\":2744,\"title\":\"Support for io.javaslang:javaslang:2.0.6\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2744\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:41:52Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-02T02:01:09Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nio.javaslang:javaslang:2.0.6\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[{\"login\":\"kimeta\"}]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T01:55:01Z\",\"body\":\"### Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `io.javaslang:javaslang:2.0.6`. Preserved work is available on https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2744-library-new-request-io.javaslang-javaslang-2.0.6-6094f1cf\\n\\nAlthough this run is tagged `test_generation_failed`, the preserved artifacts point to a later post-generation native-test/metadata-fix failure. Dynamic-access coverage was reported as `15/15 (100.00%)`, and `post-gen-interventions/io.javaslang_javaslang_2.0.6.md` records `Stage: metadata_fix_failed`. The native test report at `tests/src/io.javaslang/javaslang/2.0.6/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` shows 3 remaining errors: `HashSetInnerSerializationProxyTest`, `LinkedHashSetInnerSerializationProxyTest`, and `TreeInnerNodeInnerSerializationProxyTest`, all failing with `org.graalvm.nativeimage.MissingReflectionRegistrationError` for reflective invocation of `java.lang.Object.<init>()` from `java.io.ObjectStreamClass.newInstance` during serialization-proxy deserialization. `human-intervention-logs/io.javaslang:javaslang:2.0.6/metadata-fix/codex.log` shows repeated reruns of `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.javaslang:javaslang:2.0.6 --stacktrace` plus `generateMetadata`, `nativeTraceImage`, and `runNativeTraceImage`, but the missing constructor metadata remained unresolved. The main files to inspect are `post-gen-interventions/io.javaslang_javaslang_2.0.6.md`, `human-intervention-logs/io.javaslang:javaslang:2.0.6/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-05-02T01-52-31-351939Z.log`, `human-intervention-logs/io.javaslang:javaslang:2.0.6/metadata-fix/codex.log`, `human-intervention-logs/io.javaslang:javaslang:2.0.6/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T01-36-54-382805Z.log`, and `stats/io.javaslang/javaslang/2.0.6/execution-metrics.json`.\\n\\n1. Check out the preserved branch and reproduce `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.javaslang:javaslang:2.0.6 --stacktrace`, focusing on the three serialization-proxy tests above.\\n2. Determine the correct GraalVM metadata needed for JDK serialization allocation through `ObjectStreamClass.newInstance` for `HashSet$SerializationProxy`, `LinkedHashSet$SerializationProxy`, and `Tree$Node$SerializationProxy`; the existing `serializable`, `unsafeAllocated`, and explicit `java.lang.Object` constructor registrations were not sufficient.\\n3. Update the preserved branch with the fixed metadata and rerun the library test lane for `io.javaslang:javaslang:2.0.6`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2744#issuecomment-4362596260\"}]}},{\"number\":2738,\"title\":\"Support for args4j:args4j:2.0.26\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2738\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:41:50Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T21:30:57Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nargs4j:args4j:2.0.26\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T21:30:52Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `args4j:args4j:2.0.26`. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2738-library-new-request-args4j-args4j-2.0.26-659f7dd7\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was test generation / validation. `stats/args4j/args4j/2.0.26/execution-metrics.json` shows `status: failure` after 8 iterations, `generated_loc: 0`, `test_file: None`, `metadata_file: None`, and the starting and ending commit are both `088af233909763dd42ff4821f309bd63c387d9c4`, so the run never produced a finished patch. The preserved test tree is also incomplete: `tests/src/args4j/args4j/2.0.26/src/test/java/args4j/args4j/Args4jTest.java` is still the scaffold placeholder, and `tests/src/args4j/args4j/2.0.26/build/test-results/test/TEST-args4j.args4j.Args4jTest.xml` shows it only prints `This is just a placeholder, implement your test`.\\n\\nThere is also a concrete native-image runtime failure in the preserved output. `tests/src/args4j/args4j/2.0.26/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` shows `ExceptionInInitializerError` / `NoClassDefFoundError` for `org.kohsuke.args4j.CmdLineParser`, caused by `MissingResourceException: Can't find bundle for base name org.kohsuke.args4j.Messages, locale en_US`. That matches the empty metadata file at `metadata/args4j/args4j/2.0.26/reachability-metadata.json` (`{}`), even though the dynamic-access report reached 28/32 (87.50%).\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/args4j:args4j:2.0.26/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T21-10-12-699845Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/args4j:args4j:2.0.26/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T21-26-56-821774Z.log`\\n- `tests/src/args4j/args4j/2.0.26/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\\n- `stats/args4j/args4j/2.0.26/execution-metrics.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Replace the remaining scaffold in `Args4jTest.java` with a real library-specific test and review whether `AnnotationImplTest.java` is the right coverage target.\\n2. Add the missing native-image resource metadata for the `org.kohsuke.args4j.Messages` bundle, then rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=args4j:args4j:2.0.26`.\\n3. Recheck the dynamic-access report and confirm the final tests still cover the intended paths after the metadata fix.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2738#issuecomment-4361738263\"}]}},{\"number\":2735,\"title\":\"Support for org.mozilla:rhino:1.7R5\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2735\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:41:50Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T23:11:45Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.mozilla:rhino:1.7R5\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T21:34:31Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.mozilla:rhino:1.7R5`. Preserved work is available on the branch: `https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2735-library-new-request-org.mozilla-rhino-1.7R5-742617e9`.\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is native test validation rather than coverage collection. Dynamic-access coverage reached `119/125 (95.20%)`, but the native test run still fails in `build/tests/org.mozilla:rhino:1.7R5/3c7f88ddb9569368a24180fc68f884d8.out` with `Execution failed for task ':nativeTest'`. The concrete failure is `java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: java/awt/GraphicsEnvironment` from `org_mozilla.rhino.SwingGuiTest.appliesSplitPaneResizeWeightThroughDebuggerUtility()`, ending with `Fatal error reported via JNI: FindClass java/awt/GraphicsEnvironment failed`. The final preserved iteration then created commit `792e63ada` (`Fix Rhino SwingGui resize weight test`), but the last generation log explicitly says `I did not run tests`, so that change was never validated.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.mozilla:rhino:1.7R5/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T21-28-43-126959Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.mozilla:rhino:1.7R5/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T21-23-55-082745Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/org.mozilla:rhino:1.7R5/3c7f88ddb9569368a24180fc68f884d8.out`\\n- `tests/src/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Rework or validate the `SwingGuiTest` path so it does not depend on unavailable AWT classes under native image, then rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.mozilla:rhino:1.7R5`.\\n2. Review preserved commit `792e63ada` on the branch above and either keep it with a successful rerun or replace it with a safer native-compatible test.\\n3. If support continues, review the generated test resources under `tests/src/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/test/` for cleanup of legacy native-image config files.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2735#issuecomment-4339248549\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T23:11:39Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.mozilla:rhino:1.7R5`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2735-library-new-request-org.mozilla-rhino-1.7R5-b84be017\\n\\nAlthough this run was classified as `test_generation_failed`, the preserved artifacts suggest generation mostly completed and the likely hard failure was native test execution. `build/tests/org.mozilla:rhino:1.7R5/6b2b71a7410339afafb3b562c22b7ad3.out` shows `nativeTestCompile` and `generateDynamicAccessReport` completed successfully, and `tests/src/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` reports 111/125 covered calls (88.80%). The actual failing step appears in `build/tests/org.mozilla:rhino:1.7R5/257df64cc06356eb2f495d5fae5646e5.out`, where `:nativeTest` exits non-zero after 35 of 37 tests fail.\\n\\nThe native failures are dominated by `NoClassDefFoundError: Could not initialize class org.mozilla.javascript.VMBridge`, with additional `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` for reflective `java.lang.Object()` construction, `NoSuchMethodException` in `TypeInfoTest`, and `IllegalStateException` / `InstantiationException` around `JavaPolicySecurity` in `MainTest`. Please also inspect `human-intervention-logs/org.mozilla:rhino:1.7R5/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T23-00-51-598728Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/org.mozilla:rhino:1.7R5/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T23-05-27-862951Z.log`: the generator did update files there, but `stats/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/execution-metrics.json` still reports `generated_loc: 0` and `test_file` / `metadata_file` as `None`, so there is also a bookkeeping mismatch.\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Fix the native runtime failures on the preserved branch, starting with `VMBridge` initialization, missing reflection registrations for serialization paths, and the failing `TypeInfoTest` / `MainTest` cases.\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.mozilla:rhino:1.7R5` and confirm `:nativeTest` passes while keeping dynamic-access coverage at or above 111/125.\\n3. If the code is valid after that, investigate why the generator metrics did not record the produced files so this does not get misclassified as `test_generation_failed`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2735#issuecomment-4362087472\"}]}},{\"number\":2727,\"title\":\"Support for org.apache.commons:commons-math3:3.1.1\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2727\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:41:48Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T23:47:57Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.apache.commons:commons-math3:3.1.1\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T23:47:52Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.apache.commons:commons-math3:3.1.1`.\\n\\nPreserved work is available on the branch:\\nhttps://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2727-library-new-request-org.apache.commons-commons-math3-3.1.1-cee6927c\\n\\nMost likely failing stage: final native test validation / artifact handoff after generation. The preserved worktree does contain generated tests and reaches full dynamic-access coverage (`36/36` in `tests/src/org.apache.commons/commons-math3/3.1.1/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`), but the last full native test run still fails in `build/tests/org.apache.commons:commons-math3:3.1.1/3b2b1185c36e329729f7f0035e38e9cf.out` and `tests/src/org.apache.commons/commons-math3/3.1.1/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`:\\n- `ExceptionContextTest.serializesMessagesThrowableAndContextValues()` fails with `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` for reflective construction of `java.lang.Object()` during deserialization.\\n- `LocalizedFormatsTest.resolvesFrenchMessageFromResourceBundle()` fails because native image returns the English fallback string instead of the expected French localized message.\\n\\nA later run in `build/tests/org.apache.commons:commons-math3:3.1.1/806f493a1e6148742dd8346beba1aa68.out` succeeds only through `nativeTestCompile` and `generateDynamicAccessReport`; it does not show a clean passing `nativeTest`. The metrics file `stats/org.apache.commons/commons-math3/3.1.1/execution-metrics.json` also still records overall `status: failure` with `generated_loc: 0`, `test_file: None`, and `metadata_file: None`, which suggests the job never completed a clean final validation/metrics handoff.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.commons:commons-math3:3.1.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T23-44-47-420918Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/org.apache.commons:commons-math3:3.1.1/3b2b1185c36e329729f7f0035e38e9cf.out`\\n- `tests/src/org.apache.commons/commons-math3/3.1.1/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\\n- `stats/org.apache.commons/commons-math3/3.1.1/execution-metrics.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Check out the preserved branch and run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.commons:commons-math3:3.1.1` to reproduce the native failures.\\n2. Fix the two failing native cases: add/adjust the metadata needed for `ExceptionContext` deserialization and correct either the `LocalizedFormats` resource setup or the test expectation under native image.\\n3. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.commons:commons-math3:3.1.1` and refresh the metrics once the full test task is green.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2727#issuecomment-4362183741\"}]}},{\"number\":2717,\"title\":\"Support for org.mongodb:bson:4.11.1\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2717\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:41:47Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-02T00:27:05Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.mongodb:bson:4.11.1\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"jormundur00\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-29T00:30:34Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.mongodb:bson:4.11.1`. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fjormundur00%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2717-library-new-request-org.mongodb-bson-4.11.1-69770320\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was the post-generation handoff/metrics recording, not the scratch Gradle test run itself. In `human-intervention-logs/org.mongodb:bson:4.11.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T00-26-07-640116Z.log`, the final attempt created commit `3cc4d47a83bbee9fd04d5b013bee7a37ece12e89` and added `tests/src/org.mongodb/bson/4.11.1/src/test/java/org_mongodb/bson/StringRangeSetTest.java`. The scratch artifacts also show `StringRangeSetTest` passing and the dynamic-access report at `tests/src/org.mongodb/bson/4.11.1/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` shows full coverage for this run (`25/25`, including `org.bson.types.StringRangeSet.toArray(...)`). But the scratch metrics record still ended as failure with `generated_loc: 0`, `artifacts.test_file: None`, and `artifacts.metadata_file: None` in `/home/jovan/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2717-dac4c17b/.pending_metrics.json`.\\n\\nThere is also one content issue to review manually before opening a PR: `tests/src/org.mongodb/bson/4.11.1/src/test/java/org_mongodb/bson/BsonTest.java` is still a scaffold placeholder, and its result XML shows it only prints “This is just a placeholder, implement your test”. Please inspect `human-intervention-logs/org.mongodb:bson:4.11.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T00-26-07-640116Z.log`, `human-intervention-logs/org.mongodb:bson:4.11.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T23-37-31-251921Z.log`, and `human-intervention-logs/org.mongodb:bson:4.11.1/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`.\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Check out the preserved branch and review the generated test set, especially `StringRangeSetTest`, the `{}` metadata file, and the placeholder `BsonTest`.\\n2. Rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.mongodb:bson:4.11.1 --stacktrace` on the preserved branch to confirm the preserved work still passes and reproduces the `25/25` dynamic-access coverage.\\n3. If validation is green, clean up or replace the placeholder scaffold test and open the PR manually from the preserved branch.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2717#issuecomment-4340055868\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T00:27:00Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job failed for `org.mongodb:bson:4.11.1`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2717-library-new-request-org.mongodb-bson-4.11.1-65f98600\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was the post-generation test-quality/finalization step, not native-image execution. The preserved branch already contains generated tests plus `metadata/org.mongodb/bson/4.11.1/reachability-metadata.json`, and `tests/src/org.mongodb/bson/4.11.1/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` shows full dynamic-access coverage (`25/25`). The latest native trace run in `human-intervention-logs/org.mongodb:bson:4.11.1/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-02T00-23-03-980749Z.log` is `BUILD SUCCESSFUL` and includes `org_mongodb.bson.StringRangeSetTest > keySetCreatesTypedArrayWhenProvidedArrayIsTooSmall() SUCCESSFUL`. However, `stats/org.mongodb/bson/4.11.1/execution-metrics.json` still records `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, and `artifacts.test_file: None` / `metadata_file: None`, which is consistent with the run being rejected after generation. The preserved tree also still has the scaffold placeholder in `tests/src/org.mongodb/bson/4.11.1/src/test/java/org_mongodb/bson/BsonTest.java` (`This is just a placeholder, implement your test`), which is the strongest concrete reason to suspect the scaffold-placeholder quality gate tripped.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.mongodb:bson:4.11.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T00-21-35-879913Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.mongodb:bson:4.11.1/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-02T00-23-03-980749Z.log`\\n- `stats/org.mongodb/bson/4.11.1/execution-metrics.json`\\n\\nRecommended manual follow-up:\\n- Remove or replace the scaffold placeholder `BsonTest.java` on the preserved branch while keeping the generated focused tests.\\n- Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.mongodb:bson:4.11.1` (or re-run the workflow) to confirm the library passes once the placeholder is gone.\\n- If the rerun still fails, inspect the post-generation finalization/metrics step to determine why artifacts were not recorded despite the passing native trace and 25/25 coverage.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2717#issuecomment-4362329315\"}]}},{\"number\":2719,\"title\":\"Support for xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2719\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:41:47Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-02T00:35:45Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nxerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-29T00:07:36Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2719-library-new-request-xerces-xmlParserAPIs-2.6.2-9d0849a3\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was `add-new-library-support` test generation. The run metrics show 4 iterations, 0 generated LOC, no dynamic-access coverage, and identical start/end commits (`b224fdd12e0499e70ac9bd63915a05cbbab00387`), which matches the generated test source still being the scaffold placeholder at `tests/src/xerces/xmlParserAPIs/2.6.2/src/test/java/xerces/xmlParserAPIs/XmlParserAPIsTest.java` (“This is just a placeholder, implement your test”). Artifact discovery itself appears to have succeeded: `human-intervention-logs/xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` and `human-intervention-logs/xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` resolved URLs/description, and the preserved metadata file is just `{}`.\\n\\nThe preserved follow-up evidence points to the real blocker being `javax.xml.parsers.SecuritySupport` under the `java.xml` module. In `human-intervention-logs/xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T23-59-08-584380Z.log`, a generated `SecuritySupportTest` first hit `ClassNotFoundException: javax.xml.parsers.SecuritySupport`, and a later native-image attempt failed in `:nativeTestCompile` with `--patch-module=java.xml=.../build/javaXmlPatch` reported as “not a valid mainclass.” The related local artifacts to inspect are `tests/src/xerces/xmlParserAPIs/2.6.2/build/test-results/test/TEST-xerces.xmlParserAPIs.SecuritySupportTest.xml` and `tests/src/xerces/xmlParserAPIs/2.6.2/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` (currently `0/0`).\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Check out the preserved branch and inspect `human-intervention-logs/xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T23-59-08-584380Z.log` to recover the attempted `SecuritySupportTest` approach.\\n2. Replace the scaffold test with a real library-specific test for `javax.xml.parsers.SecuritySupport` and wire the required `java.xml` patch/open handling so both JVM and native-image runs can see the patched classes.\\n3. Re-run `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2` and `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2` after the test/build changes.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2719#issuecomment-4339978541\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"jormundur00\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-29T01:03:30Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job for `xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2` failed. Preserved work is available on branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fjormundur00%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2719-library-new-request-xerces-xmlParserAPIs-2.6.2-b56d3610\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was `add-new-library-support` / test generation. The run metrics ended in failure with `Generated LOC: 0`, and the starting and ending commit were both `4264de0b214c497f40c0ca0754d5b9ea68400f2e`, which means the automated run did not produce a net accepted patch. In the generated test tree, `tests/src/xerces/xmlParserAPIs/2.6.2/src/test/java/xerces/xmlParserAPIs/XmlParserAPIsTest.java` is still the untouched placeholder scaffold, and the native test output also prints `This is just a placeholder, implement your test`. The generation logs also show the agent could not use the upstream source URL (`Main sources ... unavailable (<urlopen error unknown url type: https>)`) and repeatedly probed the wrong path (`rg: src/test/java: No such file or directory`), which is consistent with `test_generation_failed`.\\n\\nThere is also concrete Gradle/native-test evidence that the generated SecuritySupport tests were not correct as produced. In `build/tests/xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2/9989e9c7f05c6954fbdabd2190b9c7c2.out`, `OrgXmlSaxHelpersSecuritySupportTest`, `SecuritySupportTest`, and `TransformSecuritySupportTest` all fail in `getsSystemResourceWhenClassLoaderIsNull()` with `Expecting actual not to be null`, and `:nativeTest` exits non-zero. Maintainers should inspect:\\n- `logs/xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T00-38-52-263566Z.log`\\n- `logs/xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T00-51-50-817102Z.log`\\n- `logs/xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T00-58-16-974568Z.log`\\n- `logs/xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n- `logs/xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Replace the scaffold `XmlParserAPIsTest` with a real library-specific native-image test, or remove it if the SecuritySupport tests fully supersede it.\\n2. Rework the generated `SecuritySupport` tests so they validate behavior that actually holds for `xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2` on the current JDK/GraalVM, especially the null-classloader/system-resource path that currently returns `null`.\\n3. Re-run metadata validation and the single-library test workflow for `xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2` after fixing the tests.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2719#issuecomment-4340163322\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T00:35:39Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2719-library-new-request-xerces-xmlParserAPIs-2.6.2-86c7b7be\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was post-generation review/finalization, not raw Gradle validation. In the preserved worktree, `checkstyle` passed (`human-intervention-logs/xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2/checkstyle/pi-checkstyle-2026-05-02T00-32-18-215759Z.log`), and the saved Gradle outputs under `build/tests/xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2/` show `test`, `nativeTestCompile`, `nativeTest`, and `generateDynamicAccessReport` succeeding. However, the generated patch is not acceptable for a `library-new-request`: relative to `origin/master` it modifies shared harness code in `tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/stats/LibraryStatsSupport.java`, and the generation log explicitly says this was done because the dynamic-access report contained `Unknown Source` frames with no line numbers, so the agent changed the reporter to fall back to JaCoCo method coverage. The run also adds legacy test-only native-image config files at `tests/src/xerces/xmlParserAPIs/2.6.2/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/xml-parser-apis-tests-only/reflect-config.json` and `.../resource-config.json`, which are not acceptable for new-library submissions. The metrics file still records the run as `failure` after 11 iterations and 992 generated LOC, despite 12/12 dynamic-access coverage.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T00-07-31-007803Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T00-29-32-866009Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2/checkstyle/pi-checkstyle-2026-05-02T00-32-18-215759Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2/d6486e76d13ebdefd46f63cac7b4e50b.out`\\n- `build/tests/xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2/f84682b76e11921884cc60c612f04b12.out`\\n- `stats/xerces/xmlParserAPIs/2.6.2/execution-metrics.json`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Rework the library support without touching `tests/tck-build-logic/**`; if coverage cannot be achieved without changing shared stats logic, use a different manual test strategy.\\n2. Replace the legacy test-only `reflect-config.json` and `resource-config.json` files with acceptable `reachability-metadata.json`-based metadata only, or remove the test-only metadata if unnecessary.\\n3. Rewrite the generated tests to avoid reflective access to internal `SecuritySupport*` classes and custom classloader tricks where possible, then rerun the normal library validation.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2719#issuecomment-4362374809\"}]}},{\"number\":2711,\"title\":\"Support for com.google.protobuf:protobuf-javalite:3.25.5\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2711\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:41:46Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-30T04:56:54Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\ncom.google.protobuf:protobuf-javalite:3.25.5\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T04:56:48Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `com.google.protobuf:protobuf-javalite:3.25.5`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2711-library-new-request-com.google.protobuf-protobuf-javalite-3.25.5-89a3d696\\n\\nMost likely the failure happened in `add-new-library-support` during the last dynamic-access test-generation step. The latest generation log shows the run was still trying to cover one remaining reflection site in `com.google.protobuf.UnsafeUtil$Android64MemoryAccessor`: `java.lang.reflect.Field#get(java.lang.Object)` from `getStaticObject(...)`, and the failed-run stats/metrics were still `36/37` covered calls (97.30%). Checkstyle was fixed afterward and passed, so style does not look like the blocker.\\n\\nRelevant logs to inspect:\\n- `logs/com.google.protobuf:protobuf-javalite:3.25.5/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T04-30-12-276762Z.log`\\n- `logs/com.google.protobuf:protobuf-javalite:3.25.5/checkstyle/pi-checkstyle-2026-04-30T04-36-43-652349Z.log`\\n- `logs/com.google.protobuf:protobuf-javalite:3.25.5/metadata-fix/codex.log`\\n\\nThe preserved branch looks worth salvaging: `metadata-fix/codex.log` records a follow-up fix that raises coverage to `37/37` and reports targeted `./gradlew test` and `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles` passing for this coordinate.\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Review the preserved branch diff, especially the `UnsafeUtil*` tests and the test fixture `src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json`.\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=com.google.protobuf:protobuf-javalite:3.25.5` and `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=com.google.protobuf:protobuf-javalite:3.25.5` from that branch.\\n3. If those stay green, open or update the follow-up PR from the preserved branch; otherwise adjust the final `UnsafeUtil` accessor coverage test manually and rerun.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2711#issuecomment-4349806981\"}]}},{\"number\":2705,\"title\":\"Support for org.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged:jersey-guava:2.23.2\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2705\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:41:44Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-02T00:29:52Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged:jersey-guava:2.23.2\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-29T00:42:09Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job for `org.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged:jersey-guava:2.23.2` failed. Preserved work is available at https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2705-library-new-request-org.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged-jersey-guava-2.23.2-5f2d3c9c.\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was the final `add-new-library-support` handoff/staging step, not coverage generation itself. In `human-intervention-logs/org.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged:jersey-guava:2.23.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T00-39-22-939024Z.log`, the agent adds `PlatformTest.java` and creates commit `b93f3049c4`, but it still reports `metadata/org.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged/jersey-guava/2.23.2/` as untracked. The preserved-work commit then adds `metadata/org.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged/jersey-guava/2.23.2/reachability-metadata.json`, and the metrics summary still says `Generated LOC: 0`, which points to a bookkeeping/staging failure rather than missing test coverage. Coverage itself looks complete: `tests/src/org.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged/jersey-guava/2.23.2/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` shows `14/14` covered calls.\\n\\nThere were earlier real native-image test failures during generation. `build/tests/org.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged:jersey-guava:2.23.2/71e13a276786220e26dcb816e948126d.out` shows `SerializationTest` and `TreeMultimapTest` failing with `ClassNotFoundException: jersey.repackaged.com.google.common.collect.HashMultimap` and `InvalidClassException: jersey.repackaged.com.google.common.collect.TreeMultimap; no valid constructor`; the first related fix is recorded in `human-intervention-logs/org.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged:jersey-guava:2.23.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T00-26-15-000723Z.log`.\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Check out the preserved branch and verify that `metadata/org.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged/jersey-guava/2.23.2/reachability-metadata.json` is intentionally `{}` and included with the generated tests.\\n2. Run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged:jersey-guava:2.23.2` on that branch to confirm the coordinate is green end-to-end.\\n3. If it passes, open or recreate the support PR from the preserved branch; if it still fails, start from `build/tests/org.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged:jersey-guava:2.23.2/71e13a276786220e26dcb816e948126d.out` and the final `pi-generation-2026-04-29T00-39-22-939024Z.log`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2705#issuecomment-4340095756\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T00:29:45Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job for `org.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged:jersey-guava:2.23.2` failed. Preserved work is available at https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2705-library-new-request-org.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged-jersey-guava-2.23.2-65ed931f.\\n\\nThe most likely failure was the final `add-new-library-support` staging/reporting step, not the coverage/test content itself. In `human-intervention-logs/org.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged:jersey-guava:2.23.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T00-26-41-829904Z.log`, the agent writes `tests/src/org.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged/jersey-guava/2.23.2/src/test/java/org_glassfish_jersey_bundles_repackaged/jersey_guava/PlatformTest.java`, but its later `git status --short` still shows `?? metadata/org.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged/jersey-guava/2.23.2/` and `?? .../PlatformTest.java` as untracked. That lines up with `stats/org.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged/jersey-guava/2.23.2/execution-metrics.json`, which records `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, and `artifacts.test_file` / `artifacts.metadata_file` as `None`, even though the preserved worktree now contains generated files.\\n\\nThe preserved work itself looks viable: `tests/src/org.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged/jersey-guava/2.23.2/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` reports `14/14` covered calls, and `tests/src/org.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged/jersey-guava/2.23.2/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` shows `7` native tests with `0` failures. If you want the artifact provenance details, also inspect `human-intervention-logs/org.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged:jersey-guava:2.23.2/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` and `human-intervention-logs/org.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged:jersey-guava:2.23.2/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`.\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Check out the preserved branch and verify that the generated files under `metadata/org.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged/jersey-guava/2.23.2/` and `tests/src/org.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged/jersey-guava/2.23.2/` are the intended final contents.\\n2. Run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.glassfish.jersey.bundles.repackaged:jersey-guava:2.23.2` on the preserved branch to confirm the coordinate is green end to end.\\n3. If that passes, recreate/open the support PR from the preserved branch; if it does not, start from the final generation log and the native test report paths above.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2705#issuecomment-4362338367\"}]}},{\"number\":2697,\"title\":\"Support for org.openjdk.jol:jol-core:0.2\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2697\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:41:42Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-02T00:36:12Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.openjdk.jol:jol-core:0.2\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"jormundur00\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-29T01:37:39Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.openjdk.jol:jol-core:0.2`. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fjormundur00%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2697-library-new-request-org.openjdk.jol-jol-core-0.2-7ccc9b96\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is native-image test execution after test generation, not coverage collection. The generated suite reached `13/13` dynamic-access coverage, and the JVM test results under `tests/src/org.openjdk.jol/jol-core/0.2/build/test-results/test/*.xml` are green, but `tests/src/org.openjdk.jol/jol-core/0.2/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` reports 6 native-test errors. The shared failure is `java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: Could not initialize class org.openjdk.jol.util.VMSupport`, caused by `java.lang.IllegalStateException: Infrastructure failure, klass = class org.openjdk.jol.util.VMSupport$MyBooleans4` and `java.lang.NoSuchFieldException: f1` from `VMSupport$VMOptions.getMinDiff(...)` during native execution. The native-image build/run trace is in `build/tests/org.openjdk.jol:jol-core:0.2/70ee46ef9cfe3466cc78cfc434f4c4d7.out`.\\n\\nThere is also a test-quality issue in the generated tree: `tests/src/org.openjdk.jol/jol-core/0.2/src/test/java/org_openjdk_jol/jol_core/Jol_coreTest.java` is still the scaffold placeholder (`\\\"This is just a placeholder, implement your test\\\"`), so the result is not ready to accept as a `library-new-request` PR even aside from the native failure.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.openjdk.jol:jol-core:0.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T01-33-10-033943Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.openjdk.jol:jol-core:0.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T01-10-49-399251Z.log`\\n- `tests/src/org.openjdk.jol/jol-core/0.2/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\\n- `build/tests/org.openjdk.jol:jol-core:0.2/70ee46ef9cfe3466cc78cfc434f4c4d7.out`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. On the preserved branch, either rework the tests to avoid `VMSupport` paths that break under native image or add the missing native-image support if `VMSupport` is expected to work there.\\n2. Remove the scaffold placeholder `Jol_coreTest` and keep only library-specific tests.\\n3. Rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.openjdk.jol:jol-core:0.2 --stacktrace` on the preserved branch and confirm both JVM and native test lanes pass.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2697#issuecomment-4340265068\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T00:36:06Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.openjdk.jol:jol-core:0.2`. Preserved work is available on https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2697-library-new-request-org.openjdk.jol-jol-core-0.2-d1cd4109\\n\\nThe most likely failure point was the final test-generation/PR-readiness handoff, not Gradle test execution. The preserved metrics show workflow status `failure` after 5 iterations even though dynamic-access coverage reached `13/13 (100.00%)` in `stats/org.openjdk.jol/jol-core/0.2/execution-metrics.json`, and the preserved Gradle outputs show `BUILD SUCCESSFUL` for both `:generateDynamicAccessReport` and `:nativeTest` with `7 tests successful` in `build/tests/org.openjdk.jol:jol-core:0.2/3bed707e83d6604c7c6c2c4d87a1586a.out` and `build/tests/org.openjdk.jol:jol-core:0.2/12da19d2236006e6a6eb986a073835f0.out`. In the last generation log, the model explicitly says it added `ClassDataTest` and updated `tests/src/org.openjdk.jol/jol-core/0.2/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/jol-core-test/reflect-config.json`, while the preserved branch also contains `tests/src/org.openjdk.jol/jol-core/0.2/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json`; that strongly suggests the generated test resources are not PR-ready because they still rely on a legacy `reflect-config.json`.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.openjdk.jol:jol-core:0.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T00-31-37-266748Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/org.openjdk.jol:jol-core:0.2/12da19d2236006e6a6eb986a073835f0.out`\\n- `build/tests/org.openjdk.jol:jol-core:0.2/3bed707e83d6604c7c6c2c4d87a1586a.out`\\n- `stats/org.openjdk.jol/jol-core/0.2/execution-metrics.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n- Review the preserved branch and consolidate the test-only reflection metadata into `tests/src/org.openjdk.jol/jol-core/0.2/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json`, removing the legacy `jol-core-test/reflect-config.json`.\\n- Sanity-check the generated tests and library metadata on the preserved branch, then rerun the coordinate validation/test pipeline for `org.openjdk.jol:jol-core:0.2`.\\n- If that passes cleanly, continue from the preserved branch and open a manual PR.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2697#issuecomment-4362375999\"}]}},{\"number\":2661,\"title\":\"Support for org.jetbrains.compose.foundation:foundation:1.7.3\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2661\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:40:17Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-30T05:36:35Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.jetbrains.compose.foundation:foundation:1.7.3\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"github-actions\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:41:54Z\",\"body\":\"Automation: No dependency issues were created by the triage workflow.\\n\\nThis typically means every dependency in the deps.dev expansion is already supported by the repository.\\n\\nPlan nodes:\\n```\\norg.jetbrains.compose.foundation:foundation:1.7.3\\n```\\n\\nSupported GA detected during checks:\\n```\\n(none)\\n```\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2661#issuecomment-4336337552\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T05:36:29Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.jetbrains.compose.foundation:foundation:1.7.3`. Preserved work is available on branch https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2661-library-new-request-org.jetbrains.compose.foundation-foundation-1.7.3-303aa4eb.\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was `add-new-library-support` during test generation/validation. The first generation attempt failed in `tckTest` because `nativeTest` could not resolve AndroidX dependencies (`androidx.annotation:annotation:1.8.0`, `androidx.collection:collection:1.4.0`, and several `androidx.lifecycle` artifacts) until a `google()` repository was added; see `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.compose.foundation:foundation:1.7.3/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T05-27-18-102506Z.log`. A later retry also ran the wrong Gradle task from the repo root (`Task 'compileTestKotlin' not found in root project 'reachability-metadata'`); see `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.compose.foundation:foundation:1.7.3/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T05-31-31-699858Z.log`.\\n\\nThe preserved work now contains changes to the test module, and preserved output shows `nativeTest` passing with 5 tests in `build/tests/org.jetbrains.compose.foundation:foundation:1.7.3/365624a42e2aee76645ea9f8fb8266a1.out`. However, `tests/src/org.jetbrains.compose.foundation/foundation/1.7.3/src/test/kotlin/org_jetbrains_compose_foundation/foundation/FoundationTest.kt` still contains the scaffold placeholder method `fun test() { println(\\\"This is just a placeholder, implement your test\\\") }`, and `stats/org.jetbrains.compose.foundation/foundation/1.7.3/execution-metrics.json` still reports `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, `artifacts.test_file: None`, and no dynamic-access coverage. That points to a test-generation quality/bookkeeping failure rather than a current compile/runtime failure.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.compose.foundation:foundation:1.7.3/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T05-27-18-102506Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.compose.foundation:foundation:1.7.3/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T05-31-31-699858Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.compose.foundation:foundation:1.7.3/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T05-34-56-538496Z.log`\\n- `stats/org.jetbrains.compose.foundation/foundation/1.7.3/execution-metrics.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Confirm `google()` is the intended repository fix for this test module so Compose Desktop dependencies resolve reliably.\\n2. Remove or replace the remaining scaffold placeholder test in `FoundationTest.kt` with a fully library-specific assertion.\\n3. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.jetbrains.compose.foundation:foundation:1.7.3 --stacktrace` and refresh metrics/dynamic-access reporting.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2661#issuecomment-4349953989\"}]}},{\"number\":2659,\"title\":\"Support for org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2659\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:40:17Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-02T01:34:01Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-29T02:04:28Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job for `org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0` failed. Preserved work is available at https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2659-library-new-request-org.jetbrains.kotlinx-atomicfu-0.19.0-bd3fcb5d\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is artifact/coverage collection after test generation, not the generated test itself. In `logs/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T02-01-16-717063Z.log`, the run reports `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0 --stacktrace` and that JVM and native-image tests passed successfully. But the Gradle outputs for this run fail in `build/tests/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0/942de5bf0d475d0f05a118161fb8f927.out` at `:listLibraryJars` and in `build/tests/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0/0fbb77ac4a267d46308e849a5a0c893f.out` at `:jacocoTestReport` with `No eligible artifacts found on the classpath for org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0.` The metrics also reflect that failure: `local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/2659-399694b6/.pending_metrics.json` and `script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json` record `status: failure`, `tested_library_loc: 0`, `code_coverage_percent: 0.0`, and dynamic-access coverage is unavailable.\\n\\nThis looks like a multiplatform/root-artifact mismatch. The cached `org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0` POM is `packaging=pom` and points to `atomicfu-jvm`, while the successful native test classpath in `build/tests/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0/ece4e61ae3f9dcf3871d8eef46c0e6f6.out` contains `atomicfu-jvm-0.19.0.jar`. The generated test is present at `tests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/atomicfu/0.19.0/src/test/kotlin/org_jetbrains_kotlinx/atomicfu/AtomicfuTest.kt`, and no `stats/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/atomicfu/0.19.0/stats.json` was produced.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `logs/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T02-01-16-717063Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n- `logs/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n- `build/tests/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0/942de5bf0d475d0f05a118161fb8f927.out`\\n- `build/tests/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0/0fbb77ac4a267d46308e849a5a0c893f.out`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Confirm whether this library should be handled as `org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu-jvm:0.19.0` for TCK coverage/stats, or update artifact-selection logic to treat `org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu` as a multiplatform wrapper.\\n2. Rerun the coverage/stats steps after fixing artifact selection so `listLibraryJars`, `jacocoTestReport`, and `stats/.../stats.json` can be generated.\\n3. Re-check whether the current generated test and empty `metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/atomicfu/0.19.0/reachability-metadata.json` are still valid once dynamic-access coverage is available.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2659#issuecomment-4340342176\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T01:33:55Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0`. Preserved work is available on the [preserved work branch](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2659-library-new-request-org.jetbrains.kotlinx-atomicfu-0.19.0-2569122e).\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was post-generation validation/coverage collection, not the initial test synthesis. Artifact discovery shows that `org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0` is a `pom` artifact (`human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`, which contains `<packaging>pom</packaging>`), and the preserved Gradle outputs fail with `No eligible artifacts found on the classpath for org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0` in `build/tests/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0/f2b31b2adbf5ebbe8c86c8130b20a85b.out` and `build/tests/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0/5a378179c0307608e7f48798ca0461c0.out`. The generated test was written to `tests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/atomicfu/0.19.0/src/test/kotlin/org_jetbrains_kotlinx/atomicfu/AtomicfuTest.kt`, and native test compilation resolves `atomicfu-jvm-0.19.0.jar` in `build/tests/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0/6c4cf645a5de0c265a1afcbe8d5dbb1a.out`, which strongly suggests the requested coordinate is a multiplatform wrapper while the concrete JVM artifact is `org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu-jvm:0.19.0`. Metrics also ended in failure with no exploded coverage file (`stats/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/atomicfu/0.19.0/stats.json` is missing) and `code_coverage_percent: 0.0` in `stats/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/atomicfu/0.19.0/execution-metrics.json`.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T01-28-49-782599Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0/f2b31b2adbf5ebbe8c86c8130b20a85b.out`\\n- `build/tests/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0/5a378179c0307608e7f48798ca0461c0.out`\\n- `build/tests/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0/6c4cf645a5de0c265a1afcbe8d5dbb1a.out`\\n- `stats/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/atomicfu/0.19.0/execution-metrics.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Decide whether this issue should target the concrete JVM artifact `org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu-jvm:0.19.0` instead of the `pom` wrapper `org.jetbrains.kotlinx:atomicfu:0.19.0`.\\n2. If support should remain on `atomicfu`, manually adjust validation for `pom` packaging so tasks that require eligible library JARs (`listLibraryJars`, `jacocoTestReport`) are skipped or redirected.\\n3. Rerun validation and regenerate coverage/stats for the final target coordinate.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2659#issuecomment-4362545616\"}]}},{\"number\":2644,\"title\":\"Support for org.jetbrains.compose.runtime:runtime:1.7.3\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2644\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:40:08Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-02T01:42:34Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.jetbrains.compose.runtime:runtime:1.7.3\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"github-actions\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:41:44Z\",\"body\":\"Automation: No dependency issues were created by the triage workflow.\\n\\nThis typically means every dependency in the deps.dev expansion is already supported by the repository.\\n\\nPlan nodes:\\n```\\norg.jetbrains.compose.runtime:runtime:1.7.3\\n```\\n\\nSupported GA detected during checks:\\n```\\n(none)\\n```\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2644#issuecomment-4336336240\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T20:04:48Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.jetbrains.compose.runtime:runtime:1.7.3`. Preserved work is available on branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2644-library-new-request-org.jetbrains.compose.runtime-runtime-1.7.3-0a3fdde0\\n\\nThe failure appears to be in `add-new-library-support`, not artifact discovery. `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.compose.runtime:runtime:1.7.3/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` and `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.compose.runtime:runtime:1.7.3/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` completed successfully, but the generation/test loop failed repeatedly. Earlier Gradle outputs show dependency/configuration blockers: `build/tests/org.jetbrains.compose.runtime:runtime:1.7.3/109230b28182fea22854c67a970a62d4.out` could not resolve `androidx.collection:collection:1.4.0` and `androidx.annotation:annotation:1.8.0`, and `build/tests/org.jetbrains.compose.runtime:runtime:1.7.3/2a9f1046fe192a27759bdd8fda930c94.out` failed `:listLibraryJars` with `No eligible artifacts found on the classpath for org.jetbrains.compose.runtime:runtime:1.7.3`.\\n\\nThe most likely final blocker is that the run ended before the last metadata fix was checkpointed. In `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.compose.runtime:runtime:1.7.3/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T20-01-17-258356Z.log`, the final attempt explicitly diagnoses that `metadata/org.jetbrains.compose.runtime/runtime/index.json` references `1.7.3` but `metadata/org.jetbrains.compose.runtime/runtime/1.7.3/reachability-metadata.json` was missing, writes `{}` to that file, and then reruns `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.jetbrains.compose.runtime:runtime:1.7.3`, which passes including native-image execution. The metrics run still ended in failure at commit `159814fc46f2b199facd90ed20091d834d2988fd`, before that metadata file was preserved on the branch. Dynamic-access coverage is still unavailable; there is no `stats/org.jetbrains.compose.runtime/runtime/1.7.3/stats.json` in the preserved worktree.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n1. `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.compose.runtime:runtime:1.7.3/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T20-01-17-258356Z.log`\\n2. `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.compose.runtime:runtime:1.7.3/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T19-58-55-476062Z.log`\\n3. `build/tests/org.jetbrains.compose.runtime:runtime:1.7.3/109230b28182fea22854c67a970a62d4.out`\\n4. `build/tests/org.jetbrains.compose.runtime:runtime:1.7.3/2a9f1046fe192a27759bdd8fda930c94.out`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Review the preserved branch and keep the generated test changes together with `metadata/org.jetbrains.compose.runtime/runtime/1.7.3/reachability-metadata.json`.\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.jetbrains.compose.runtime:runtime:1.7.3` to confirm the coordinate stays green in CI.\\n3. Regenerate stats for this coordinate so `stats/org.jetbrains.compose.runtime/runtime/1.7.3/stats.json` exists and coverage is no longer unavailable.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2644#issuecomment-4338659725\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T01:42:28Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.jetbrains.compose.runtime:runtime:1.7.3`. Preserved work is available on the branch: `https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2644-library-new-request-org.jetbrains.compose.runtime-runtime-1.7.3-581001e3`.\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was generated test validation. In `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.compose.runtime:runtime:1.7.3/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T01-28-22-815734Z.log`, `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.jetbrains.compose.runtime:runtime:1.7.3` failed in `:compileTestKotlin` because the generated test referenced `androidx.compose.runtime.ComposeVersion`, which is internal (`RuntimeTest.kt:10` and `RuntimeTest.kt:237`). The run metrics still ended as failed in `stats/org.jetbrains.compose.runtime/runtime/1.7.3/execution-metrics.json` (`status: failure`, 5 iterations, coverage not produced).\\n\\nThere is also evidence that later preserved work fixed the bad test and validated successfully: `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.compose.runtime:runtime:1.7.3/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T01-37-37-372138Z.log` reports successful validation, and the preserved test reports show 6 passing JVM tests in `tests/src/org.jetbrains.compose.runtime/runtime/1.7.3/build/test-results/test/TEST-org_jetbrains_compose_runtime.runtime.RuntimeTest.xml` and 6 passing native tests in `tests/src/org.jetbrains.compose.runtime/runtime/1.7.3/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.compose.runtime:runtime:1.7.3/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T01-28-22-815734Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.compose.runtime:runtime:1.7.3/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T01-37-37-372138Z.log`\\n- `stats/org.jetbrains.compose.runtime/runtime/1.7.3/execution-metrics.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Review the preserved branch and keep the later test fix that removes the invalid `ComposeVersion` usage.\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.jetbrains.compose.runtime:runtime:1.7.3` from that preserved branch to refresh the failed run state.\\n3. If the rerun is green, proceed with the PR/update from the preserved branch; if not, continue from the same branch and inspect the generated test module logs under `build/tests/org.jetbrains.compose.runtime:runtime:1.7.3/`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2644#issuecomment-4362565554\"}]}},{\"number\":2628,\"title\":\"Support for org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js:2.3.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2628\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:40:00Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-02T02:02:28Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js:2.3.0\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"github-actions\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:41:30Z\",\"body\":\"Automation: No dependency issues were created by the triage workflow.\\n\\nThis typically means every dependency in the deps.dev expansion is already supported by the repository.\\n\\nPlan nodes:\\n```\\norg.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js:2.3.0\\n```\\n\\nSupported GA detected during checks:\\n```\\n(none)\\n```\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2628#issuecomment-4336334143\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-29T02:19:04Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js:2.3.0`. Preserved work is available on:\\nhttps://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2628-library-new-request-org.jetbrains.kotlin-kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js-2.3.0-2768b518\\n\\nArtifact discovery appears to have completed, but test generation most likely failed in the `scaffold` stage. `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js:2.3.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` ends with `BUILD SUCCESSFUL` and the run produced `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlin-kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js-2.3.0.json`, but `build/reports/problems/problems-report.html` records `requestedTasks: \\\"scaffold --coordinates=org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js:2.3.0\\\"` and Gradle reports `Cannot choose between the available variants of org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js:2.3.0`. The same report shows the ambiguous variants are `wasmJsApiElements` (`org.gradle.usage=kotlin-api`) and `wasmJsRuntimeElements` (`org.gradle.usage=kotlin-runtime`), so the scaffold consumer is not selecting a Wasm usage explicitly.\\n\\nThere is no generated test tree under `tests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js/2.3.0`, no `stats/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js/2.3.0/stats.json`, and no scratch metrics output for this coordinate, so dynamic-access coverage remains unavailable. Maintainers should inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js:2.3.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n- `build/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.jetbrains.kotlin-kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js-2.3.0.log`\\n- `build/reports/problems/problems-report.html`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Reproduce `./gradlew scaffold --coordinates=org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js:2.3.0 --stacktrace` and update scaffold/test-generation dependency resolution so this Wasm artifact sets an explicit `org.gradle.usage`.\\n2. After scaffold succeeds, regenerate the library test and confirm `tests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js/2.3.0` and `stats/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js/2.3.0/stats.json` are created.\\n3. Rerun the library validation pipeline for `org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js:2.3.0`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2628#issuecomment-4340386805\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T02:02:22Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job failed for `org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js:2.3.0`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch:\\nhttps://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2628-library-new-request-org.jetbrains.kotlin-kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js-2.3.0-0924b471\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was test generation/scaffolding after artifact discovery. The preserved `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js:2.3.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` shows `discoverArtifactMetadata` completed successfully, but it also shows that this artifact is published as `packaging=klib` with Gradle metadata `org.gradle.jvm.environment=non-jvm`, `org.jetbrains.kotlin.platform.type=wasm`, and `org.jetbrains.kotlin.wasm.target=js`. There is no generated `tests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js/2.3.0`, no `metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js/...`, no `stats/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js/2.3.0`, and run metrics / dynamic-access coverage are unavailable, which suggests the pipeline stopped before it could produce a JVM/native-image test project for this non-JVM Kotlin/Wasm JS module.\\n\\nPlease inspect `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js:2.3.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` first. If the preserved worktree still has build outputs, also check `build/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.jetbrains.kotlin-kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js-2.3.0.log` and `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlin-kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js-2.3.0.json`.\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n- Decide whether `org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-wasm-js` should be excluded from the standard new-library JVM/native-image pipeline because it is a Kotlin/Wasm `klib`.\\n- If support is still desired, create a minimal manual test project for the Wasm JS artifact and verify what validation or metadata collection is actually meaningful for this target.\\n- Update the automation or triage rules so future non-JVM `klib` / Wasm artifacts fail early with a clearer reason.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2628#issuecomment-4362612375\"}]}},{\"number\":2623,\"title\":\"Support for org.aspectj:aspectjrt:1.9.6\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2623\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:39:58Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-02T04:56:35Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.aspectj:aspectjrt:1.9.6\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"}]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"github-actions\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:42:00Z\",\"body\":\"Automation: No dependency issues were created by the triage workflow.\\n\\nThis typically means every dependency in the deps.dev expansion is already supported by the repository.\\n\\nPlan nodes:\\n```\\norg.aspectj:aspectjrt:1.9.6\\n```\\n\\nSupported GA detected during checks:\\n```\\n(none)\\n```\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2623#issuecomment-4336338575\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-29T02:59:32Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.aspectj:aspectjrt:1.9.6`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2623-library-new-request-org.aspectj-aspectjrt-1.9.6-2f612dd3\\n\\nThe most likely failure point was the final test-generation/finalization stage, not the generated tests themselves. The last generation transcript (`logs/org.aspectj:aspectjrt:1.9.6/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T02-57-15-373021Z.log`) ends after committing only test changes through `4962d73f318ffb82a1a1f1a0067463836d2dd80c` and explicitly reports `metadata/org.aspectj/aspectjrt/1.9.6/reachability-metadata.json` as still untracked. The ending commit contains only test sources plus test `reflect-config.json`; the metadata file was added later only by the preservation commit, and there is still no tracked `stats/org.aspectj/aspectjrt/1.9.6/stats.json` in the preserved worktree. At the same time, the local evidence for the generated tests is good: `tests/src/org.aspectj/aspectjrt/1.9.6/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` shows full coverage (72/72 overall; `AjTypeImpl` 37/37), and `build/tests/org.aspectj:aspectjrt:1.9.6/507bd0ad2602ea07c399639eee350062.out` shows `:nativeTest` completed with `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `logs/org.aspectj:aspectjrt:1.9.6/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T02-57-15-373021Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.aspectj:aspectjrt:1.9.6/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T02-55-35-775389Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/org.aspectj:aspectjrt:1.9.6/507bd0ad2602ea07c399639eee350062.out`\\n- `tests/src/org.aspectj/aspectjrt/1.9.6/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Review the preserved branch and keep the generated test set if it looks acceptable for a new-library PR.\\n2. Add/verify the missing library artifacts in the actual change set, especially `metadata/org.aspectj/aspectjrt/1.9.6/reachability-metadata.json` and `stats/org.aspectj/aspectjrt/1.9.6/stats.json`.\\n3. Re-run the library lane for `org.aspectj:aspectjrt:1.9.6` to confirm the finalized branch passes end-to-end.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2623#issuecomment-4340519846\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T03:32:03Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.aspectj:aspectjrt:1.9.6`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2623-library-new-request-org.aspectj-aspectjrt-1.9.6-faa755c0\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is test generation/finalization, not coverage discovery. The dynamic-access report reached 72/72 (100%), but the run metrics still ended with `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, `metadata_entries: 0`, and `test_file`/`metadata_file` both `None` (`forge/.pending_metrics.json`, `stats/org.aspectj/aspectjrt/1.9.6/execution-metrics.json`). In the last generation attempt, the agent added `InitializerSignatureImplTest` but explicitly did not run tests, and it still had untracked outputs under `metadata/org.aspectj/aspectjrt/1.9.6/` and `tests/src/org.aspectj/aspectjrt/1.9.6/src/test/java/org_aspectj/aspectjrt/InitializerSignatureImplTest.java` (`human-intervention-logs/org.aspectj:aspectjrt:1.9.6/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T03-28-00-600680Z.log`).\\n\\nThe preserved Gradle output shows native-image build succeeded, but `:nativeTest` still failed with 5 generated tests: `AdviceSignatureImplTest`, `ConstructorSignatureImplTest`, `FieldSignatureImplTest`, and two `MethodSignatureImplTest` cases. The failures are null-result/NPE assertions around `getAdvice()`, `getConstructor()`, `getField()`, and `getMethod()` (`build/tests/org.aspectj:aspectjrt:1.9.6/6aa318705215bbec7fd40dedf68a5e95.out`). The preserved test set also still contains the scaffold placeholder `AspectjrtTest`, which prints `This is just a placeholder, implement your test`.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.aspectj:aspectjrt:1.9.6/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T03-28-00-600680Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.aspectj:aspectjrt:1.9.6/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T03-24-37-060860Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/org.aspectj:aspectjrt:1.9.6/6aa318705215bbec7fd40dedf68a5e95.out`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Review the preserved branch and replace/remove the scaffold placeholder test, then fix the generated signature tests so they match actual AspectJ runtime behavior.\\n2. Rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.aspectj:aspectjrt:1.9.6` on the preserved branch and verify `:nativeTest` passes.\\n3. If the signature-test failures come from incorrect test assumptions rather than missing metadata, keep `metadata/org.aspectj/aspectjrt/1.9.6/reachability-metadata.json` as-is (`{}`) and only rewrite/regenerate the tests.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2623#issuecomment-4362808148\"}]}},{\"number\":2451,\"title\":\"Support for org.apache.groovy:groovy:4.0.22\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2451\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:09:42Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-02T04:35:03Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.apache.groovy:groovy:4.0.22\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T04:34:56Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job for `org.apache.groovy:groovy:4.0.22` failed. Preserved work is available on this branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2451-library-new-request-org.apache.groovy-groovy-4.0.22-2495617f\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was generated test validation during native test execution. The post-gen summary shows the generated Groovy suite initially had 8 native-runtime failures; 7 were classified as non-metadata failures caused by Groovy runtime class generation or native-image-incompatible dynamic dispatch (`CallSiteGenerator`, `Tuple$tuple`, `ConfigObject$flatten`, `InvokerHelper$createScript`, `GroovyShell.evaluate`) and were removed, but the remaining test `observableCollectionsPublishMutationEvents()` still fails with `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` for a proxy implementing `java.beans.PropertyChangeListener`. That exact failure is visible in `build/tests/org.apache.groovy:groovy:4.0.22/ef80c011666dad0a56325c9c72b66b11.out` and `tests/src/org.apache.groovy/groovy/4.0.22/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`, and is summarized in `post-gen-interventions/org.apache.groovy_groovy_4.0.22.md` and `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.groovy:groovy:4.0.22/metadata-fix/codex.log`. Metrics also ended in failure after 6 iterations in `stats/org.apache.groovy/groovy/4.0.22/execution-metrics.json`, and no dynamic-access coverage artifact was produced under `tests/src/org.apache.groovy/groovy/4.0.22/build/reports/`.\\n\\nRelevant logs to inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.groovy:groovy:4.0.22/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-05-02T04-29-50-896311Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.groovy:groovy:4.0.22/metadata-fix/codex.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.groovy:groovy:4.0.22/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T04-13-08-021405Z.log`\\n- `post-gen-interventions/org.apache.groovy_groovy_4.0.22.md`\\n- `build/tests/org.apache.groovy:groovy:4.0.22/ef80c011666dad0a56325c9c72b66b11.out`\\n\\n1. Add the missing proxy reflection entry for `java.beans.PropertyChangeListener` to `metadata/org.apache.groovy/groovy/4.0.22/reachability-metadata.json` and rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.groovy:groovy:4.0.22 --stacktrace`.\\n2. Review whether the removed tests should be rewritten to avoid unsupported Groovy runtime class-definition paths rather than restored as-is.\\n3. If those runtime-generated-code scenarios are intended support targets, decide whether Groovy needs a different strategy than the standard `reachability-metadata.json`-only flow before reopening automation for this library.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2451#issuecomment-4362954100\"}]}},{\"number\":2448,\"title\":\"Support for io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2448\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:09:33Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-02T04:01:49Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nio.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T21:03:08Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job for `io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2` failed. Preserved work is available on branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2448-library-new-request-io.micrometer-micrometer-core-1.8.2-d1479dd2\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is final test-generation validation, not Gradle/native-image execution. Metrics report `test_generation_failed`, while dynamic-access coverage still reached `16/16 (100.00%)`. The generated suite still contains the scaffold placeholder test at `tests/src/io.micrometer/micrometer-core/1.8.2/src/test/java/io_micrometer/micrometer_core/Micrometer_coreTest.java`, and both `tests/src/io.micrometer/micrometer-core/1.8.2/build/test-results/test/TEST-io_micrometer.micrometer_core.Micrometer_coreTest.xml` and `tests/src/io.micrometer/micrometer-core/1.8.2/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` show that this placeholder test actually ran. The generation log `human-intervention-logs/io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T20-58-31-246686Z.log` also shows the scaffold file being read unchanged, while other iterations added class-specific coverage work.\\n\\nPlease inspect these logs first:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T20-58-31-246686Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T20-45-13-777820Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T21-00-40-685006Z.log`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Remove or replace `Micrometer_coreTest.java` with a real Micrometer-specific test so no scaffold placeholder remains in the suite.\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2` and `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2` from the preserved branch.\\n3. If those pass cleanly, keep the generated Micrometer-specific tests and continue the normal `library-new-request` flow from the preserved branch.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2448#issuecomment-4339041219\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T04:01:42Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2`. Preserved work is available on the preserved branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2448-library-new-request-io.micrometer-micrometer-core-1.8.2-796139b0\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is native test validation during the final test-generation/refinement loop. The preserved branch does contain generated tests, but `build/tests/io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2/ce959c4146d61e859d232d1fe4339e3d.out` shows `> Task :nativeTest FAILED` with 4 failing tests:\\n- `HazelcastIMapAdapterTest.bindsLegacyHazelcastIMapThroughIsolatedPublicCacheBinder()` -> `Expecting not blank but was: null`\\n- `ProcessorMetricsTest.bindsProcessorGaugesAndReadsCpuUsageValues()` -> `Expecting NaN to be finite`\\n- `PropertyValidatorTest.simpleConfigModeResolvesEnumValueIgnoringCase()` -> `NoSuchMethodException: io.micrometer.core.instrument.simple.CountingMode.values()`\\n- `PropertyValidatorTest.getEnumReportsMalformedValueWithAllowedEnumConstants()` -> the same `NoSuchMethodException`\\n\\nThere is also scaffold left behind: the same native test output still prints `This is just a placeholder, implement your test`, and `tests/src/io.micrometer/micrometer-core/1.8.2/src/test/java/io_micrometer/micrometer_core/Micrometer_coreTest.java` is still the placeholder scaffold. Dynamic-access coverage improved to `15/16` (`93.75%`), but `tests/src/io.micrometer/micrometer-core/1.8.2/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` still shows one uncovered call site: `io.micrometer.core.instrument.binder.cache.HazelcastIMapAdapter.resolveOneOf(HazelcastIMapAdapter.java:222)`. The final generation logs also show source-context path errors (`ENOENT`) while reading Micrometer sources, which may have interrupted the last refinement pass.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T03-57-58-812901Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T03-51-49-607788Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2/ce959c4146d61e859d232d1fe4339e3d.out`\\n- `tests/src/io.micrometer/micrometer-core/1.8.2/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Replace/remove the scaffold placeholder in `Micrometer_coreTest` and keep the suite library-specific.\\n2. Fix the 4 native-image test failures above and rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2`.\\n3. Add or refine coverage for `HazelcastIMapAdapter.resolveOneOf(HazelcastIMapAdapter.java:222)`, then rerun `./gradlew generateDynamicAccessReport -Pcoordinates=io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2448#issuecomment-4362871159\"}]}},{\"number\":2425,\"title\":\"Support for org.apache.maven.surefire:surefire-api:2.22.2\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2425\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:09:08Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-02T05:34:30Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.apache.maven.surefire:surefire-api:2.22.2\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T05:34:24Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.apache.maven.surefire:surefire-api:2.22.2`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2425-library-new-request-org.apache.maven.surefire-surefire-api-2.22.2-21b01310\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is `nativeTest`, not initial source discovery. JVM tests passed and the generated coverage reached `60/60`, but `build/tests/org.apache.maven.surefire:surefire-api:2.22.2/a14eb2e7f4cc8475fd360caf8c249cbf.out` ends with `Execution failed for task ':nativeTest'`, and `tests/src/org.apache.maven.surefire/surefire-api/2.22.2/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` reports 3 native failures (2 errors, 1 failure).\\n\\nThe concrete native failures are:\\n1. `SurefireReflectorTest.loadsProviderApiTypesAndCreatesConsoleLoggerDecorator()` and `SurefireReflectorInnerClassLoaderProxyTest.proxyInvokesMatchingPublicMethodOnDelegate()` fail with `org.apache.maven.surefire.util.SurefireReflectionException: java.lang.ClassNotFoundException: org.apache.maven.surefire.report.ReporterConfiguration`.\\n2. `Java7SupportTest.managesSymbolicLinksThroughJava7Support()` fails because `Java7Support.isJava7()` is false at runtime.\\n\\nThe preserved branch already contains generated tests and `metadata/org.apache.maven.surefire/surefire-api/2.22.2/reachability-metadata.json`, but `stats/org.apache.maven.surefire/surefire-api/2.22.2/execution-metrics.json` still records `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, and no recorded test/metadata artifacts, so the metrics/artifact capture also looks inconsistent.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.maven.surefire:surefire-api:2.22.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T05-27-19-983253Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.maven.surefire:surefire-api:2.22.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T05-30-08-188808Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/org.apache.maven.surefire:surefire-api:2.22.2/a14eb2e7f4cc8475fd360caf8c249cbf.out`\\n- `tests/src/org.apache.maven.surefire/surefire-api/2.22.2/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\\n- `stats/org.apache.maven.surefire/surefire-api/2.22.2/execution-metrics.json`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Fix the native-image failures on the preserved branch, likely by adding the missing reachability metadata needed for `ReporterConfiguration` or by narrowing the reflector tests to a native-supported path.\\n2. Make `Java7SupportTest` version-agnostic for the current JDK/GraalVM instead of asserting `Java7Support.isJava7()`.\\n3. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.maven.surefire:surefire-api:2.22.2` and confirm the metrics/artifact record updates correctly.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2425#issuecomment-4363061958\"}]}},{\"number\":2405,\"title\":\"Support for asm:asm:3.1\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2405\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:09:04Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T20:30:51Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nasm:asm:3.1\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T14:19:38Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2405-library-new-request-asm-asm-3.1-438dbebc\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was generated-test validation/handoff, not artifact discovery. `human-intervention-logs/asm:asm:3.1/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` and `human-intervention-logs/asm:asm:3.1/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` completed successfully, and the two PI generation logs show candidate commits were created for `ClassReaderTest` (`a9ad3f43fe`) and `ClassWriterTest` (`7e65474ad7`). However, the run metrics still report failure with 7 iterations, `Generated LOC: 0`, and the same start/end commit (`54b89dd01f072d5783b078553cb9d43c690766b4`), while the checked-out source still contains only the placeholder `tests/src/asm/asm/3.1/src/test/java/asm/asm/AsmTest.java`.\\n\\nThe available Gradle outputs also show why dynamic-access coverage stayed at 0/2. JVM tests passed in `tests/src/asm/asm/3.1/build/test-results/test/TEST-asm.asm.ClassReaderTest.xml` and `tests/src/asm/asm/3.1/build/test-results/test/TEST-asm.asm.ClassWriterTest.xml`, but native-image execution failed in `tests/src/asm/asm/3.1/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` with 2 errors in `ClassWriterTest`: `java.lang.ClassNotFoundException: asm.asm.ClassWriterTestFirstList`. The coverage report at `tests/src/asm/asm/3.1/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` therefore remained at 0/2 uncovered call sites.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/asm:asm:3.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-27T14-05-01-095334Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/asm:asm:3.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-27T14-12-24-077718Z.log`\\n- `tests/src/asm/asm/3.1/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\\n- `tests/src/asm/asm/3.1/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Check out the preserved branch and recover the generated `ClassReaderTest` and `ClassWriterTest` changes into the actual test tree.\\n2. Fix `ClassWriterTest` so its helper classes are reachable under native image, or replace that approach with a native-safe test that still exercises `ClassWriter.getCommonSuperClass(...)`.\\n3. Rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=asm:asm:3.1` and `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=asm:asm:3.1`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2405#issuecomment-4327722358\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T20:30:46Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job for `asm:asm:3.1` failed. Preserved work is available on https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2405-library-new-request-asm-asm-3.1-ba5dfbd6.\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was post-generation test quality / dynamic-access coverage, not artifact discovery. `human-intervention-logs/asm:asm:3.1/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` and `human-intervention-logs/asm:asm:3.1/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` completed successfully, and the generated JVM/native tests also ran successfully (`build/tests/asm:asm:3.1/1742f35eb89b83cf13e53f834dd25653.out` shows 8 native tests successful). However, `tests/src/asm/asm/3.1/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` still reports `0/2` covered calls, and the tracked call sites remain uncovered in `tests/src/asm/asm/3.1/build/native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access/asm-3.1/resource-calls.json` and `tests/src/asm/asm/3.1/build/native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access/asm-3.1/reflection-calls.json`:\\n- `org.objectweb.asm.ClassReader.<init>(Unknown Source)` -> `java.lang.ClassLoader#getSystemResourceAsStream(java.lang.String)`\\n- `org.objectweb.asm.ClassWriter.getCommonSuperClass(Unknown Source)` -> `java.lang.Class#forName(java.lang.String)`\\n\\nThe preserved branch does contain attempted follow-up tests, but it still includes a scaffold placeholder test at `tests/src/asm/asm/3.1/src/test/java/asm/asm/AsmTest.java` (`This is just a placeholder, implement your test`), which is a strong sign the generator did not converge on a fully library-specific submission. The run metrics in `stats/asm/asm/3.1/execution-metrics.json` also recorded failure after 6 iterations with `generated_loc: 0` and `code_coverage_percent: 0.0`. For the iteration history, inspect `human-intervention-logs/asm:asm:3.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T20-11-55-346242Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/asm:asm:3.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T20-19-53-807118Z.log`.\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Start from the preserved branch and replace/remove the scaffold `AsmTest` with real ASM-specific coverage.\\n2. Rework `ClassReaderTest` and `ClassWriterTest` so native execution actually reaches the two tracked call sites above, then rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=asm:asm:3.1`.\\n3. Confirm `tests/src/asm/asm/3.1/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` improves before opening a PR.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2405#issuecomment-4361490186\"}]}},{\"number\":2392,\"title\":\"Support for ant:ant:1.6\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2392\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:08:59Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-02T06:33:44Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nant:ant:1.6\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T01:45:54Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job for `ant:ant:1.6` failed. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2392-library-new-request-ant-ant-1.6-1b59575d\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was generated-test verification in the metadata-fix/post-gen follow-up, not low coverage. The run still reported `195/222` dynamic-access coverage (`87.84%`), but `human-intervention-logs/ant:ant:1.6/metadata-fix/codex.log` shows `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=ant:ant:1.6 --stacktrace` only improved to `81/87` native tests passing, and `human-intervention-logs/ant:ant:1.6/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-04-28T01-38-57-693351Z.log` says 5 generated tests had to be removed because they were failing for non-metadata native-image reasons. After that cleanup, `tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` still shows 1 remaining native error: `ant.ant.RegexpMatcherFactoryTest#createsDefaultJdkMatcherAfterAvailabilityProbe()` with `No supported regular expression matcher found`.\\n\\nThis looks like a remaining metadata/reachability gap in Ant’s legacy regexp factory path. `human-intervention-logs/ant:ant:1.6/metadata-fix/codex.log` shows `RegexpMatcherFactory` reflectively loading `org.apache.tools.ant.util.regexp.Jdk14RegexpMatcher` via `Class.forName(...)`, and the preserved branch already added `Jdk14RegexpMatcher` to both `metadata/ant/ant/1.6/reachability-metadata.json` and `tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/ant-ant-tests/reflect-config.json`, but that was still not enough for the native image to instantiate the default matcher. The main logs to inspect are `human-intervention-logs/ant:ant:1.6/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T01-16-56-985640Z.log`, `human-intervention-logs/ant:ant:1.6/metadata-fix/codex.log`, and `human-intervention-logs/ant:ant:1.6/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-04-28T01-38-57-693351Z.log`.\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Review the preserved branch and keep only the native-safe, library-specific tests; the post-gen report already identifies 5 generated tests that failed for non-metadata reasons.\\n2. Investigate the `RegexpMatcherFactory` / `Jdk14RegexpMatcher` reflective loading path and adjust metadata or test-side native-image config so the default matcher is retained and instantiable in native image.\\n3. Re-run `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=ant:ant:1.6` and `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=ant:ant:1.6` (plus the future-defaults lane if needed).\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2392#issuecomment-4331753423\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T06:33:37Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job for `ant:ant:1.6` failed. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2392-library-new-request-ant-ant-1.6-ab7ca92c\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was post-generation/native validation rather than initial metadata generation. The preserved branch contains generated metadata and tests, and the run reached `199/219` dynamic-access coverage (`90.87%`), but `stats/ant/ant/1.6/execution-metrics.json` still ended with `status: failure`, `tested_library_loc: 0`, and `code_coverage_percent: 0.0`. The clearest reproducer is in `logs/ant:ant:1.6/metadata-fix/codex.log`: `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=ant:ant:1.6` fails in native test `ant.ant.ClassConstantsTest#readInitializesByteArrayParameterTypeInFreshAntClassLoader` with `java.lang.ClassNotFoundException: org.apache.tools.ant.filters.ClassConstants`. The same failure is recorded in `test-results-native/test/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`. That log also notes this is not a `Missing*RegistrationError`, so this does not look like a straightforward metadata-entry gap.\\n\\nThe generation logs also suggest the run never reached a clean validated finish. In `logs/ant:ant:1.6/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T05-57-26-719914Z.log`, the final generation step is still editing tests and explicitly says it did not compile or run tests. `post-gen-interventions/ant_ant_1.6.md` summarizes the likely root cause as an isolated `AntClassLoader`/native runtime classpath issue in the generated `ClassConstantsTest` path, not missing reachability metadata.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `logs/ant:ant:1.6/metadata-fix/codex.log`\\n- `logs/ant:ant:1.6/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T05-57-26-719914Z.log`\\n- `post-gen-interventions/ant_ant_1.6.md`\\n- `test-results-native/test/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Review and adjust the generated `ClassConstantsTest` path that creates an isolated `AntClassLoader`; it appears to rely on runtime classpath loading behavior that does not hold in native.\\n2. Rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=ant:ant:1.6` from the preserved branch after fixing or removing that unsupported test path.\\n3. Only pursue further metadata changes if the rerun surfaces an actual `Missing*RegistrationError`; current evidence points to a test/runtime-classpath issue instead.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2392#issuecomment-4363174840\"}]}},{\"number\":2363,\"title\":\"Support for net.minidev:accessors-smart:1.2\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2363\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:08:46Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-02T04:23:56Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nnet.minidev:accessors-smart:1.2\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"jormundur00\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T07:41:21Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job failed for `net.minidev:accessors-smart:2.4.7`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fjormundur00%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2363-library-new-request-net.minidev-accessors-smart-2.4.7-d294306f\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was generated native test coverage, followed by an unsuccessful metadata-fix rescue. In the final generation pass, the job added `DynamicClassLoaderTest` coverage for `BeansAccess.get(...)` and `DynamicClassLoader.directInstance(...)`, including extra test-only reflection metadata and `--add-opens` settings. The later metadata-fix/post-gen analysis concluded that these tests drive `accessors-smart` into runtime bytecode generation of `*AccAccess` classes, which is not a normal reachability-metadata gap: the predefined-classes workaround did not stabilize because the generated accessor class hashes were not reusable, and Native Image still hit runtime class-definition limits. Metrics also reported dynamic-access coverage as unavailable.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `logs/net.minidev:accessors-smart:2.4.7/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T07-07-02-171544Z.log`\\n- `logs/net.minidev:accessors-smart:2.4.7/metadata-fix/codex.log`\\n- `logs/net.minidev:accessors-smart:2.4.7/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-04-28T07-34-33-919489Z.log`\\n- `post-gen-interventions/net.minidev_accessors-smart_2.4.7.md`\\n\\nSuggested manual next steps:\\n- Decide whether this library should only be supported for the pre-generated accessor path under native image, rather than for runtime-generated accessor classes.\\n- If yes, remove or replace the runtime-codegen tests (`ASMUtilTest`, `AccessorTest`, `BeansAccessBuilderTest`, `DynamicClassLoaderTest`) with coverage that stays on the supported pre-generated path, then rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=net.minidev:accessors-smart:2.4.7`.\\n- If full runtime-codegen support is required, investigate a stable Native Image strategy for `net.minidev.asm.DynamicClassLoader`/predefined classes before reopening automation for this library.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2363#issuecomment-4333271102\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T04:23:50Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `net.minidev:accessors-smart:1.2`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2363-library-new-request-net.minidev-accessors-smart-1.2-58d1e40c\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was `add-new-library-support` orchestration / test-generation bookkeeping, not artifact URL discovery. Both `human-intervention-logs/net.minidev:accessors-smart:1.2/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` and `human-intervention-logs/net.minidev:accessors-smart:1.2/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` completed successfully. In the failing generation loop, `human-intervention-logs/net.minidev:accessors-smart:1.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T04-18-31-508573Z.log` shows a hard error when the run tried to read `local_repositories/source_context/net.minidev/accessors-smart/1.2` and got `No such file or directory` / `Command exited with code 2`.\\n\\nThere is also a mismatch between the preserved work and the recorded metrics. The later generation log `human-intervention-logs/net.minidev:accessors-smart:1.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T04-20-53-749940Z.log` produced `BeansAccessTest`, and the preserved branch contains commit `16d514abb1` (`Dynamic-access coverage for net.minidev.asm.BeansAccess (10/10)`). The generated reports also look good: `tests/src/net.minidev/accessors-smart/1.2/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` reports `10/10` covered calls, and `tests/src/net.minidev/accessors-smart/1.2/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` shows 5 native tests with 0 failures/errors. However, `stats/net.minidev/accessors-smart/1.2/execution-metrics.json` still records `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, and `artifacts.test_file: \\\"None\\\"`, which suggests the run failed while recording or finalizing generated test artifacts after the tests were produced.\\n\\nOne cleanup issue remains in the preserved tests: `tests/src/net.minidev/accessors-smart/1.2/src/test/java/net_minidev/accessors_smart/Accessors_smartTest.java` is still the scaffold placeholder, even though the meaningful coverage appears to be in `AccessorTest`, `DynamicClassLoaderTest`, and `BeansAccessTest`.\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Check out the preserved branch and review the generated tests, especially `AccessorTest`, `DynamicClassLoaderTest`, and `BeansAccessTest`, then remove or replace the scaffold `Accessors_smartTest`.\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=net.minidev:accessors-smart:1.2` on the preserved branch and confirm the native test report and dynamic-access report still stay green at `10/10`.\\n3. Investigate why `add-new-library-support` finalized this run as failed despite generated tests and coverage, starting with `pi-generation-2026-05-02T04-18-31-508573Z.log` and `stats/net.minidev/accessors-smart/1.2/execution-metrics.json`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2363#issuecomment-4362927534\"}]}},{\"number\":2297,\"title\":\"Support for jtidy:jtidy:4aug2000r7-dev\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2297\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:08:34Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-30T07:05:51Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\njtidy:jtidy:4aug2000r7-dev\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"}]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"jormundur00\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T07:05:51Z\",\"body\":\"Lib has no debug metadata.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2297#issuecomment-4350363222\"}]}},{\"number\":2273,\"title\":\"Support for org.codehaus.plexus:plexus-utils:1.0.4\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2273\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:08:30Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T19:11:12Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.codehaus.plexus:plexus-utils:1.0.4\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T19:11:06Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job for `org.codehaus.plexus:plexus-utils:1.0.4` failed. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2273-library-new-request-org.codehaus.plexus-plexus-utils-1.0.4-95a3a2eb\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was post-generation validation. `stats/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-utils/1.0.4/execution-metrics.json` shows the run ended in `failure` after 9 iterations, and the generated coverage report at `tests/src/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-utils/1.0.4/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` stops at `29/30` covered calls (`96.67%`), with one remaining uncovered site at `org.codehaus.plexus.util.reflection.Reflector.getObjectProperty(Reflector.java:474)`. The last preserved generator attempt in `human-intervention-logs/org.codehaus.plexus:plexus-utils:1.0.4/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T19-07-18-263601Z.log` focused on `ReflectionValueExtractor` and produced `ReflectionValueExtractorTest`, so the run appears to have stalled before closing the final `Reflector` path.\\n\\nThere is also concrete native-test failure evidence to inspect. `build/tests/org.codehaus.plexus:plexus-utils:1.0.4/8ec917e6e7bcc2e60441c855f6fa05fd.out` and `tests/src/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-utils/1.0.4/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` show `nativeTest` failed with 3 tests: `ClassMapTest` has 2 assertion failures (`getPublicMethod`/`findMethod` returned `null` under native), and `FastMapTest` fails with `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` for reflective access to `java.lang.String.serialVersionUID`. The generated test set also still contains a scaffold placeholder in `tests/src/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-utils/1.0.4/src/test/java/org_codehaus_plexus/plexus_utils/Plexus_utilsTest.java`.\\n\\nSuggested manual next steps:\\n1. Fix or replace the failing generated tests (`ClassMapTest`, `FastMapTest`) and remove the scaffold placeholder test.\\n2. Add coverage for `Reflector.getObjectProperty(...)` and rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.codehaus.plexus:plexus-utils:1.0.4`.\\n3. If the `FastMap` serialization scenario is kept, add the needed metadata for the reflective serialization path or rewrite the test to avoid it.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2273#issuecomment-4361128404\"}]}},{\"number\":2258,\"title\":\"Support for org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-websocket:9.0.83\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2258\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:08:29Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T22:01:40Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-websocket:9.0.83\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T16:50:53Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-websocket:9.0.83`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2258-library-new-request-org.apache.tomcat.embed-tomcat-embed-websocket-9.0.83-f4e4d2b1\\n\\nMost likely failing stage: final dynamic-access coverage generation. After 16 iterations, the generated test project was building and both JVM and native tests were passing, but metrics still stopped at `30/31` covered calls (`96.77%`). The only remaining uncovered call is `java.lang.reflect.Constructor#newInstance(...)` from `javax.websocket.server.ServerEndpointConfig$Configurator.loadDefault(ServerEndpointConfig.java:184)`, visible in `tests/src/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-websocket/9.0.83/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`.\\n\\nThe last generation attempts focused on that exact fallback path and added `ServerEndpointConfigInnerConfiguratorTest` plus `tests/src/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-websocket/9.0.83/src/test/resources/junit-platform.properties` to force class-name ordering, because the logs conclude the call is only reachable before the static default configurator cache is initialized. See `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-websocket:9.0.83/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T16-40-17-721982Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-websocket:9.0.83/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T16-43-16-124216Z.log`. However, the native test report still shows `WsWebSocketContainerTest` running before `ServerEndpointConfigInnerConfiguratorTest`, so that ordering tweak did not take effect under native and the last call site remained uncovered: `tests/src/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-websocket/9.0.83/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`.\\n\\nThere is also still a scaffold placeholder test in `tests/src/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-websocket/9.0.83/src/test/java/org_apache_tomcat_embed/tomcat_embed_websocket/Tomcat_embed_websocketTest.java`, and its output is visible in `build/tests/org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-websocket:9.0.83/1fe55195eb48792453f8b4259deae6b5.out`.\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. On the preserved branch, make the `ServerEndpointConfig.Configurator.loadDefault()` fallback test deterministic under native image without relying on JUnit class ordering being honored.\\n2. Re-run the target coordinate and confirm the dynamic-access report reaches `31/31`.\\n3. Replace or remove the scaffold placeholder `Tomcat_embed_websocketTest` before opening a PR.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2258#issuecomment-4337355440\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T22:01:34Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-websocket:9.0.83`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2258-library-new-request-org.apache.tomcat.embed-tomcat-embed-websocket-9.0.83-1d052c0c\\n\\nMost likely the failure was in the dynamic-access test-generation/coverage completion stage, not in basic Gradle validation. The generated JVM and native test reports under `tests/src/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-websocket/9.0.83/build/test-results/` show 0 failures, but the final dynamic-access report still ends at 30/31 covered calls (96.77%). The one remaining uncovered call is `java.lang.reflect.Constructor#newInstance(Object[])` from `javax.websocket.server.ServerEndpointConfig$Configurator.loadDefault(ServerEndpointConfig.java:184)` in `tests/src/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-websocket/9.0.83/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`. The run metrics also ended in failure after 15 iterations in `stats/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-websocket/9.0.83/execution-metrics.json`.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-websocket:9.0.83/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T21-58-26-248743Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-websocket:9.0.83/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T21-50-35-604888Z.log`\\n- `tests/src/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-websocket/9.0.83/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Add or adjust a test that exercises the default `ServerEndpointConfig.Configurator` loading path so `loadDefault()` is actually reached under native-image tracking.\\n2. Rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-websocket:9.0.83` and confirm the dynamic-access report reaches 31/31.\\n3. If that passes, continue from the preserved branch and push the follow-up there.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2258#issuecomment-4361846043\"}]}},{\"number\":2261,\"title\":\"Support for ch.qos.reload4j:reload4j:1.2.19\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2261\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:08:29Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T20:57:48Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nch.qos.reload4j:reload4j:1.2.19\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T23:01:42Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `ch.qos.reload4j:reload4j:1.2.19`. Preserved work is available on branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2261-library-new-request-ch.qos.reload4j-reload4j-1.2.19-7b667af6\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is the metadata-fix/native test phase after generation, not initial scaffolding. The generated suite achieved `62/65` dynamic-access coverage (`95.38%`), with only `org.apache.log4j.net.ZeroConfSupport` still partially uncovered (`10/13`) in `tests/src/ch.qos.reload4j/reload4j/1.2.19/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`. However, native execution still fails in reload4j socket event deserialization: `SocketAppenderTest.sendsSerializedLoggingEventToSocketServer()` and `SocketHubAppenderTest.broadcastsSerializedLoggingEventToConnectedClient()` fail with `java.io.InvalidClassException: java.util.Hashtable; no valid constructor`, rooted in `org.apache.log4j.spi.LoggingEvent.readObject`, as shown in `tests/src/ch.qos.reload4j/reload4j/1.2.19/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`.\\n\\nThe preserved post-gen report also shows two non-metadata failures were already removed from the generated suite: `SocketHubAppenderInnerServerMonitorTest` (`SocketTimeoutException`) and `ZeroConfSupportTest` (`NullPointerException`). The remaining blocker is the socket serialization path. The metadata-fix loop in `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.reload4j:reload4j:1.2.19/metadata-fix/codex.log` repeatedly uncovered additional JDK serialization requirements around `java.util.Hashtable`, `java.lang.Object`, `java.lang.String.serialVersionUID`, and `java.lang.Exception.serialVersionUID`, but still ended in `BUILD FAILED`.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.reload4j:reload4j:1.2.19/metadata-fix/codex.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.reload4j:reload4j:1.2.19/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-04-27T22-57-09-527969Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/ch.qos.reload4j:reload4j:1.2.19/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-27T22-35-02-719864Z.log`\\n- `tests/src/ch.qos.reload4j/reload4j/1.2.19/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\\n- `tests/src/ch.qos.reload4j/reload4j/1.2.19/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Reproduce `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=ch.qos.reload4j:reload4j:1.2.19 --stacktrace` on the preserved branch and focus on the socket serialization tests.\\n2. Decide whether to complete the missing JDK serialization/deserialization metadata for `LoggingEvent`/`Hashtable`, or to replace the current socket tests with a narrower assertion that avoids this unstable serialization chain.\\n3. Re-run both default and `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all` test lanes for this coordinate after the manual fix.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2261#issuecomment-4331087910\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T20:57:41Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `ch.qos.reload4j:reload4j:1.2.19`. Preserved work is available here: `https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2261-library-new-request-ch.qos.reload4j-reload4j-1.2.19-c6e032e7`.\\n\\nThe failure appears to be in the post-generation native test / metadata-fix stage, not in initial coverage generation. `stats/ch.qos.reload4j/reload4j/1.2.19/execution-metrics.json` shows the run reached 25 iterations, generated 1592 LOC, and achieved dynamic-access coverage `65/65 (100%)`, but still ended with status `failure`. `logs/ch.qos.reload4j:reload4j:1.2.19/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-05-01T20-54-02-948118Z.log` records `Stage: metadata_fix_failed`, and the preserved Gradle output in `build/tests/ch.qos.reload4j:reload4j:1.2.19/5ce5568916c199c7a2155d4be884d971.out` shows the remaining native failure is `MDCKeySetExtractorTest.returnsPropertyKeysThroughLegacySerializationFallback()`, which hits `org.graalvm.nativeimage.MissingReflectionRegistrationError: Cannot reflectively invoke constructor 'public java.lang.Object()'` from the generated `ReflectionFactory.newConstructorForSerialization(...)` path. `logs/ch.qos.reload4j:reload4j:1.2.19/metadata-fix/codex.log` also notes that adding `sun.reflect.ReflectionFactory` and `java.lang.Object` metadata did not clear this failure.\\n\\nThere were earlier generated-test issues as well: the post-gen log notes isolated class-loading behavior in `EnhancedThrowableRendererTest` and `SocketHubAppender` monitor-thread shutdown exceptions, but those were treated as non-metadata test problems. The remaining blocker is the legacy serialization fallback exercised by `tests/src/ch.qos.reload4j/reload4j/1.2.19/src/test/java/ch_qos_reload4j/reload4j/MDCKeySetExtractorTest.java`.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n1. `logs/ch.qos.reload4j:reload4j:1.2.19/metadata-fix/codex.log`\\n2. `logs/ch.qos.reload4j:reload4j:1.2.19/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-05-01T20-54-02-948118Z.log`\\n3. `build/tests/ch.qos.reload4j:reload4j:1.2.19/5ce5568916c199c7a2155d4be884d971.out`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Reproduce with `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=ch.qos.reload4j:reload4j:1.2.19` on the preserved branch and inspect the generated `MDCKeySetExtractorTest` legacy serialization path.\\n2. Decide whether that `ReflectionFactory`-based fallback should be supported with different metadata/conditions, or whether the generated test should be rewritten/removed as not representative of intended native-image support.\\n3. Rerun the targeted library test after resolving that path, while keeping the earlier post-gen cleanup for the non-metadata test failures.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2261#issuecomment-4361609807\"}]}},{\"number\":2237,\"title\":\"Support for com.google.collections:google-collections:1.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2237\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:08:26Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-02T02:19:16Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\ncom.google.collections:google-collections:1.0\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T02:19:08Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job failed for `com.google.collections:google-collections:1.0`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2237-library-new-request-com.google.collections-google-collections-1.0-d7104333\\n\\nMost likely failing stage: test generation / stabilization. The run exhausted 25 iterations but never produced accepted artifacts: `stats/com.google.collections/google-collections/1.0/execution-metrics.json` ends with `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, `metadata_entries: 0`, and both `test_file` / `metadata_file` set to `None`. An earlier generation attempt also failed on the generated JVM test itself: `human-intervention-logs/com.google.collections:google-collections:1.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T01-24-24-488732Z.log` shows `FinalizableReferenceQueueInnerDecoupledLoaderTest` failing with `java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException: Setting a Security Manager is not supported`.\\n\\nThere is also evidence that later generated tests were still not viable under native image. `build/tests/com.google.collections:google-collections:1.0/bf0e9c7530122dfc7e0f83c6488724d8.out` shows 31 `nativeTest` failures, including `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` for `java.lang.Object.<init>()`, multiple `InvalidClassException ... no valid constructor` deserialization failures, and `NoSuchMethodException` around `com.google.common.base.internal.Finalizer.startFinalizer(...)`. The final generation log, `human-intervention-logs/com.google.collections:google-collections:1.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T02-14-01-328452Z.log`, shows follow-up edits were attempted, but the metadata file still was not recognized as a tracked artifact: `git ls-files --error-unmatch metadata/com.google.collections/google-collections/1.0/reachability-metadata.json` returned `pathspec ... did not match any file(s) known to git`. Dynamic-access coverage was reported as 97/97 (100%), but that did not result in a passing or finalized submission.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.google.collections:google-collections:1.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T01-24-24-488732Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.google.collections:google-collections:1.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T02-14-01-328452Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/com.google.collections:google-collections:1.0/bf0e9c7530122dfc7e0f83c6488724d8.out`\\n- `tests/src/com.google.collections/google-collections/1.0/`\\n- `metadata/com.google.collections/google-collections/1.0/reachability-metadata.json`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Review and trim/fix the generated tests in `tests/src/com.google.collections/google-collections/1.0`, especially the `FinalizableReferenceQueue*` and serialization-heavy tests, so they pass on the current JDK/native-image toolchain.\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=com.google.collections:google-collections:1.0` and use `build/tests/com.google.collections:google-collections:1.0/*.out` to verify the remaining native-image failures.\\n3. Make sure the metadata/test artifacts on the preserved branch are actually tracked and finalized, especially `metadata/com.google.collections/google-collections/1.0/reachability-metadata.json`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2237#issuecomment-4362650139\"}]}},{\"number\":2236,\"title\":\"Support for com.jcraft:jsch:0.1.27\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2236\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:08:26Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-02T02:43:42Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\ncom.jcraft:jsch:0.1.27\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T21:47:54Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `com.jcraft:jsch:0.1.27`. Preserved work is available on branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2236-library-new-request-com.jcraft-jsch-0.1.27-04accb2c\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was test generation, not artifact URL discovery. The preserved logs show both discovery steps completed successfully (`:populateArtifactURLs` and `:discoverArtifactMetadata`), and `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/com.jcraft-jsch-0.1.27.json` was populated. However, the generated test project still contains only the scaffold placeholder in `tests/src/com.jcraft/jsch/0.1.27/src/test/java/com_jcraft/jsch/JschTest.java` (`This is just a placeholder, implement your test`), so no library-specific test was produced. There is also no `stats/com.jcraft/jsch/0.1.27/stats.json`, which matches the unavailable dynamic-access coverage.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.jcraft:jsch:0.1.27/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.jcraft:jsch:0.1.27/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n- `tests/src/com.jcraft/jsch/0.1.27/src/test/java/com_jcraft/jsch/JschTest.java`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Replace the scaffold `JschTest` with a real `jsch`-specific test that exercises behavior under native image.\\n2. Run the library workflow locally for `com.jcraft:jsch:0.1.27` to regenerate metadata/stats and confirm the test passes.\\n3. Update the preserved branch with the completed test and any resulting metadata or stats files.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2236#issuecomment-4330659128\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T02:43:34Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `com.jcraft:jsch:0.1.27`. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2236-library-new-request-com.jcraft-jsch-0.1.27-cdd9c3bf\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was the add-new-library-support test-generation/coverage finalization, not artifact discovery. The preserved branch contains generated `metadata/com.jcraft/jsch/0.1.27/reachability-metadata.json` and `tests/src/com.jcraft/jsch/0.1.27/src/test/java/com_jcraft/jsch/IdentityFileTest.java`, and the saved JVM/native outputs are successful (`build/tests/com.jcraft:jsch:0.1.27/9450f0e02be4d8e54a65920864eea773.out`, `build/tests/com.jcraft:jsch:0.1.27/1b8a589df1d4d0df26d166ecd2a40b3d.out`, plus `tests/src/com.jcraft/jsch/0.1.27/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`). However, `stats/com.jcraft/jsch/0.1.27/execution-metrics.json` still records `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, `metadata_entries: 0`, and artifacts `None`, and `tests/src/com.jcraft/jsch/0.1.27/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` reports `hasDynamicAccess: false` with `0/0` calls even though the generation log targeted 6 uncovered `IdentityFile` reflection call sites.\\n\\nThe generation log also shows the agent diagnosing a coverage-attribution problem: it noted that the published JSch classes do not expose line numbers to JaCoCo, so executed dynamic-access calls could not be marked covered, and it experimented with a `build.gradle` workaround that was not preserved in the final branch snapshot. Please inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.jcraft:jsch:0.1.27/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T02-29-44-226937Z.log`\\n- `stats/com.jcraft/jsch/0.1.27/execution-metrics.json`\\n- `tests/src/com.jcraft/jsch/0.1.27/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n- `build/tests/com.jcraft:jsch:0.1.27/9450f0e02be4d8e54a65920864eea773.out`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Review the preserved `IdentityFileTest` and `reachability-metadata.json` on the preserved branch and decide whether to cherry-pick them.\\n2. Re-run generation/validation from that branch and determine whether the source-jar/line-number workaround from the generation log needs to be applied so coverage can be attributed correctly.\\n3. Regenerate stats/metrics after the rerun and confirm `stats/com.jcraft/jsch/0.1.27/execution-metrics.json` no longer reports zero generated artifacts.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2236#issuecomment-4362707014\"}]}},{\"number\":2217,\"title\":\"Support for org.codehaus.jsr166-mirror:jsr166y:1.7.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2217\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:08:19Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-27T23:32:02Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.codehaus.jsr166-mirror:jsr166y:1.7.0\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T23:31:56Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.codehaus.jsr166-mirror:jsr166y:1.7.0`. Preserved work is available on branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2217-library-new-request-org.codehaus.jsr166-mirror-jsr166y-1.7.0-25f29255\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is test generation. Artifact URL discovery and artifact metadata discovery appear to have completed successfully (`human-intervention-logs/org.codehaus.jsr166-mirror:jsr166y:1.7.0/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` and `human-intervention-logs/org.codehaus.jsr166-mirror:jsr166y:1.7.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` produced the metadata inputs, and `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/org.codehaus.jsr166-mirror-jsr166y-1.7.0.json` exists), but the generated test is still only the scaffold placeholder: `tests/src/org.codehaus.jsr166-mirror/jsr166y/1.7.0/src/test/java/org_codehaus_jsr166_mirror/jsr166y/Jsr166yTest.java` contains `System.out.println(\\\"This is just a placeholder, implement your test\\\");`. The generated metadata is also empty (`metadata/org.codehaus.jsr166-mirror/jsr166y/1.7.0/reachability-metadata.json` is `{}`), and no target `stats/org.codehaus.jsr166-mirror/jsr166y/1.7.0/stats.json` was produced, which matches the unavailable dynamic-access coverage.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.codehaus.jsr166-mirror:jsr166y:1.7.0/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.codehaus.jsr166-mirror:jsr166y:1.7.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n- `tests/src/org.codehaus.jsr166-mirror/jsr166y/1.7.0/src/test/java/org_codehaus_jsr166_mirror/jsr166y/Jsr166yTest.java`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Replace the scaffold test with a library-specific test that exercises real `jsr166y` behavior under native image.\\n2. Regenerate or hand-author any required reachability metadata if that test exposes dynamic access.\\n3. Rerun the library validation for `org.codehaus.jsr166-mirror:jsr166y:1.7.0` and confirm a target `stats.json` is produced.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2217#issuecomment-4331233010\"}]}},{\"number\":2215,\"title\":\"Support for org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-dom-api-compat:2.3.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2215\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:08:14Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-27T23:35:38Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-dom-api-compat:2.3.0\\n\\n### Library source code URL\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n### Link to the existing test suite\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\\n\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"github-actions\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:09:32Z\",\"body\":\"Automation: No dependency issues were created by the triage workflow.\\n\\nThis typically means every dependency in the deps.dev expansion is already supported by the repository.\\n\\nPlan nodes:\\n```\\norg.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-dom-api-compat:2.3.0\\norg.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib:2.3.0\\norg.jetbrains:annotations:13.0\\n```\\n\\nSupported GA detected during checks:\\n```\\norg.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib\\norg.jetbrains:annotations\\n```\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2215#issuecomment-4326468422\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T23:35:32Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-dom-api-compat:2.3.0`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2215-library-new-request-org.jetbrains.kotlin-kotlin-dom-api-compat-2.3.0-45c2cfb7\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is test generation after artifact discovery. The preserved log at `logs/org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-dom-api-compat:2.3.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` shows `:discoverArtifactMetadata` completed successfully and the agent exited with code 0 after writing discovered artifact metadata for this coordinate, but there are no generated files for this library under `metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-dom-api-compat`, `tests/src/...`, or `stats/...`, and dynamic-access coverage is unavailable because no stats were produced. On the preserved branch, the only committed change is the discovery log, which further suggests the pipeline failed before any test sources or metadata were generated.\\n\\nPlease inspect `logs/org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-dom-api-compat:2.3.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` and `build/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.jetbrains.kotlin-kotlin-dom-api-compat-2.3.0.log` on the preserved branch to confirm what inputs were handed off to generation.\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Verify that the discovered source, test, and documentation locations for `kotlin-dom-api-compat:2.3.0` are correct and usable for generating a library-specific test.\\n2. Re-run or debug the test-generation step for this coordinate to capture the actual generation error, since discovery itself succeeded.\\n3. If generation still cannot produce a test, add a hand-written Kotlin/JS test and the corresponding metadata for this library version.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2215#issuecomment-4331250438\"}]}},{\"number\":2199,\"title\":\"Support for org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm:1.9.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2199\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:07:56Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-27T23:42:28Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm:1.9.0\\n\\n### Library source code URL\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n### Link to the existing test suite\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\\n\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T23:42:22Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm:1.9.0`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2199-library-new-request-org.jetbrains.kotlinx-kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm-1.9.0-10ab1aaa\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is test generation, not artifact URL/metadata discovery. Both preserved logs for `logs/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm:1.9.0/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` and `logs/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm:1.9.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` end successfully; the discovery log also records `Ran agent for org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm:1.9.0 (exit 0)` and `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`. However, the preserved branch still contains only a scaffold test at `tests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm/1.9.0/src/test/kotlin/org_jetbrains_kotlinx/kotlinx_serialization_json_jvm/Kotlinx_serialization_json_jvmTest.kt` with `println(\\\"This is just a placeholder, implement your test\\\")`, while `metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm/1.9.0/reachability-metadata.json` is still `{}`.\\n\\nThere is also no generated stats file for this coordinate under `stats/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm/1.9.0/`, and the scratch run-metrics repo for this run does not contain a metrics entry for this library, which matches the reported `dynamic-access coverage: unavailable` and suggests the workflow stopped before meaningful test execution/coverage collection.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `logs/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm:1.9.0/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\\n- `logs/org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm:1.9.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`\\n- `tests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm/1.9.0/src/test/kotlin/org_jetbrains_kotlinx/kotlinx_serialization_json_jvm/Kotlinx_serialization_json_jvmTest.kt`\\n- `metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm/1.9.0/reachability-metadata.json`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n- Replace the scaffold test with a real Kotlin/JVM test that exercises `kotlinx.serialization.json` behavior under native image.\\n- Re-run the library validation/test pipeline for `org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm:1.9.0` to generate stats and dynamic-access coverage.\\n- If native-image failures then surface missing metadata, update `metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-json-jvm/1.9.0/reachability-metadata.json` accordingly and rerun.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2199#issuecomment-4331276855\"}]}},{\"number\":2197,\"title\":\"Support for org.apache.httpcomponents.core5:httpcore5:5.2\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2197\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:07:53Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-28T00:13:39Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.apache.httpcomponents.core5:httpcore5:5.2\\n\\n### Library source code URL\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n### Link to the existing test suite\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\\n\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"github-actions\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:09:11Z\",\"body\":\"Automation: No dependency issues were created by the triage workflow.\\n\\nThis typically means every dependency in the deps.dev expansion is already supported by the repository.\\n\\nPlan nodes:\\n```\\norg.apache.httpcomponents.core5:httpcore5:5.3.4\\n```\\n\\nSupported GA detected during checks:\\n```\\n(none)\\n```\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2197#issuecomment-4326466446\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T00:13:34Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.apache.httpcomponents.core5:httpcore5:5.2`, even though the generated metrics reached `6/6` dynamic-access coverage in `stats/org.apache.httpcomponents.core5/httpcore5/5.2/stats.json`. The most likely failing stage was native validation in the add-new-library-support flow: `build/tests/org.apache.httpcomponents.core5:httpcore5:5.2/94d6636fffa2d5867fa25cbf296e21da.out` shows `:nativeTest FAILED`, with both `SerializableEntityTest` cases failing on `UnsupportedFeatureError: SerializationConstructorAccessor class not found for declaringClass: java.lang.String`, which points to missing serialization metadata that the coverage stats did not catch.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2197-library-new-request-org.apache.httpcomponents.core5-httpcore5-5.2-fb6e6338\\n\\nThe preserved branch already contains a follow-up preservation commit that adds the missing `java.lang.String` serialization/reflection entry and a `resources` entry for `org/apache/hc/core5/version.properties`, and updates `VersionInfoTest` to read the real library resource. The main logs to inspect are `logs/org.apache.httpcomponents.core5:httpcore5:5.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-27T23-48-29-820329Z.log`, `logs/org.apache.httpcomponents.core5:httpcore5:5.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-27T23-50-20-994411Z.log`, `logs/org.apache.httpcomponents.core5:httpcore5:5.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-27T23-53-13-817531Z.log`, and `logs/org.apache.httpcomponents.core5:httpcore5:5.2/metadata-fix/codex.log`; the latter shows the follow-up verification passing for both the default lane and `future-defaults-all`.\\n\\n1. Review the preserved branch diff, especially `metadata/org.apache.httpcomponents.core5/httpcore5/5.2/reachability-metadata.json` and `tests/src/org.apache.httpcomponents.core5/httpcore5/5.2/src/test/java/org_apache_httpcomponents_core5/httpcore5/VersionInfoTest.java`.\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.httpcomponents.core5:httpcore5:5.2` and `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.httpcomponents.core5:httpcore5:5.2` from that branch.\\n3. If those stay green, use the preserved branch as the basis for the PR/update.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2197#issuecomment-4331394796\"}]}},{\"number\":2193,\"title\":\"Support for org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-js:2.3.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2193\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:07:46Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-27T23:46:24Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-js:2.3.0\\n\\n### Library source code URL\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n### Link to the existing test suite\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\\n\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"github-actions\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:09:01Z\",\"body\":\"Automation: No dependency issues were created by the triage workflow.\\n\\nThis typically means every dependency in the deps.dev expansion is already supported by the repository.\\n\\nPlan nodes:\\n```\\norg.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-js:2.3.0\\n```\\n\\nSupported GA detected during checks:\\n```\\n(none)\\n```\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2193#issuecomment-4326465460\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T23:46:18Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job for `org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-js:2.3.0` failed. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2193-library-new-request-org.jetbrains.kotlin-kotlin-stdlib-js-2.3.0-c8a5ebfd\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was test generation/scaffolding after artifact metadata discovery completed successfully. In `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-js:2.3.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`, the discovery step finishes with `Ran agent for org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-js:2.3.0 (exit 0)`, and the run produced `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlin-kotlin-stdlib-js-2.3.0.json`. However, there is no generated `tests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-stdlib-js/2.3.0`, no `metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-stdlib-js/...`, and no `stats/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-stdlib-js/...`, and dynamic-access coverage/metrics are unavailable. The same discovery log shows the artifact is packaged as `klib`, so this Kotlin/JS coordinate likely needs non-standard handling during scaffold/test generation.\\n\\nPlease inspect `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-js:2.3.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` first, then `build/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/org.jetbrains.kotlin-kotlin-stdlib-js-2.3.0.log` and `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlin-kotlin-stdlib-js-2.3.0.json` if they are still present in the worktree.\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Confirm whether `org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-js:2.3.0` is expected to be supported by the new-library generator for Kotlin/JS `klib` artifacts.\\n2. If it is supported, manually scaffold the test project under `tests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-stdlib-js/2.3.0` and add the corresponding `metadata/` and `stats/` entries.\\n3. If it is not supported, document that limitation for this coordinate or update automation to reject/route `klib` artifacts earlier.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2193#issuecomment-4331292450\"}]}},{\"number\":2181,\"title\":\"Support for org.slf4j:slf4j-log4j12:1.6.1\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2181\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:07:26Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-02T03:44:23Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.slf4j:slf4j-log4j12:1.6.1\\n\\n### Library source code URL\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n### Link to the existing test suite\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\\n\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"github-actions\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:08:48Z\",\"body\":\"Automation: No dependency issues were created by the triage workflow.\\n\\nThis typically means every dependency in the deps.dev expansion is already supported by the repository.\\n\\nPlan nodes:\\n```\\norg.slf4j:slf4j-log4j12:1.7.25\\nlog4j:log4j:1.2.17\\norg.slf4j:slf4j-api:1.7.25\\norg.apache.openejb:javaee-api:5.0-2\\n```\\n\\nSupported GA detected during checks:\\n```\\nlog4j:log4j\\norg.apache.openejb:javaee-api\\n```\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2181#issuecomment-4326464235\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-02T03:44:18Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.slf4j:slf4j-log4j12:1.6.1`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2181-library-new-request-org.slf4j-slf4j-log4j12-1.6.1-684d00b0\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was `add-new-library-support` during generated test validation/native execution, not artifact discovery. Both `human-intervention-logs/org.slf4j:slf4j-log4j12:1.6.1/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` and `human-intervention-logs/org.slf4j:slf4j-log4j12:1.6.1/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` end successfully, but the preserved generated tests still contain a scaffold placeholder and the native test results fail. `tests/src/org.slf4j/slf4j-log4j12/1.6.1/src/test/java/org_slf4j/slf4j_log4j12/Slf4j_log4j12Test.java` still prints `This is just a placeholder, implement your test`, and the same output appears in `tests/src/org.slf4j/slf4j-log4j12/1.6.1/build/test-results/test/TEST-org_slf4j.slf4j_log4j12.Slf4j_log4j12Test.xml`. Native results in `tests/src/org.slf4j/slf4j-log4j12/1.6.1/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` show `Log4jLoggerAdapterTest` failing with `NoClassDefFoundError: org.slf4j.LoggerFactory` and `ClassCastException: org.slf4j.helpers.NOPLogger cannot be cast to org.slf4j.spi.LocationAwareLogger`. The metrics file also records a failed run with no accepted generated artifacts despite 4/4 dynamic-access coverage: `stats/org.slf4j/slf4j-log4j12/1.6.1/execution-metrics.json`.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.slf4j:slf4j-log4j12:1.6.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T03-35-54-722761Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.slf4j:slf4j-log4j12:1.6.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T03-38-37-574866Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.slf4j:slf4j-log4j12:1.6.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T03-41-14-581014Z.log`\\n- `tests/src/org.slf4j/slf4j-log4j12/1.6.1/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\\n- `tests/src/org.slf4j/slf4j-log4j12/1.6.1/src/test/java/org_slf4j/slf4j_log4j12/Slf4j_log4j12Test.java`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Replace the remaining scaffold `Slf4j_log4j12Test` with a real library-specific test or remove it if redundant.\\n2. Fix `Log4jLoggerAdapterTest` so it passes under native image without falling back to `NOPLogger` / `NoClassDefFoundError`.\\n3. Re-run `checkMetadataFiles` and `test` for `org.slf4j:slf4j-log4j12:1.6.1`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2181#issuecomment-4362838878\"}]}},{\"number\":2158,\"title\":\"Support for org.scala-lang:scala-library:2.11.8\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2158\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:06:49Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T23:52:44Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.scala-lang:scala-library:2.11.8\\n\\n### Library source code URL\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n### Link to the existing test suite\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\\n\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"github-actions\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:08:02Z\",\"body\":\"Automation: No dependency issues were created by the triage workflow.\\n\\nThis typically means every dependency in the deps.dev expansion is already supported by the repository.\\n\\nPlan nodes:\\n```\\norg.scala-lang:scala-library:2.11.12\\n```\\n\\nSupported GA detected during checks:\\n```\\n(none)\\n```\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2158#issuecomment-4326459307\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T23:52:37Z\",\"body\":\"### Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job for `org.scala-lang:scala-library:2.11.8` failed. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2158-library-new-request-org.scala-lang-scala-library-2.11.8-23ad6dae\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is post-generation metadata fixing / native validation, not initial test generation. The generated dynamic-access report still reached 52/64 call sites (81.25%), but `post-gen-interventions/org.scala-lang_scala-library_2.11.8.md` records `Stage: metadata_fix_failed`, and `logs/org.scala-lang:scala-library:2.11.8/metadata-fix/codex.log` plus `tests/src/org.scala-lang/scala-library/2.11.8/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` show 4 remaining native failures. Three are serialization/deserialization gaps: `StreamInnerSerializationProxyTest` and both `TrieMapTest` cases fail with `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` for `java.lang.Object.<init>()` during `ObjectInputStream` deserialization. The remaining `LambdaDeserializerTest` fails with `java.io.InvalidObjectException: ReflectiveOperationException during deserialization` from `SerializedLambda.readResolve`. There is also a likely version-mismatch complication: `tests/src/org.scala-lang/scala-library/2.11.8/build.gradle` pulls `org.scala-lang:scala-library:2.13.16` and `scala-compiler:2.13.16` in the generated test project even though the requested coordinate is `2.11.8`.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `logs/org.scala-lang:scala-library:2.11.8/metadata-fix/codex.log`\\n- `logs/org.scala-lang:scala-library:2.11.8/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-05-01T23-48-26-215783Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.scala-lang:scala-library:2.11.8/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T23-25-58-805050Z.log`\\n- `tests/src/org.scala-lang/scala-library/2.11.8/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\\n- `tests/src/org.scala-lang/scala-library/2.11.8/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Reproduce on the preserved branch with `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.scala-lang:scala-library:2.11.8` and confirm the 4 native failures.\\n2. Fix the remaining serialization metadata gaps for `Stream` / `TrieMap` and the serializable-lambda deserialization path, then rerun native validation.\\n3. Verify whether the generated test project should depend on Scala `2.13.16`; if not, align it with `2.11.8` and rerun generation/validation.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2158#issuecomment-4362194925\"}]}},{\"number\":2155,\"title\":\"Support for org.junit.jupiter:junit-jupiter-api:5.8.2\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2155\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T11:06:44Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-30T04:47:40Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.junit.jupiter:junit-jupiter-api:5.8.2\\n\\n### Library source code URL\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n### Link to the existing test suite\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\\n\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T04:47:34Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.junit.jupiter:junit-jupiter-api:5.8.2`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2155-library-new-request-org.junit.jupiter-junit-jupiter-api-5.8.2-7fc27d8f\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was `nativeTest` after test generation. The generation log shows the agent created and committed a dedicated `JRETest` attempt (`e70f304299 Add JRE dynamic access coverage test`) to cover the remaining reflective call in `org.junit.jupiter.api.condition.JRE`, and the dynamic-access report reached 1/1 coverage, but the native test run then failed with `org_junit_jupiter.junit_jupiter_api.condition.JRETest > currentVersionMatchesRuntimeMajorVersion() FAILED` and `expected: OTHER but was: null` in `build/tests/org.junit.jupiter:junit-jupiter-api:5.8.2/22148a26f63a0d013b5eaf7d77866a19.out`. The metrics file still records `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, and `artifacts.test_file: None`, so the preserved branch mainly contains logs/metadata rather than the generated test sources.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.junit.jupiter:junit-jupiter-api:5.8.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T04-45-07-460882Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/org.junit.jupiter:junit-jupiter-api:5.8.2/22148a26f63a0d013b5eaf7d77866a19.out`\\n- `stats/org.junit.jupiter/junit-jupiter-api/5.8.2/execution-metrics.json`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Recreate/adapt the attempted `JRETest` from the generation log and handle native-image behavior where `JRE.currentVersion()` can be `null` instead of `OTHER`.\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.junit.jupiter:junit-jupiter-api:5.8.2` and confirm both JVM tests and `nativeTest` pass.\\n3. If that test approach is not viable, replace the scaffold-only placeholder with a different library-specific native test that still exercises `org.junit.jupiter.api.condition.JRE.determineCurrentVersion()`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/2155#issuecomment-4349755053\"}]}},{\"number\":1559,\"title\":\"Support for org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1559\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-26T14:38:19Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-28T08:59:10Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20\\n\\n### Library source code URL\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n### Link to the existing test suite\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"github-actions\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-26T14:39:40Z\",\"body\":\"Automation: No dependency issues were created by the triage workflow.\\n\\nThis typically means every dependency in the deps.dev expansion is already supported by the repository or listed in metadata/library-and-framework-list.json.\\n\\nPlan nodes:\\n```\\norg.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20\\n```\\n\\nSupported GA detected during checks:\\n```\\n(none)\\n```\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1559#issuecomment-4135498364\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-11T21:38:00Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nAutomation completed for `org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20`, but dynamic-access coverage remains `0/24` (0.00%). This suggests the generated tests are not exercising the required dynamic-access paths well enough.\\n\\nRecommended manual follow-up:\\n- Inspect the generated tests and compare them with the dynamic-access report to find uncovered call sites.\\n- Verify whether the library requires environment setup, fixtures, or execution paths that automation did not trigger.\\n- Add or adjust focused tests for the uncovered paths before relying on the generated metadata.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1559#issuecomment-4230222035\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-28T08:59:03Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job for `org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20` failed. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-1559-library-new-request-org.projectlombok-lombok-1.18.20-c6ba61e1\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was post-generation test/native validation, not artifact discovery or URL population. Evidence: `human-intervention-logs/org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` and `human-intervention-logs/org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` both end with `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`, and the generated test suite reached 25/25 dynamic-access coverage (100%). However, the generator log `human-intervention-logs/org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T01-06-33-811043Z.log` shows the final coverage commit (`7fe7ddda`) was produced without compiling or running tests.\\n\\nThe native test output points to Lombok-specific runtime/resource behavior as the blocker. In `tests/src/org.projectlombok/lombok/1.18.20/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`, `ShadowClassLoaderTest` aborts because native image does not expose shadow-loader resources as enumerable jar/file URLs, and `AgentTest` aborts with `IllegalArgumentException: Unknown protocol: resource:/lombok/launch/Agent.class`. The follow-up log `human-intervention-logs/org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20/metadata-fix/codex.log` shows extra manual work was then needed to add shadow-loader reflection/resource metadata plus predefined classes (`predefined-classes-config.json` and 79 `.classdata` files) before a focused `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20 --stacktrace` run became green.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T01-01-01-546648Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T01-06-33-811043Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20/metadata-fix/codex.log`\\n- `tests/src/org.projectlombok/lombok/1.18.20/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Review the preserved branch and decide whether to keep the added metadata/predefined-classes files and the native-specific test adjustments.\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20 --stacktrace` and `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.projectlombok:lombok:1.18.20 --stacktrace`.\\n3. If skipped native tests are not acceptable for a new-library request, replace those assertions with coverage that works under native-image `resource:` URL semantics.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1559#issuecomment-4333786120\"}]}},{\"number\":1558,\"title\":\"Support for org.wildfly.common:wildfly-common:1.5.0.Final\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1558\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-26T14:38:19Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-29T09:14:24Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.wildfly.common:wildfly-common:1.5.0.Final\\n\\n### Library source code URL\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n### Link to the existing test suite\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-29T09:14:17Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.wildfly.common:wildfly-common:1.5.0.Final`.\\n\\nPreserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-1558-library-new-request-org.wildfly.common-wildfly-common-1.5.0.Final-0cdbba37\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was the dynamic-access-guided test generation/coverage step, not basic metadata validation. In the preserved work, `logs/org.wildfly.common:wildfly-common:1.5.0.Final/metadata-fix/codex.log` shows the follow-up validation passing for `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.wildfly.common:wildfly-common:1.5.0.Final` and also for the `future-defaults-all` lane, but `stats/org.wildfly.common/wildfly-common/1.5.0.Final/stats.json` still reports only `2/8` covered dynamic-access calls (`25.00%`), which is too low for a new-library support result. Earlier generation attempts were also unstable under native-image validation: `logs/org.wildfly.common:wildfly-common:1.5.0.Final/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T08-56-07-438356Z.log` shows `:nativeTestCompile` failing with `graal-sdk-1.0.0-rc9.jar contains class org.graalvm.nativeimage.impl.ProcessPropertiesSupport ... must not be passed via -cp`.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `logs/org.wildfly.common:wildfly-common:1.5.0.Final/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T08-49-36-673271Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.wildfly.common:wildfly-common:1.5.0.Final/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T08-56-07-438356Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.wildfly.common:wildfly-common:1.5.0.Final/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T08-58-57-336505Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.wildfly.common:wildfly-common:1.5.0.Final/metadata-fix/codex.log`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Review the preserved test module under `tests/src/org.wildfly.common/wildfly-common/1.5.0.Final/` and add library-specific tests for the remaining uncovered dynamic-access sites.\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.wildfly.common:wildfly-common:1.5.0.Final` and refresh `stats/org.wildfly.common/wildfly-common/1.5.0.Final/stats.json` until coverage reaches at least 50%.\\n3. If `nativeTestCompile` still fails on the latest GraalVM lane, investigate the `graal-sdk`/builder-classpath conflict before opening a PR.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1558#issuecomment-4342324363\"}]}},{\"number\":1521,\"title\":\"Support for org.hibernate.common:hibernate-commons-annotations:5.1.2.Final\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1521\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-26T14:36:53Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-29T07:51:54Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.hibernate.common:hibernate-commons-annotations:5.1.2.Final\\n\\n### Library source code URL\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n### Link to the existing test suite\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-29T07:51:47Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job for `org.hibernate.common:hibernate-commons-annotations:5.1.2.Final` failed. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-1521-library-new-request-org.hibernate.common-hibernate-commons-annotations-5.1.2.Final-f8c564ae\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was workflow finalization/bookkeeping after test generation, not the final dynamic-access run itself. The run metrics entry at `local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/1521-214181aa/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json` records `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, `metadata_entries: 0`, and `artifacts.test_file = None` / `artifacts.metadata_file = None`, even though the recorded ending commit was `9846429b7a4ed6f492410902d8b68d440abab664` and the run added 9 focused test commits after the scaffold. The final run window from `77eabc1f39` to `9846429b7a` contains only test-source changes; `metadata/org.hibernate.common/hibernate-commons-annotations/5.1.2.Final/reachability-metadata.json` was not present in that ending commit and only appears later in the preservation commit `4ab12f4067`.\\n\\nThere was an earlier native runtime failure during one iteration, but it does not look like the final blocker. `build/tests/org.hibernate.common:hibernate-commons-annotations:5.1.2.Final/a1651f8ffd825cc6d42f57a47016b7be.out` shows `:nativeTest FAILED` with `Invalid logger interface org.hibernate.annotations.common.util.impl.Log`, while the later `build/tests/org.hibernate.common:hibernate-commons-annotations:5.1.2.Final/ce0cfb9b6e46685cf9a370133b663736.out` shows `BUILD SUCCESSFUL` and writes `tests/src/org.hibernate.common/hibernate-commons-annotations/5.1.2.Final/build/native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access/hibernate-commons-annotations-5.1.2.Final/reflection-calls.json`. That report contains 22 dynamic-access call sites across 14 methods, which matches the reported 22/22 (100.00%) coverage.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.hibernate.common:hibernate-commons-annotations:5.1.2.Final/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T07-47-43-005593Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.hibernate.common:hibernate-commons-annotations:5.1.2.Final/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T07-45-24-926822Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/org.hibernate.common:hibernate-commons-annotations:5.1.2.Final/ce0cfb9b6e46685cf9a370133b663736.out`\\n- `build/tests/org.hibernate.common:hibernate-commons-annotations:5.1.2.Final/a1651f8ffd825cc6d42f57a47016b7be.out`\\n- `local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/1521-214181aa/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Review the preserved branch and make sure the intended final tree includes both the generated test suite and `metadata/org.hibernate.common/hibernate-commons-annotations/5.1.2.Final/reachability-metadata.json`; the failed run’s ending commit did not include that metadata file.\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.hibernate.common:hibernate-commons-annotations:5.1.2.Final` on the preserved branch to confirm the preserved state still passes and reproduces the 22/22 dynamic-access coverage.\\n3. Replace or remove the remaining scaffold placeholder `tests/src/org.hibernate.common/hibernate-commons-annotations/5.1.2.Final/src/test/java/org_hibernate_common/hibernate_commons_annotations/Hibernate_commons_annotationsTest.java` before opening or resuming a PR.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1521#issuecomment-4341815910\"}]}},{\"number\":1511,\"title\":\"Support for org.eclipse.jetty:jetty-alpn-client:11.0.12\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1511\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-26T14:36:03Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T21:03:21Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.eclipse.jetty:jetty-alpn-client:11.0.12\\n\\n### Library source code URL\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n### Link to the existing test suite\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-05-01T21:03:15Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job was marked failed with `test_generation_failed`. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-1511-library-new-request-org.eclipse.jetty-jetty-alpn-client-11.0.12-b0f45154\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is the test-generation/orchestration handoff, not artifact discovery or Gradle validation. Artifact discovery completed in `logs/org.eclipse.jetty:jetty-alpn-client:11.0.12/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` and `logs/org.eclipse.jetty:jetty-alpn-client:11.0.12/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`, and the preserved metrics ended with `status: success` after 4 iterations at commit `b4a078435da5acdf2899b0dc211f2135ac59de54` in `stats/org.eclipse.jetty/jetty-alpn-client/11.0.12/execution-metrics.json`. The three generation retries in `logs/org.eclipse.jetty:jetty-alpn-client:11.0.12/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T20-50-20-959876Z.log`, `logs/org.eclipse.jetty:jetty-alpn-client:11.0.12/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T20-53-27-466846Z.log`, and `logs/org.eclipse.jetty:jetty-alpn-client:11.0.12/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T20-57-47-132854Z.log` show repeated iteration on the ALPN client tests; the preserved worktree now contains a scoped test/metadata diff, and archived Gradle outputs under `build/tests/org.eclipse.jetty:jetty-alpn-client:11.0.12/` show `checkMetadataFiles`, `checkstyle`, dynamic-access report generation, and native `test` succeeding with 9/9 tests passing. `stats/org.eclipse.jetty/jetty-alpn-client/11.0.12/stats.json` reports `0/0` dynamic-access calls, so this does not appear to be a coverage-gate failure either.\\n\\n1. Review the three `pi-generation` logs above to confirm why the controller kept the issue in `test_generation_failed` after a valid test/metadata patch had already been produced.\\n2. Inspect the preserved branch diff together with `build/tests/org.eclipse.jetty:jetty-alpn-client:11.0.12/b5f4615e928d6bd34f1f6e3df1912933.out` and the test XMLs under `tests/src/org.eclipse.jetty/jetty-alpn-client/11.0.12/build/test-results/` to decide whether to promote the preserved work directly.\\n3. If the preserved result looks acceptable, rerun or manually continue the `library-new-request` flow from the preserved branch so the issue state matches the successful validation artifacts.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1511#issuecomment-4361632331\"}]}},{\"number\":1504,\"title\":\"Support for org.bouncycastle:bcutil-jdk18on:1.77\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1504\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-26T14:35:31Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-27T10:48:39Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.bouncycastle:bcutil-jdk18on:1.77\\n\\n### Library source code URL\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n### Link to the existing test suite\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"github-actions\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-26T14:36:52Z\",\"body\":\"Automation: No dependency issues were created by the triage workflow.\\n\\nThis typically means every dependency in the deps.dev expansion is already supported by the repository or listed in metadata/library-and-framework-list.json.\\n\\nPlan nodes:\\n```\\norg.bouncycastle:bcutil-jdk18on:1.77\\norg.bouncycastle:bcprov-jdk18on:1.77\\n```\\n\\nSupported GA detected during checks:\\n```\\n(none)\\n```\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1504#issuecomment-4135465842\"