At\":\"2026-04-11T20:28:31Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nAutomation completed for `org.jgroups:jgroups:5.2.0.Final`, but dynamic-access coverage remains `0/151` (0.00%). This suggests the generated tests are not exercising the required dynamic-access paths well enough.\\n\\nRecommended manual follow-up:\\n- Inspect the generated tests and compare them with the dynamic-access report to find uncovered call sites.\\n- Verify whether the library requires environment setup, fixtures, or execution paths that automation did not trigger.\\n- Add or adjust focused tests for the uncovered paths before relying on the generated metadata.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1498#issuecomment-4230129532\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-29T22:25:54Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job for `org.jgroups:jgroups:5.2.0.Final` failed. Preserved work is available on `https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-1498-library-new-request-org.jgroups-jgroups-5.2.0.Final-59cee94f`.\\n\\nMost likely the run failed in the final validation/curation stage rather than during initial generation. The metrics file at `stats/org.jgroups/jgroups/5.2.0.Final/execution-metrics.json` ends with `status: failure` after 43 iterations and still records `generated_loc: 0`, `test_file: None`, and `metadata_file: None`, even though the preserved branch contains generated commits through `07887b099`. In the preserved worktree, `build/tests/org.jgroups:jgroups:5.2.0.Final/0c512898d6ec2b0c3a57d1d8fc1caea7.out` and `build/tests/org.jgroups:jgroups:5.2.0.Final/931b9c026bbdcab21b0c1d063a2e3a22.out` are successful, but `build/tests/org.jgroups:jgroups:5.2.0.Final/da82c66cccf0e2fc4a808892389a66fe.out` fails at `:nativeTest` with many runtime errors, including `MissingResourceException: Can't find bundle for base name jg-messages, locale en_US`, `NoClassDefFoundError: Could not initialize class org.jgroups.util.Util`, and `InvalidClassException: java.util.ArrayList; no valid constructor`.\\n\\nThere are also unresolved generation-quality issues in the preserved tests. `tests/src/org.jgroups/jgroups/5.2.0.Final/src/test/java/org_jgroups/jgroups/JgroupsTest.java` is still the scaffold placeholder, and `tests/src/org.jgroups/jgroups/5.2.0.Final/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` still leaves 2 call sites uncovered (`org.jgroups.logging.LogFactory.isAvailable` and `org.jgroups.util.Base64$1.resolveClass`), matching the reported 148/150 dynamic-access coverage. The last generation attempts were still iterating on these areas in `logs/org.jgroups:jgroups:5.2.0.Final/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T21-54-11-324122Z.log`, `logs/org.jgroups:jgroups:5.2.0.Final/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T22-02-08-716016Z.log`, and `logs/org.jgroups:jgroups:5.2.0.Final/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T22-20-26-461392Z.log`.\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Check out the preserved branch and fix the failing native runtime cases from `build/tests/org.jgroups:jgroups:5.2.0.Final/da82c66cccf0e2fc4a808892389a66fe.out`, starting with the missing `jg-messages` resource/metadata and the failing deserialization paths.\\n2. Replace or remove the scaffold `JgroupsTest` so the test suite contains only real JGroups-specific coverage.\\n3. Re-run the JGroups lane and confirm both `nativeTest` passes and the remaining 2 uncovered dynamic-access call sites are addressed.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1498#issuecomment-4347975355\"}]}},{\"number\":1497,\"title\":\"Support for org.bouncycastle:bcprov-jdk15to18:1.77\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1497\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-26T14:35:12Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-27T10:48:37Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.bouncycastle:bcprov-jdk15to18:1.77\\n\\n### Library source code URL\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n### Link to the existing test suite\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"github-actions\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-26T14:36:33Z\",\"body\":\"Automation: No dependency issues were created by the triage workflow.\\n\\nThis typically means every dependency in the deps.dev expansion is already supported by the repository or listed in metadata/library-and-framework-list.json.\\n\\nPlan nodes:\\n```\\norg.bouncycastle:bcprov-jdk15to18:1.77\\n```\\n\\nSupported GA detected during checks:\\n```\\n(none)\\n```\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1497#issuecomment-4135461777\"}]}},{\"number\":1496,\"title\":\"Support for org.bouncycastle:bcprov-jdk15on:1.48\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1496\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-26T14:35:07Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:14:09Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.bouncycastle:bcprov-jdk15on:1.48\\n\\n### Library source code URL\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n### Link to the existing test suite\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"github-actions\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-26T14:36:22Z\",\"body\":\"Automation: No dependency issues were created by the triage workflow.\\n\\nThis typically means every dependency in the deps.dev expansion is already supported by the repository or listed in metadata/library-and-framework-list.json.\\n\\nPlan nodes:\\n```\\norg.bouncycastle:bcprov-jdk15on:1.70\\n```\\n\\nSupported GA detected during checks:\\n```\\n(none)\\n```\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1496#issuecomment-4135459743\"}]}},{\"number\":1491,\"title\":\"Support for org.javassist:javassist:3.14.0-GA\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1491\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-26T14:34:53Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-28T14:42:28Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.javassist:javassist:3.14.0-GA\\n\\n### Library source code URL\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n### Link to the existing test suite\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T13:22:46Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.javassist:javassist:3.24.1-GA`. Preserved work is available on `https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-1491-library-new-request-org.javassist-javassist-3.24.1-GA-79eefbcf`.\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was post-generation native test validation, not initial metadata generation. `human-intervention-logs/org.javassist:javassist:3.24.1-GA/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-04-27T13-05-30-640142Z.log` reports 10 generated test failures after the metadata-fix stage. `human-intervention-logs/org.javassist:javassist:3.24.1-GA/metadata-fix/codex.log` shows the real metadata issue had already been narrowed to serialization around `javassist.tools.reflect.Metaobject` / `javassist.tools.rmi.ObjectImporter`, but the remaining failures were non-metadata problems in generated tests: `UnsupportedFeatureError` during runtime proxy class definition, `javassist.NotFoundException` from `ClassPool` lookups (`java.io.Serializable`, `java.lang.Object`, `javassist.util.proxy.SecurityActions`), `NoSuchFieldException: stack`, and `javassist.tools.web.BadHttpRequest`. The dynamic-access stats are still meaningful at 68/103 covered calls (66.02%), so this looks like unsupported generated scenarios rather than no viable library support. `human-intervention-logs/org.javassist:javassist:3.24.1-GA/checkstyle/pi-checkstyle-2026-04-27T13-08-17-766990Z.log` only shows a single naming fix, so checkstyle was not the blocker.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.javassist:javassist:3.24.1-GA/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-04-27T13-05-30-640142Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.javassist:javassist:3.24.1-GA/metadata-fix/codex.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.javassist:javassist:3.24.1-GA/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-27T13-00-21-617560Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.javassist:javassist:3.24.1-GA/checkstyle/pi-checkstyle-2026-04-27T13-08-17-766990Z.log`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Review the preserved branch and keep or rewrite only the tests that exercise supportable native-image behavior; drop the generated tests that rely on runtime class definition, runtime bytecode/classpath lookup, or fragile JDK-internal assumptions.\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.javassist:javassist:3.24.1-GA` and `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.javassist:javassist:3.24.1-GA` on the preserved branch.\\n3. If those pass, continue the manual follow-up from the preserved branch rather than restarting generation from scratch.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1491#issuecomment-4327312012\"}]}},{\"number\":1485,\"title\":\"Support for org.apache.logging.log4j:log4j-api:2.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1485\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-26T14:34:35Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-26T21:28:15Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.apache.logging.log4j:log4j-api:2.0\\n\\n### Library source code URL\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n### Link to the existing test suite\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"github-actions\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-26T14:35:53Z\",\"body\":\"Automation: No dependency issues were created by the triage workflow.\\n\\nThis typically means every dependency in the deps.dev expansion is already supported by the repository or listed in metadata/library-and-framework-list.json.\\n\\nPlan nodes:\\n```\\norg.apache.logging.log4j:log4j-api:2.17.1\\norg.osgi:org.osgi.core:4.3.1\\n```\\n\\nSupported GA detected during checks:\\n```\\n(none)\\n```\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1485#issuecomment-4135453734\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-26T21:28:12Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nAutomated test generation failed validation for `org.apache.logging.log4j:log4j-api:2.0`. The run did reach `21/21` dynamic-access coverage (`100.00%`) with `dynamic_access_main_sources_pi_gpt-5.4`, so the likely failure was not test exploration itself but the post-generation native test verification / metadata-fix stage.\\n\\nMost likely failing stage: post-gen native test validation (`metadata_fix_failed`). Concrete evidence:\\n- `/home/vjovanov/c/metadata-forge/logs/pi-post-gen-org.apache.logging.log4j_log4j-api_2.0-2026-04-26T21-24-38-666636Z.log` says the generated support was reduced to `9` passing native tests and `1` remaining metadata-related failure after removing `3` non-metadata child-first-classloader/runtime tests.\\n- `/home/vjovanov/c/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/1485-42bed769/tests/src/org.apache.logging.log4j/log4j-api/2.0/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` shows the remaining error is `ThreadDumpMessageTest.serializesAndDeserializesUsingTheProxyRepresentation()` failing with `org.graalvm.nativeimage.MissingReflectionRegistrationError: Cannot reflectively invoke constructor 'public java.lang.Object()'`, coming from `ObjectStreamClass.newInstance` / `ObjectInputStream.readOrdinaryObject` during deserialization.\\n- `/home/vjovanov/c/metadata-forge/logs/codex_org.apache.logging.log4j_log4j-api_2.0.log` shows the metadata repair improved the run from `9/13` passing to a single remaining metadata failure, while the other dropped tests were classified as native runtime/classloader limitations rather than metadata gaps.\\n\\nLogs and artifacts to inspect:\\n- `/home/vjovanov/c/metadata-forge/logs/pi-post-gen-org.apache.logging.log4j_log4j-api_2.0-2026-04-26T21-24-38-666636Z.log`\\n- `/home/vjovanov/c/metadata-forge/logs/codex_org.apache.logging.log4j_log4j-api_2.0.log`\\n- `/home/vjovanov/c/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/1485-42bed769/tests/src/org.apache.logging.log4j/log4j-api/2.0/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Review `metadata/org.apache.logging.log4j/log4j-api/2.0/reachability-metadata.json` and decide whether the `java.lang.Object.<init>()` reflection registration needs to be made less restrictive or otherwise adjusted for the `ThreadDumpMessage` deserialization path.\\n2. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.logging.log4j:log4j-api:2.0 --stacktrace` and `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.logging.log4j:log4j-api:2.0 --stacktrace` after that metadata change.\\n3. Confirm that the removed `LogManagerTest` / `ThreadContextTest` child-first-loader cases should stay excluded as native runtime limitations, not metadata regressions.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1485#issuecomment-4323041523\"}]}},{\"number\":1463,\"title\":\"Support for org.robolectric:android-all:10-robolectric-5803371\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1463\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-26T14:33:31Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-30T00:30:44Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.robolectric:android-all:10-robolectric-5803371\\n\\n### Library source code URL\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n### Link to the existing test suite\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T00:30:38Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job failed for `org.robolectric:android-all:10-robolectric-5803371`. Preserved work is available at https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-1463-library-new-request-org.robolectric-android-all-10-robolectric-5803371-5692115c.\\n\\nThe failure appears to be in the iterative test-generation stage, not artifact discovery. `logs/org.robolectric:android-all:10-robolectric-5803371/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` and `logs/org.robolectric:android-all:10-robolectric-5803371/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log` completed successfully, but `logs/org.robolectric:android-all:10-robolectric-5803371/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T00-23-02-265648Z.log` shows the first generated tests failing with `UnsatisfiedLinkError`/`NoSuchMethodError` in `android.util.SparseArray`, `android.util.LruCache`, and `android.text.TextUtils`. A later iteration had to add `-H:+AllowDeprecatedBuilderClassesOnImageClasspath` because `android-all-10-robolectric-5803371.jar` bundles JDK classes such as `java.math.BigDecimal`, which native-image rejects by default; see `logs/org.robolectric:android-all:10-robolectric-5803371/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T00-26-11-707353Z.log`.\\n\\nThe final iteration does get the generated module green: `logs/org.robolectric:android-all:10-robolectric-5803371/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T00-27-48-937336Z.log` shows the preserved test suite passing under both JVM and native image. The workflow still ends in failure, though, and dynamic-access coverage was never produced: `stats/org.robolectric/android-all/10-robolectric-5803371/execution-metrics.json` records `status: failure`, `iterations: 7`, and `code_coverage_percent: 0.0`, and there is no `stats/org.robolectric/android-all/10-robolectric-5803371/stats.json` or dynamic-access report to review. This likely needs a maintainer decision on whether `android-all` is a valid target here, since it repackages Android/JDK platform classes and requires a deprecated native-image escape hatch.\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Review the preserved branch and decide whether this artifact should be supported at all, given the repeated JVM/runtime incompatibilities and the need for `-H:+AllowDeprecatedBuilderClassesOnImageClasspath`.\\n2. If support should continue, keep or rework the preserved test/build changes and rerun the library flow until it emits a real dynamic-access report and `stats/org.robolectric/android-all/10-robolectric-5803371/stats.json`.\\n3. If coverage still cannot be generated, close or re-scope the request with the root cause documented from the logs above.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1463#issuecomment-4348565293\"}]}},{\"number\":1462,\"title\":\"Support for org.conscrypt:conscrypt-openjdk-uber:1.1.4\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1462\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-26T14:33:30Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-30T14:13:54Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\norg.conscrypt:conscrypt-openjdk-uber:1.1.4\\n\\n### Library source code URL\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n### Link to the existing test suite\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T01:23:22Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.conscrypt:conscrypt-openjdk-uber:1.4.0`. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-1462-library-new-request-org.conscrypt-conscrypt-openjdk-uber-1.4.0-1483d661\\n\\nMost likely failing stage: the dynamic-access test-generation / verification loop stopped with one call site still uncovered. `stats/org.conscrypt/conscrypt-openjdk-uber/1.4.0/execution-metrics.json` shows `status: failure`, `iterations: 14`, and no finalized `test_file` or `metadata_file`. The final coverage report at `tests/src/org.conscrypt/conscrypt-openjdk-uber/1.4.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` is `37/38`, with the only remaining uncovered site at `org.conscrypt.NativeLibraryLoader.loadFromWorkdir(NativeLibraryLoader.java:173)` for the macOS `.dynlib` fallback `ClassLoader#getResource(...)` call.\\n\\nThere was also a failing native test run during the loop. `build/tests/org.conscrypt:conscrypt-openjdk-uber:1.4.0/514f4297a07921510881aac3c0f7af44.out` shows `> Task :nativeTest FAILED`, including `NativeLibraryLoaderTest > isolatedOsxLoaderQueriesDynlibFallbackResource()` failing its assertion, plus several Conscrypt provider tests failing with `UnsatisfiedLinkError` / `NoClassDefFoundError` around `org.conscrypt.NativeCrypto`. The last preserved generation log, `human-intervention-logs/org.conscrypt:conscrypt-openjdk-uber:1.4.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T01-21-10-645740Z.log`, shows the final change was commit `37dcdba0ed` adding `OpenSSLCipherInnerEVP_AEADTest`, which appears to cover the AEAD gap but does not resolve the remaining `NativeLibraryLoader` gap.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.conscrypt:conscrypt-openjdk-uber:1.4.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T01-21-10-645740Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/org.conscrypt:conscrypt-openjdk-uber:1.4.0/514f4297a07921510881aac3c0f7af44.out`\\n- `tests/src/org.conscrypt/conscrypt-openjdk-uber/1.4.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.conscrypt:conscrypt-openjdk-uber:1.4.0` on the preserved branch to confirm the final state after commit `37dcdba0ed`.\\n2. Adjust `NativeLibraryLoaderTest` so the macOS `.dynlib` fallback path at `NativeLibraryLoader.java:173` is exercised reliably in both JVM and native-image runs.\\n3. If native tests still fail on `org.conscrypt.NativeCrypto`, decide whether this library needs additional native-image test configuration or whether the current provider-based tests should be narrowed.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1462#issuecomment-4348871118\"}]}},{\"number\":1451,\"title\":\"Support for jakarta.el:jakarta.el-api:3.0.2\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1451\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-26T14:33:09Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-30T01:23:06Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\njakarta.el:jakarta.el-api:3.0.2\\n\\n### Library source code URL\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n### Link to the existing test suite\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-13T16:01:48Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nAutomation completed for `jakarta.el:jakarta.el-api:3.0.2`, but dynamic-access coverage remains `0/28` (0.00%). This suggests the generated tests are not exercising the required dynamic-access paths well enough.\\n\\nRecommended manual follow-up:\\n- Inspect the generated tests and compare them with the dynamic-access report to find uncovered call sites.\\n- Verify whether the library requires environment setup, fixtures, or execution paths that automation did not trigger.\\n- Add or adjust focused tests for the uncovered paths before relying on the generated metadata.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1451#issuecomment-4237833059\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T01:23:01Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `jakarta.el:jakarta.el-api:3.0.2`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-1451-library-new-request-jakarta.el-jakarta.el-api-3.0.2-0f6d16f0\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is native test execution, not artifac