` is intentionally tracked in the final change set (it is currently `{}` in preserved work).\\n3. Remove or replace the leftover scaffold `Jakarta_el_apiTest` before merging this new-library support.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1451#issuecomment-4348868539\"}]}},{\"number\":1430,\"title\":\"Support for jakarta.activation:jakarta.activation-api:1.2.1\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1430\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-26T14:32:18Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-05-01T20:20:27Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\njakarta.activation:jakarta.activation-api:1.2.1\\n\\n### Library source code URL\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n### Link to the existing test suite\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"github-actions\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-26T14:33:39Z\",\"body\":\"Automation: No dependency issues were created by the triage workflow.\\n\\nThis typically means every dependency in the deps.dev expansion is already supported by the repository or listed in metadata/library-and-framework-list.json.\\n\\nPlan nodes:\\n```\\njakarta.activation:jakarta.activation-api:2.1.0\\n```\\n\\nSupported GA detected during checks:\\n```\\n(none)\\n```\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1430#issuecomment-4135428154\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-14T11:19:41Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nAutomation completed for `jakarta.activation:jakarta.activation-api:2.1.0`, but dynamic-access coverage remains `0/13` (0.00%). This suggests the generated tests are not exercising the required dynamic-access paths well enough.\\n\\nRecommended manual follow-up:\\n- Inspect the generated tests and compare them with the dynamic-access report to find uncovered call sites.\\n- Verify whether the library requires environment setup, fixtures, or execution paths tha