in-stdlib-jdk8:1.5.31/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T21-03-45-412798Z.log` and `build/tests/org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-jdk8:1.5.31/cf54656e46b8ab551b8694477f467013.out`), and the module reports show passing JVM/native tests plus a `0/0` dynamic-access report (`tests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-stdlib-jdk8/1.5.31/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`). However, `stats/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-stdlib-jdk8/1.5.31/execution-metrics.json` records `\\\"status\\\": \\\"failure\\\"`, has no `stats` block, and `code_coverage_percent` is `0.0`, while the expected `stats/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-stdlib-jdk8/1.5.31/stats.json` is missing entirely. Artifact discovery and URL population completed successfully, so the failure does not appear to be in those earlier stages (`human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-jdk8:1.5.31/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log`, `human-intervention-logs/org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-stdlib-jdk8:1.5.31/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`).\\n\\nRecommended manual follow-up:\\n- Inspect why the run was marked failed after successful `javaTest` and `nativeTest`, focusing on stats/metrics generation for `stats/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-stdlib-jdk8/1.5.31/`.\\n- Compare this run with the neighboring successful Kotlin artifacts (`kotlin-stdlib-jdk7` / `kotlin-stdlib-common`) to restore the missing `stats.json` and `stats` block in `execution-metrics.json`.\\n- If metrics regeneration succeeds, reuse the preserved branch contents and rerun the issue workflow for this coordinate.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1396#issuecomment-4361653407\"}]}},{\"number\":1382,\"title\":\"Support for commons-collections:commons-collections:2.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1382\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-26T14:30:46Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-28T03:00:19Z\",\"body\":\"### Fu