d the same start/end commit (`035806b92c7a7d9a1c3b72c57618ddd5ace4ecd8`). The current worktree only retains the placeholder `tests/src/commons-collections/commons-collections/2.0/src/test/java/commons_collections/commons_collections/Commons_collectionsTest.java` and an empty `metadata/commons-collections/commons-collections/2.0/reachability-metadata.json`, which suggests the generated test work was not carried into the final recorded state.\\n\\nThere is also a concrete native-image failure in the generated test output. `tests/src/commons-collections/commons-collections/2.0/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` and `build/tests/commons-collections:commons-collections:2.0/19a7d2cd6536636d4243f442d3f23cae.out` show 3 native test failures: `BeanMapTest.convertsStringValuesUsingSingleArgumentConstructors()` fails with `IllegalArgumentException`, and both `CursorableLinkedList` serialization tests fail with `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` for `java.lang.Object.<init>()`. The dynamic-access report at `tests/src/commons-collections/commons-collections/2.0/build/native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access/commons-collections-2.0/reflection-calls.json` still lists all 9 dynamic-access call sites, matching the reported `0/9` coverage. For comparison, artifact discovery and URL population completed successfully in `human-intervention-logs/commons-collections:commons-collections:2.0/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` and `human-intervention-logs/commons-collections:commons-collections:2.0/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`.\\n\\nLogs to inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/commons-collections:commons-collections:2.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T02-45-43-405257Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/commons-collections:commons-collections:2.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T02-53-29-346685Z.log`\\n- `tests/src/commons-collections/commons-collections/2.0/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\\n- `build/tests/commons-collections:commons-collections:2.0/19a7d2cd6536636d4243f442d3f23cae.out`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Recover the generated `BeanMapTest` and `CursorableLinkedListTest` work from the preserved branch/logs and restore it into the actual source tree.\\n2. Replace the placeholder test and add the missing reflection metadata needed for native serialization, at minimum the no-arg constructor for `java.lang.Object`, then fix or remove the failing `BeanMap` constructor-conversion assertion.\\n3. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=commons-collections:commons-collections:2.0` and `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=commons-collections:commons-collections:2.0`, then regenerate stats to confirm coverage improves from `0/9`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1382#issuecomment-4332060523\"}]}},{\"number\":1344,\"title\":\"Support for net.java.dev.jna:jna-platform:5.8.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1344\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-26T14:29:38Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-30T05:14:07Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\nnet.java.dev.jna:jna-platform:5.8.0\\n\\n### Library source code URL\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n### Link to the existing test suite\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T05:14:00Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated `library-new-request` job for `net.java.dev.jna:jna-platform:5.8.0` failed with `test_generation_failed`. Preserved work is available here: `https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-1344-library-new-request-net.java.dev.jna-jna-platform-5.8.0-246438ba`.\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was test-generation finalization / artifact collection, not the last code-edit step itself. The latest generation log still shows the agent creating and committing tests through `7cada9a7d0` (`logs/net.java.dev.jna:jna-platform:5.8.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T05-10-44-886905Z.log`), and the preserved branch contains generated metadata/tests plus Gradle outputs. However, `stats/net.java.dev.jna/jna-platform/5.8.0/execution-metrics.json` still reports `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, and `artifacts.test_file` / `artifacts.metadata_file` as `None`, which does not match the preserved commit range or files on disk.\\n\\nThe preserved output also still needs manual cleanup before it is ready: `tests/src/net.java.dev.jna/jna-platform/5.8.0/src/test/java/net_java_dev_jna/jna_platform/Jna_platformTest.java` is still a scaffold placeholder, and the generated test resources use a legacy `src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/jna-platform-test/reflect-config.json`. The local dynamic-access report shows 25/27 covered calls, with the remaining uncovered sites in `com.sun.jna.platform.win32.COM.util.Factory.createProxy(...)` and `com.sun.jna.platform.win32.COM.util.ObjectFactory.createProxy(...)`. JVM test XMLs were produced, but `TEST-net_java_dev_jna.jna_platform.Win32ExceptionTest.xml` also contains a background Linux `UnsatisfiedLinkError` for `PeekMessage`, so the current test set may still be platform-fragile.\\n\\nLogs to inspect:\\n- `logs/net.java.dev.jna:jna-platform:5.8.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T05-10-44-886905Z.log`\\n- `logs/net.java.dev.jna:jna-platform:5.8.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T04-20-29-452341Z.log`\\n- `logs/net.java.dev.jna:jna-platform:5.8.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T04-15-41-115166Z.log`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Review the preserved branch, replace/remove the scaffold `Jna_platformTest`, and convert the test-only legacy `reflect-config.json` to repo-acceptable `reachability-metadata.json` usage.\\n2. Rework the JNA tests to avoid platform-fragile Win32 behavior on Linux and, if needed, cover the remaining `Factory.createProxy` / `ObjectFactory.createProxy` call sites.\\n3. Rerun `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles test -Pcoordinates=net.java.dev.jna:jna-platform:5.8.0` and refresh the metrics/artifact collection.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1344#issuecomment-4349871067\"}]}},{\"number\":1336,\"title\":\"Support for com.mchange:c3p0:0.9.5.4\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1336\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-26T14:29:21Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-30T05:44:33Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\ncom.mchange:c3p0:0.9.5.4\\n\\n### Library source code URL\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n### Link to the existing test suite\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"github-actions\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-26T14:30:43Z\",\"body\":\"Automation: No dependency issues were created by the triage workflow.\\n\\nThis typically means every dependency in the deps.dev expansion is already supported by the repository or listed in metadata/library-and-framework-list.json.\\n\\nPlan nodes:\\n```\\ncom.mchange:c3p0:0.9.5.4\\ncom.mchange:mchange-commons-java:0.2.15\\n```\\n\\nSupported GA detected during checks:\\n```\\n(none)\\n```\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1336#issuecomment-4135394497\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-30T05:44:25Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `com.mchange:c3p0:0.9.5.4`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-1336-library-new-request-com.mchange-c3p0-0.9.5.4-074b32b5\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was native test validation/finalization after iterative test generation. The run did generate a large test suite and reached 135/137 dynamic-access coverage (98.54%), but `build/tests/com.mchange:c3p0:0.9.5.4/3e3c565f90266ac3b021a6faebee714f.out` shows `:nativeTest FAILED` with 25 failing tests. The dominant failure is `java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: Could not initialize class com.mchange.v2.c3p0.C3P0Registry` across many generated tests, and the same output also shows `UnsupportedFeatureError` for serialization of `com.mchange.v2.c3p0.impl.DbAuth`. The final dynamic-access report still leaves 2 uncovered reflective calls in `com.mchange.v2.c3p0.C3P0Registry.<clinit>` (`Class#forName` and `Class#newInstance`), while the preserved metadata file is only `{}`.\\n\\nThere is also evidence that the bookkeeping/finalization step did not capture the generated artifacts correctly. In `human-intervention-logs/com.mchange:c3p0:0.9.5.4/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T05-39-28-147046Z.log`, the agent reports committing the last coverage test (`4b76c34f0`) but immediately notes that `metadata/com.mchange/c3p0/0.9.5.4/` was still untracked. `stats/com.mchange/c3p0/0.9.5.4/execution-metrics.json` then records `generated_loc: 0`, `metadata_entries: 0`, `artifacts.test_file: None`, and `artifacts.metadata_file: None`, which does not match the preserved branch contents.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.mchange:c3p0:0.9.5.4/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T05-39-28-147046Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.mchange:c3p0:0.9.5.4/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-30T04-18-01-524332Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/com.mchange:c3p0:0.9.5.4/3e3c565f90266ac3b021a6faebee714f.out`\\n- `tests/src/com.mchange/c3p0/0.9.5.4/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n- `stats/com.mchange/c3p0/0.9.5.4/execution-metrics.json`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Fix or trim the generated tests that trigger `C3P0Registry` initialization under native, and add metadata for the remaining `C3P0Registry.<clinit>` reflective calls.\\n2. Add the missing serialization metadata for `com.mchange.v2.c3p0.impl.DbAuth`, then rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=com.mchange:c3p0:0.9.5.4`.\\n3. After the native test suite passes, reconcile the recorded artifacts/metrics so the run no longer reports `generated_loc: 0` and `artifacts.*: None`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1336#issuecomment-4349984836\"}]}},{\"number\":1302,\"title\":\"Support for com.atomikos:atomikos-util:6.0.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1302\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-26T14:27:10Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-26T23:18:43Z\",\"body\":\"### Full Maven coordinates\\n\\ncom.atomikos:atomikos-util:6.0.0\\n\\n### Library source code URL\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n### Link to the existing test suite\\n\\nN/A\\n\\n_This issue was created by automation._\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-26T23:18:41Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job for `com.atomikos:atomikos-util:6.0.0` failed with `test_generation_failed`. Preserved work is available on the branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-1302-library-new-request-com.atomikos-atomikos-util-6.0.0-9c02fc57\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage is final metrics/reporting or orchestration after test generation, not the coordinate’s actual test run. Concrete evidence:\\n- Run metrics still ended in failure with `tested_library_loc: 0`, `code_coverage_percent: 0.0`, and only 1 metadata entry in `/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/1302-b921021e/.pending_metrics.json` and `/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/1302-b921021e/script_run_metrics/add_new_library_support.json`.\\n- The generated test project reports full dynamic-access coverage (`21/21`) in `/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/1302-b921021e/tests/src/com.atomikos/atomikos-util/6.0.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`.\\n- The follow-up validation in `/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/logs/metadata-fix/com.atomikos_atomikos-util_6.0.0/codex.log` shows `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=com.atomikos:atomikos-util:6.0.0 --stacktrace` finishing successfully, including native-image build and `14 tests successful, 0 failed`.\\n- Checkstyle was also repaired and passed; see `/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/logs/checkstyle/com.atomikos_atomikos-util_6.0.0/pi-checkstyle-2026-04-26T23-06-03-796666Z.log`.\\n- The final generation attempt and preserved commit are in `/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/logs/add-new-library-support/com.atomikos_atomikos-util_6.0.0/pi-generation-2026-04-26T22-55-03-651501Z.log`. There are also session-recording errors in the preserved logs (`failed to record rollout items: thread ... not found`), which may explain the bad final status.\\n\\nLogs/artifacts to inspect first:\\n- `/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/logs/add-new-library-support/com.atomikos_atomikos-util_6.0.0/pi-generation-2026-04-26T22-55-03-651501Z.log`\\n- `/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/logs/checkstyle/com.atomikos_atomikos-util_6.0.0/pi-checkstyle-2026-04-26T23-06-03-796666Z.log`\\n- `/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/logs/metadata-fix/com.atomikos_atomikos-util_6.0.0/codex.log`\\n- `/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/forge_run_metrics/1302-b921021e/.pending_metrics.json`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Check out the preserved branch and verify why metrics recorded `0` tested LOC even though the generated project has passing JVM/native tests, JaCoCo output, and `21/21` dynamic-access coverage.\\n2. Review the generated tests on the preserved branch for acceptability, then rerun `./gradlew checkstyle test -Pcoordinates=com.atomikos:atomikos-util:6.0.0 --stacktrace`.\\n3. If the rerun stays green, regenerate the library stats/metrics for this coordinate or re-trigger the automation so the final status matches the preserved artifacts.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/1302#issuecomment-4323283757\"}]}},{\"number\":542,\"title\":\"Add support for `org.apache.seata:seata-all:2.1.0`\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/542\",\"createdAt\":\"2024-10-07T06:33:23Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-29T03:25:28Z\",\"body\":\"**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\\r\\nA clear and concise description of what the problem is. Ex. I'm always frustrated when [...]\\r\\n\\r\\n- No.\\r\\n\\r\\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\\r\\nA clear and concise description of what you want to happen.\\r\\n\\r\\n- Add support for `org.apache.seata:seata-all:2.1.0`.\\r\\n- The relevant JSON entry is available at https://github.com/apache/shardingsphere/tree/2a11d03d8f6a6c2631284b9d051724dfb05b1f54/infra/reachability-metadata/src/main/resources/META-INF/native-image/org.apache.seata/seata-all/2.1.0 .\\r\\n\\r\\n**Describe alternatives you've considered**\\r\\nA clear and concise description of any alternative solutions or features you've considered.\\r\\n\\r\\n- Null.\\r\\n\\r\\n**Additional context**\\r\\nAdd any other context or screenshots about the feature request here.\\r\\n\\r\\n- Refer to https://github.com/apache/shardingsphere/issues/29052 .\\r\\n- Refer to https://github.com/apache/incubator-seata/issues/6686 .\\r\\n\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"linghengqian\"},\"createdAt\":\"2024-10-07T06:33:41Z\",\"body\":\"- I am working on the current issue.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/542#issuecomment-2396019891\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"linghengqian\"},\"createdAt\":\"2024-10-30T11:11:10Z\",\"body\":\"- The situation was so serious that the Docker Image `apache/seata-server:2.2.0` used by the unit tests did not comply with t