< 0.1% (1st)   < 0.1\\nperl-base              5.38.2-3.2build2             5.38.2-3.2ubuntu0.2                         deb           CVE-2025-40909       Medium      < 0.1% (0th)   < 0.1\\nlibgssapi-krb5-2       1.20.1-6ubuntu2.1            1.20.1-6ubuntu2.5                           deb           CVE-2025-24528       Medium      N/A            N/A\\nlibk5crypto3           1.20.1-6ubuntu2.1            1.20.1-6ubuntu2.5                           deb           CVE-2025-24528       Medium      N/A            N/A\\nlibkrb5-3              1.20.1-6ubuntu2.1            1.20.1-6ubuntu2.5                           deb           CVE-2025-24528       Medium      N/A            N/A\\nlibkrb5support0        1.20.1-6ubuntu2.1            1.20.1-6ubuntu2.5                           deb           CVE-2025-24528       Medium      N/A            N/A\\nlibssh-4               0.10.6-2build2               0.10.6-2ubuntu0.1                           deb           CVE-2025-4877        Medium      N/A            N/A\\n```\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/542#issuecomment-3193502444\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-29T03:25:20Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.apache.seata:seata-all:2.1.0`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-542-library-new-request-org.apache.seata-seata-all-2.1.0-773708ae\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was native-image test validation after test generation, not initial test creation. The preserved branch contains a large generated Seata test suite, and `tests/src/org.apache.seata/seata-all/2.1.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` shows 109/111 dynamic-access calls covered, but `build/tests/org.apache.seata:seata-all:2.1.0/945a586092e130479992d762ee669337.out` and `tests/src/org.apache.seata/seata-all/2.1.0/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` show `:nativeTest` failed with 53 tests run and 12 failures/errors. The failing native tests include missing metadata (`MissingReflectionRegistrationError` for Spring proxy classes and `java.lang.Throwable.serialVersionUID`) and additional test/setup problems (`Can not find embedded druid`, missing `org.example.seata.ContextOnlyParameter`, `field not found: com.taobao.hsf.app.spring.util.HSFSpringProviderBean, field: providerBean`, ByteBuddy proxy creation failures, and missing `oracle.jdbc.xa.client.OracleXAConnection`). The preserved metadata file is still just `{}` at `metadata/org.apache.seata/seata-all/2.1.0/reachability-metadata.json`.\\n\\nPlease inspect these artifacts first:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.seata:seata-all:2.1.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T03-12-23-636048Z.log`\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.seata:seata-all:2.1.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T03-19-57-681650Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/org.apache.seata:seata-all:2.1.0/945a586092e130479992d762ee669337.out`\\n- `tests/src/org.apache.seata/seata-all/2.1.0/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\\n- `tests/src/org.apache.seata/seata-all/2.1.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Review the preserved branch and keep only the generated tests that are valid for native-image coverage; rewrite or drop the brittle ones.\\n2. Replace the placeholder `{}` metadata with the missing reflection/proxy entries indicated by the native test failures, and add any required test resources/classes for the remaining setup failures.\\n3. Re-run the single-coordinate test lane for `org.apache.seata:seata-all:2.1.0` and refresh coverage/stats once `:nativeTest` is green.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/542#issuecomment-4340607968\"}]}},{\"number\":446,\"title\":\"Add support for `org.apache.calcite:calcite-core:1.35.0`\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/446\",\"createdAt\":\"2024-02-12T08:23:18Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-29T07:54:13Z\",\"body\":\"**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\\r\\nA clear and concise description of what the problem is. Ex. I'm always frustrated when [...]\\r\\n\\r\\n- No.\\r\\n\\r\\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\\r\\nA clear and concise description of what you want to happen.\\r\\n\\r\\n- Add support for `org.apache.calcite:calcite-core:1.35.0`.\\r\\n- The relevant JSON entry is available at https://github.com/apache/shardingsphere/tree/0397f829d60b47cd57b255a4f48132d627e7b10c/infra/reachability-metadata/src/main/resources/META-INF/native-image/org.apache.calcite/calcite-core/1.35.0 .\\r\\n\\r\\n**Describe alternatives you've considered**\\r\\nA clear and concise description of any alternative solutions or features you've considered.\\r\\n\\r\\n- Null.\\r\\n\\r\\n**Additional context**\\r\\nAdd any other context or screenshots about the feature request here.\\r\\n- Refer to https://github.com/apache/shardingsphere/issues/29052 .\\r\\n\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"linghengqian\"},\"createdAt\":\"2024-02-12T08:23:31Z\",\"body\":\"- I'm working on this issue.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/446#issuecomment-1938220735\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-29T02:43:05Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.apache.calcite:calcite-core:1.35.0`. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-446-library-new-request-org.apache.calcite-calcite-core-1.35.0-f7117214\\n\\nThe most likely blocker was the test-generation/native-validation stage. In `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.calcite:calcite-core:1.35.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T02-39-15-786553Z.log`, the run shows `JaninoCompilerTest > compilesInMemoryJavaSourceWithJaninoClassLoader() FAILED` with `java.lang.NullPointerException: args.destdir` from `JaninoCompiler.compile()`. The same log later records a candidate fix on commit `0de9972d0b` for `JaninoCompilerTest`, but it ends with “I did not rerun the Gradle test locally,” so the branch was preserved without a verified rerun.\\n\\nThere are also broader native-image failures in the preserved workspace. `build/tests/org.apache.calcite:calcite-core:1.35.0/b61131a365d59ce199f35b8198aa1188.out` shows `> Task :nativeTest FAILED`, and `tests/src/org.apache.calcite/calcite-core/1.35.0/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml` reports 58 tests with 4 failures and 33 errors, including multiple `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` cases for Calcite resource/proxy interfaces, resource-loading failures, and `RelJsonTest` failing with `unknown type LogicalValues`. Dynamic-access coverage is high but not complete: `tests/src/org.apache.calcite/calcite-core/1.35.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` is 120/121, with the remaining uncovered call at `org.apache.calcite.sql.parser.SqlAbstractParserImpl$MetadataImpl.virtualCall(SqlAbstractParserImpl.java:800)` (`Method.invoke`).\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.calcite:calcite-core:1.35.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T02-39-15-786553Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/org.apache.calcite:calcite-core:1.35.0/b61131a365d59ce199f35b8198aa1188.out`\\n- `tests/src/org.apache.calcite/calcite-core/1.35.0/build/test-results/test-native/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\\n- `tests/src/org.apache.calcite/calcite-core/1.35.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Check out the preserved branch, review commit `0de9972d0b`, and rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.calcite:calcite-core:1.35.0`.\\n2. Fix the remaining native-image metadata gaps reported in `TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`, especially the proxy/resource reflection and `RelJson` failures.\\n3. If needed, add coverage for the remaining uncovered dynamic-access call in `SqlAbstractParserImpl$MetadataImpl.virtualCall` and regenerate the report.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/446#issuecomment-4340469461\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"kimeta\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-29T07:54:05Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.apache.calcite:calcite-core:1.35.0`. Preserved work is available here: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fkimeta%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-446-library-new-request-org.apache.calcite-calcite-core-1.35.0-7965b4ca\\n\\nThis does not look like a coverage problem: the run reported dynamic-access coverage `120/120 (100.00%)`. The most likely failing stage was generated test synthesis / post-generation validation. The generated test tree still contains a scaffold-only placeholder test at `tests/src/org.apache.calcite/calcite-core/1.35.0/src/test/java/org_apache_calcite/calcite_core/Calcite_coreTest.java` (`System.out.println(\\\"This is just a placeholder, implement your test\\\")`), and it also includes legacy test-only native-image config files under `tests/src/org.apache.calcite/calcite-core/1.35.0/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/` (`reflect-config.json`, `proxy-config.json`, `resource-config.json`), which is not valid for `library-new-request`.\\n\\nThere was also a real native-image build blocker during generation: `build/tests/org.apache.calcite:calcite-core:1.35.0/66ec708d0370a384500022a6bc8d597d.out` shows `:nativeTestCompile FAILED` with `UnsupportedFeatureException: Type not found during analysis: ... sun.security.x509.X509CertInfo`. The post-gen intervention report says the suite mixed Janino/runtime-codegen failures with actual metadata gaps, and removed several generated Janino-related tests, but the suite still needs manual cleanup and follow-up metadata work.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `logs/org.apache.calcite:calcite-core:1.35.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T07-18-35-953891Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.apache.calcite:calcite-core:1.35.0/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-04-29T07-44-03-696333Z.log`\\n- `build/tests/org.apache.calcite:calcite-core:1.35.0/66ec708d0370a384500022a6bc8d597d.out`\\n- `post-gen-interventions/org.apache.calcite_calcite-core_1.35.0.md`\\n\\nNext steps:\\n1. Replace/remove the scaffold `Calcite_coreTest` and delete the legacy `META-INF/native-image/*.json` files from the generated test tree.\\n2. Rework or drop the Janino/enumerable/runtime-codegen scenarios so the suite only keeps stable Native Image metadata cases.\\n3. Fix the remaining metadata gaps called out in the post-gen report (`Resources$BooleanProp` constructor reflection and `SerializableCharset` serialization), then rerun `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.calcite:calcite-core:1.35.0`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/446#issuecomment-4341827410\"}]}},{\"number\":426,\"title\":\"Add Support for org.modelmapper:modelmapper:3.2.0\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/426\",\"createdAt\":\"2023-11-25T08:46:17Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-29T09:10:03Z\",\"body\":\"Requesting reachability metadata support for `org.modelmapper:modelmapper:3.2.0`\\r\\n\\r\\nhttps://modelmapper.org\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"dnestoro\"},\"createdAt\":\"2023-11-27T14:29:23Z\",\"body\":\"Hey, thanks for this request. It is a really nice idea to have this new library. At the moment we don't have a need for it, so it will be very nice if you can provide a pull request that adds metadata for this library. [Here](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md) is our guide, how to contribute to metadata repository. If you have any questions, please feel free to ask.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/426#issuecomment-1827944972\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-29T09:09:56Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `org.modelmapper:modelmapper:3.2.0`. Preserved work branch: `https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-426-library-new-request-org.modelmapper-modelmapper-3.2.0-65154db9`.\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was post-generation/native test validation. The last generation attempt only committed a single focused test (`Add ModelMapper Members field mapping test`, ending commit `1231970e2b`) and explicitly left `metadata/org.modelmapper/modelmapper/3.2.0/` untracked in `logs/org.modelmapper:modelmapper:3.2.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T08-50-44-186803Z.log`. The generated test tree is still not in reviewable shape: it contains a scaffold placeholder test (`tests/src/org.modelmapper/modelmapper/3.2.0/src/test/java/org_modelmapper/modelmapper/ModelmapperTest.java` prints “This is just a placeholder, implement your test”) and helper/test code under library-internal packages such as `tests/src/org.modelmapper/modelmapper/3.2.0/src/test/java/org/modelmapper/internal/...`.\\n\\nConcrete failure evidence:\\n- `build/tests/org.modelmapper:modelmapper:3.2.0/fb0ad8286a7841bc7104ed0e95bd25c0.out` shows `nativeTest FAILED`; `ModelmapperTest > test()` still runs as a placeholder, and `SunReflectionFactoryHelperTest` fails with `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` for `java.lang.Object.<init>()`.\\n- `logs/org.modelmapper:modelmapper:3.2.0/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-04-29T09-03-32-163957Z.log` reports that 68 generated failures were non-metadata native-image-incompatible tests, and after trimming those the run still ended at `43` passed / `1` failed (`SunReflectionFactoryHelperTest`).\\n- `logs/org.modelmapper:modelmapper:3.2.0/metadata-fix/codex.log` shows follow-up attempts hit both schema issues in generated metadata and then a larger native run still failing on Byte Buddy/runtime-class-generation paths.\\n- Metrics also ended in failure, and there is no `stats/org.modelmapper/modelmapper/3.2.0/stats.json`, so dynamic-access coverage is still unavailable.\\n\\nPlease inspect:\\n- `logs/org.modelmapper:modelmapper:3.2.0/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-29T08-50-44-186803Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.modelmapper:modelmapper:3.2.0/post-gen/pi-post-gen-2026-04-29T09-03-32-163957Z.log`\\n- `logs/org.modelmapper:modelmapper:3.2.0/metadata-fix/codex.log`\\n- `build/tests/org.modelmapper:modelmapper:3.2.0/fb0ad8286a7841bc7104ed0e95bd25c0.out`\\n\\nManual next steps:\\n1. Replace/remove the scaffold and library-internal generated tests, and keep only public-API, native-image-compatible tests for `modelmapper`.\\n2. Fix and verify the remaining metadata gap around `SunReflectionFactoryHelperTest` / `java.lang.Object.<init>()`, and confirm the metadata file is valid and actually consumed by the native build.\\n3. Rerun `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=org.modelmapper:modelmapper:3.2.0`, `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.modelmapper:modelmapper:3.2.0`, and `./gradlew generateLibraryStats -Pcoordinates=org.modelmapper:modelmapper:3.2.0`.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/426#issuecomment-4342297941\"}]}},{\"number\":159,\"title\":\"Support for com.baomidou:mybatis-plus-boot-starter:jar:3.5.3.1\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/159\",\"createdAt\":\"2023-01-04T20:09:02Z\",\"updatedAt\":\"2026-04-27T09:28:59Z\",\"body\":\"**Describe the problem**\\r\\n`\\r\\nException in thread \\\"main\\\" org.springframework.boot.context.properties.bind.MissingParametersCompilerArgumentException: Constructor binding in a native image requires compilation with -parameters but the following classes were compiled without it:\\r\\n        org.apache.ibatis.builder.CacheRefResolver\\r\\n        org.apache.ibatis.parsing.XNode\\r\\n        org.apache.ibatis.builder.annotation.MethodResolver\\r\\n        org.apache.ibatis.builder.ResultMapResolver\\r\\n        org.apache.ibatis.mapping.ResultFlag\\r\\n\\r\\n        at org.springframework.boot.context.properties.bind.BindableRuntimeHintsRegistrar.registerHints(BindableRuntimeHintsRegistrar.java:87)\\r\\n        at org.springframework.boot.context.properties.ConfigurationPropertiesBeanFactoryInitializationAotProcessor$ConfigurationPropertiesReflectionHintsContribution.applyTo(ConfigurationPropertiesBeanFactoryInitializationAotProcessor.java:70)\\r\\n        at org.springframework.context.aot.BeanFactoryInitializationAotContributions.applyTo(BeanFactoryInitializationAotContributions.java:78)\\r\\n        at org.springframework.context.aot.ApplicationContextAotGenerator.lambda$processAheadOfTime$0(ApplicationContextAotGenerator.java:58)\\r\\n        at org.springframework.context.aot.ApplicationContextAotGenerator.withCglibClassHandler(ApplicationContextAotGenerator.java:67)\\r\\n        at org.springframework.context.aot.ApplicationContextAotGenerator.processAheadOfTime(ApplicationContextAotGenerator.java:53)\\r\\n        at org.springframework.context.aot.ContextAotProcessor.performAotProcessing(ContextAotProcessor.java:106)\\r\\n        at org.springframework.context.aot.ContextAotProcessor.doProcess(ContextAotProcessor.java:84)\\r\\n        at org.springframework.context.aot.ContextAotProcessor.doProcess(ContextAotProcessor.java:49)\\r\\n        at org.springframework.context.aot.AbstractAotProcessor.process(AbstractAotProcessor.java:82)\\r\\n        at org.springframework.boot.SpringApplicationAotProcessor.main(SpringApplicationAotProcessor.java:76)\\r\\n`\\r\\n\\r\\n**Additional context**\\r\\nAdd any other context about the problem here.\\r\\n\\r\\n**System Info (please complete the following information):**\\r\\n - OS: [e.g. `mac`]\\r\\n - GraalVM Version [e.g. `graalvm-ce-java17-22.3.0`]\\r\\n - Java Version [e.g. `17`]\\r\\n - Plugin version [e.g. `native-maven-plugin:0.9.19`]\\r\\n\\r\\n**To Reproduce**\\r\\n[demo 2.zip](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/files/10347124/demo.2.zip)\\r\\n\",\"assignees\":{\"nodes\":[]},\"comments\":{\"nodes\":[{\"author\":{\"login\":\"wilkinsona\"},\"createdAt\":\"2023-01-05T10:30:07Z\",\"body\":\"I don't think this can be fixed with reachability metadata. The problem will need to be addressed in the code that's attempting to bind configuration properties directly to ibatis classes. Presumably that code is part of mybatis-plus-boot-starter.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/159#issuecomment-1372040628\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"sdeleuze\"},\"createdAt\":\"2023-01-05T11:04:58Z\",\"body\":\"@dnestoro I think you can close this issue.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/159#issuecomment-1372075483\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"fushun1990\"},\"createdAt\":\"2023-01-05T12:55:19Z\",\"body\":\"ok，\\r\\n但是能否给我一些意见，我应该怎么进行修改才可以解决这个问题了。或者是否有相似问题的解决方案我做参考。\\r\\n我没有找到相关是学习文档和解决方案。谢谢！！\\r\\n\\r\\n以上文字是中文翻译的。抱歉\\r\\n\\r\\nok\\r\\nBut could you please give me some advice on how I should modify to solve this problem? Or whether there are solutions to similar problems for my reference.\\r\\nI did not find the relevant documentation and solution. Thank you!!\\r\\n\\r\\nThe above text is translated from Chinese. Sorry\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/159#issuecomment-1372180391\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"linghengqian\"},\"createdAt\":\"2023-01-07T18:37:43Z\",\"body\":\"@fushun1990 \\n\\n- What kind of help do you need? Do you want to attend GraalVM's offline meetings? None of these questions are relevant to the current issue. \\n\\n- Normally you just need to create a Gradle project and write unit tests for Mybatis Plus using GraalVM Native Build Tools Gradle Plugin. You can then collect GraalVM reachability metadata by executing Gradle tasks and manually adjust and execute nativeTest. \\n\\n- You major need to read the https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md and https://graalvm.github.io/native-build-tools/latest/gradle-plugin.html . In any case, you must first finish see https://www.graalvm.org/22.3/docs/ , of course, all the documents, to understand why we want to collect GraalVM reachability metadata.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/159#issuecomment-1374568931\"},{\"author\":{\"login\":\"vjovanov\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-04-27T09:28:52Z\",\"body\":\"Human intervention needed\\n\\nThe automated job failed for `com.baomidou:mybatis-plus-boot-starter:jar`.\\n\\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-159-library-new-request-com.baomidou-mybatis-plus-boot-starter-jar-9fdc0fb6\\n\\nThe most likely failing stage was artifact discovery feeding test generation. In `logs/com.baomidou:mybatis-plus-boot-starter:jar/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log` (also mirrored in `build/agent-artifact-discovery-logs/com.baomidou-mybatis-plus-boot-starter-jar.log`), the run was asked to resolve the exact version `jar` for `com.baomidou:mybatis-plus-boot-starter`. Maven metadata shows only normal numeric versions for this artifact, and the attempted fetch for `.../mybatis-plus-boot-starter/jar/mybatis-plus-boot-starter-jar.pom` returned HTTP 404 `NoSuchKey`. The generated discovery output in `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/com.baomidou-mybatis-plus-boot-starter-jar.json` therefore fell back to `N/A` for `source-code-url`, `test-code-url`, and `documentation-url`.\\n\\nThere is no generated `tests/src/com.baomidou/mybatis-plus-boot-starter/...`, `metadata/com.baomidou/mybatis-plus-boot-starter/...`, or `stats/com.baomidou/mybatis-plus-boot-starter/...` output in the preserved worktree, and no matching run metrics entry was recorded for this coordinate. That points to a bad coordinate/version input (`jar` being treated as the version) rather than a library-specific metadata or native-image test failure.\\n\\nSuggested manual next steps:\\n1. Re-run the new-library flow with the correct full coordinates including a real version, not `:jar` as the version.\\n2. Check the issue/pipeline input parsing so packaging/classifier is not being written into the version field for `library-new-request`.\\n3. After correcting the coordinates, regenerate discovery/test artifacts and verify `build/discovered-artifact-metadata/com.baomidou-mybatis-plus-boot-starter-jar.json` no longer contains `N/A` placeholders.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/159#issuecomment-4325787474\"}]}}]}}}\n/tmp/grm-5418-fix/metadata/org.apache.kafka/kafka-streams/3.6.0/reachability-metadata.json:132:      \"type\" : \"org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\",\n/tmp/grm-5418-fix/metadata/org.apache.kafka/kafka-clients/3.5.1/reachability-metadata.json:164:      \"type\": \"org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.BooleanSerializer\",\n/tmp/grm-5418-fix/metadata/org.apache.kafka/kafka-clients/3.5.1/reachability-metadata.json:188:      \"type\": \"org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.ByteArraySerializer\",\n/tmp/grm-5418-fix/metadata/org.apache.kafka/kafka-clients/3.5.1/reachability-metadata.json:356:      \"type\": \"org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.LongSerializer\",\n/tmp/grm-5418-fix/metadata/org.apache.kafka/kafka-clients/3.5.1/reachability-metadata.json:560:      \"type\": \"org.apache.kafka.common.serialization.StringSerializer\",\n/tmp/grm-5418-fix/metadata/org.ehcache/ehcache/3.10.8-jakarta/reachability-metadata.json:1281:      \"type\": \"org.ehcache.impl.serialization.LongSerializer\",\n/tmp/grm-5418-fix/metadata/org.ehcache/ehcache/3.10.8-jakarta/reachability-metadata.json:1295:      \"type\": \"o